title: green bean casserole
directions: Brown ground beef.
Add onion and salt to taste.
Add barley, carrots, celery, tomato soup and green beans (including juice). You may have to add a can of water.
Simmer slowly until barley is cooked.
When vegetables are tender you can cover casserole with biscuits and bake until biscuits are done or serve as is.
Good with thick slices of homemade bread and butter.

title: tuna frito pie
directions: Place tuna and Fritos in layers in casserole dish. Heat mushroom soup and milk in saucepan. Pour over tuna mixture. Place cheese slices over top. Bake in 375° oven for 30 minutes. Makes 4 servings.

title: indian pudding
directions: Boil in top of double boiler the milk.
Stir in corn meal. Cook 15 minutes, stirring often.
Stir in dark molasses; cook 5 more minutes.
Remove from heat; stir in butter, salt, ginger, sugar, egg, raisins and cinnamon.
Pour into greased baking dish. Bake for 1 1/2 hours at 325°.
Serve with vanilla ice cream or frozen yogurt.

title: pineapple upside-down cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Melt margarine in 1 (13 x 9 x 2-inch) pan over low heat.
Sprinkle brown sugar evenly over margarine. Arrange pineapple on top and decorate with cherries.
Pour prepared batter evenly over mixture in pan.
Bake 45 to 55 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.

title: chili
directions: Brown and drain hamburger. Put your chili beans, diced tomatoes, tomato sauce and onion in a crock-pot. Add hamburger. Season with chili powder until you like the way it tastes, the way you want it to. Let it simmer all day, stirring occasionally. Eat and you are done.

title: marinated apple cake
directions: Mix and let stand for 1 hour.
Blend in 3 cups flour which were sifted with 2 teaspoons baking soda.
Bake in greased tube pan at 350° for 1 hour or until done.

title: squash casserole
directions: Combine all vegetables in large bowl.
Combine soup and sour cream in small bowl.
Then add to vegetable mixture.
Set aside. In another bowl toss stuffing mix with melted margarine.
Layer the vegetable mix into a large, Pam-sprayed casserole dish, alternating with stuffing mix, ending with a layer of the stuffing mix on top.
Bake at 350° for about 30 to 40 minutes.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: spoon bread
directions: Place yeast in water.
Melt oleo and cream with sugar in large bowl.
Add beaten egg.
Mix together dissolved yeast and cream mixture, then add flour.
Stir until mixed well.
Place in airtight bowl and keep in refrigerator.
When ready to use, spoon in well-greased muffin pans and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
These are great, even more so for busy families.

title: kim's easter creation
directions: Cream butter, vanilla and salt.
Blend in condensed milk until smooth.
Gradually add sugar.
Blend well after each addition until mixture becomes very stiff.
Turn from bowl onto clean board and knead in remaining sugar.
Mixture should be smooth and not sticky. Cut mixture into desired number of pieces.
With palms, mold into egg shape.
Place on wax paper-lined cookie sheet.
Put in refrigerator to chill, several hours or overnight.
Dip eggs into dipping chocolate.

title: chocolate chip oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream together the oleo and shortening and then mix in the brown sugar and white sugar.
Then add eggs, one at a time. Dissolve the soda in the hot water and add to the dough along with the salt and vanilla.
Mix all ingredients well and add flour, oatmeal, chocolate chips and peanuts.
Mix well and bake for approximately 10 minutes at 350°.
These are great!

title: king ranch chicken
directions: Combine chicken, onion and green pepper.
Layer alternately with softened tortillas in large shallow buttered casserole.
Top with grated cheese and sprinkle with chili powder.
Add in order: chicken soup, mushroom soup and tomatoes.
Cook for 30 to 45 minutes at 350°.
Serves 8.

title: oven baked chicken and biscuits
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Mix dry ingredients in paper bag.
Place butter in oblong 13 x 9 1/2-inch pan.
Set in oven to melt.
Shake chicken in bag, 3 or 4 pieces at a time.
Place chicken skin side down in hot butter.
Bake 45 minutes.

title: black olive dip
directions: Mix mayonnaise and sour cream until blended.
Add remaining ingredients.
Season to taste with salt and pepper and Tabasco. Refrigerate at least one hour and up to 8 hours.
Serve with chips.

title: hot potato salad
directions: Mix last four ingredients and heat until cheese melts.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch greased dish over potatoes.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.
Cover with foil for the first 20 minutes.
Quick and easy.

title: spinach dip
directions: Thaw and strain spinach through a towel.
Chop onions and water chestnuts.
Add to spinach.
Mix in sour cream and mayo. Season with Cajun spice.
Serve chilled with crackers.

title: chicken breast
directions: Brown chicken breasts on both sides; place in casserole dish. Add mushroom soup and 1 can water in bowl and stir.
Pour over chicken breasts.
Cut stick of oleo around the chicken and place in oven for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Serve over hot rice.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Mix onion, celery, pepper, green beans, corn, celery soup and sour cream in large baking dish.
Melt margarine.
Mix with enough cracker crumbs to cover casserole.
Top with almonds.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: grandma lowe's barbecue sauce
directions: Boil for 15 minutes.
Add more water if necessary.
Pour over meat and bake.
Good with hamburgers.

title: fried green tomatoes
directions: Slice tomatoes (can use 2 large green tomatoes and 2 large ripe tomatoes).
Salt and pepper them and then coat with flour. Fry in skillet in oil until brown.

title: fireside hodge podge
directions: Brown hamburger, onion and Italian sausage.
Precook lima beans.
Place all other ingredients in Dutch oven.
Add hamburger mixture and lima beans.
Bake 1 hour at 325°.

title: 100-year-old oatmeal cookies
directions: Sift flour and resift 2 to 3 times with salt, soda and spices. Beat egg; add sugar; mix well.
Add melted shortening, molasses and water; beat vigorously.
Add flour mixture.
Mix well.
Stir in oats, raisins and nuts.
Drop by tablespoon on greased cookie sheet.
(Mash with fork dipped in sugar - optional.)
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: apple crisp
directions: Pare and slice apples in baking dish; add water, flour, sugar and cinnamon.
Work
in
butter.
Spread over apples and bake until apples are cooked
and
top
is
brown.
Serve with cream.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Set aside to chill. When thick enough add pineapple, 1/2 c. chopped celery and 1/2 c. chopped nuts.

title: zucchini and yellow squash casserole
directions: Mix all except 1/2 cup stuffing.
Pour into lightly greased casserole and top with remaining stuffing.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until golden brown.

title: chicken and noodle casserole
directions: Combine all (set aside some noodles for top).
Bake in 9 x 12-inch dish at 350° until good and hot 1/2 to 1 hour.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix the first 8 ingredients together by hand.
Add the flavoring, nuts and bananas.
Bake in a greased and floured tube pan at 350° for 1 hour and 15 to 20 minutes or bake in 3 greased and floured regular size coffee cans or other small cans of equal size at 350° for 1 hour.

title: mushroom supreme
directions: Clean mushrooms; slice very fine.
Melt butter in saucepan with onions and parsley; simmer.
Add mushrooms and juice of lemon, continue to simmer until mushrooms have absorbed liquid. Then dust with a little flour.
Gradually, add consomme stirring until thickens.
Cook slowly for 15 minutes.
Before serving, add cream and seasonings to taste.
Makes 6 servings.

title: pasta e fagioli soup
directions: Heat oil in large skillet or soup pot over medium-high heat. Add beef and saute, stirring to break up, about 5 minutes, or until beef loses pink color.
Add onion, carrots and celery; simmer 10 minutes.
Place 1 cup hot water in small bowl and add bouillon granules to dissolve.
Stir bouillon mixture, oregano, black pepper, parsley, pepper sauce and pasta sauce into skillet. Simmer 10 minutes.
Add 1 quart water, or enough to reach desired consistency, stir and simmer about 30 minutes.
Stir in beans. Stir in pasta just before serving.
Makes about 1 gallon.

title: coated pecans
directions: Put all ingredients, but vanilla and pecans, in a saucepan. Cook until a ball forms when dropped in cold water.
Stir in vanilla and pecans.
Mix well and let cool.

title: low sodium seasoning
directions: Mix together and store in an airtight container.
This makes a lot, so plan to share.
Delicious on everything, especially scrambled egg or soup.

title: poppy seed cake
directions: Mix all together and pour into a greased and floured Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes (checking after 30 minutes). Cool 10 minutes.
Turn out and sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: bridal brunch french toast
directions: Preheat oven to 375 degrees.
Combine butter and sweetener in a 9x13 baking dish.
Set in preheated oven until butter is melted. Remove from oven.
Layer 1/2 slices of bread in two rows, overlapping edges of bread.
Beat eggs with milk in mixing bowl. Pour over bread.
Bake for 15 minutes, or until bread is firm. Remove from oven.
Cover with fruit and powdered sugar and serve. If you want glazed side on top, flip toast with spatula.

title: white castle appetizers
directions: Brown hamburger.
Cool.
Add onion soup mix and cheese. Separate rolls and cut in half.
Place meat and cheese filling in center; bring the 3 sides to middle and pinch closed.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes in 375° oven until golden brown.
Makes 32 appetizers.

title: tasty meatballs
directions: Soak bread in water and then squeeze water out, but not completely dry.
Add bread to meat, then season with onion and garlic salt, some oregano, pepper and Parmesan cheese.
After blending the ingredients together, form into meatballs.
Put in a pan on a rack with some water in the bottom of the pan.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.
May be also baked as a meat loaf.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Thin cream cheese (room temperature) with 2 tablespoons milk. Mix
all ingredients and add 1 can shrimp	(I
like
2 cans). Drain and rinse shrimp in cold water.

title: graham cracker cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter together.
Add beaten egg yolks, milk and salt.
Beat well.
Roll graham crackers very fine and mix with baking powder. Add to butter and sugar.
Mix.
Add vanilla and fold in 3 stiffly beaten egg whites. Bake in 2 layer pans at 350° for 25 minutes.
Let cool and frost with whipped cream.

title: dump cake
directions: Pour cherries and pineapple (juice and all) into a 9 x 12-inch pan.
Mix.
Dump dry cake mix over fruit evenly.
Dot with margarine; sprinkle with pecans, cinnamon and a little sugar. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cucumber salad
directions: Place cucumber slices in a large bowl.
Sprinkle with salt; cover with water and let stand for 45 minutes.
Drain; place on paper towels and pat dry.
Combine sour cream and remaining ingredients in a bowl.
Add cucumber slices, tossing to coat. Cover and chill at least 1 hour.
Yields 2 to 4 servings.

title: blender banana bread
directions: In blender container, chop walnut meats for 8 to 10 seconds until chopped.
Pour into large mixing bowl; add flour, baking powder and salt to bowl.
In blender container, place bananas, butter, sugar, egg and blend for 6 seconds, pushing down the bananas to process.
Pour over mixture in the bowl.
Stir until blended and pour into a greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Great warm or toasted!

title: peach ice cream superb
directions: Wash and chill 4-quart ice cream container and dash.
Chill thoroughly.
Force peaches through food mill or food processor. Stir the sugar and lemon juice into peaches; set aside for 20 minutes.
Combine the cream, salt and extracts; mix with peaches until well blended.
Fill freezer to fill line with ice cream mixture and follow freezing directions.
Makes about 3 quarts.

title: lazy man brunswick stew
directions: Saute onion in bottom of large pan until tender.
Add all other ingredients.
Simmer on low, stirring occasionally until well heated.

title: salmon "things"
directions: Drain salmon and save 1/4 cup liquid.
Put salmon in a bowl and flake.
Add egg and flour; mix well.
Stir in pepper and onion.
Mix baking powder into reserved liquid and beat until it foams.
Add to salmon mixture.
Drop by teaspoonfuls into hot oil. They are done almost instantly.
Drain on a paper towel.

title: party salad
directions: Combine Cool Whip and Eagle Brand milk in large bowl; chill 1 hour, then add other ingredients.
Stir well and refrigerate overnight.
Top with cherries if desired.

title: after school crunchies vegie dip
directions: Mix in a bowl cream cheese, sour cream and tomato juice.
Add dry Ranch salad dressing mix.
Mix well. Cut up some raw vegetables for dipping.
Dip and munch.

title: pineapple cheese cake
directions: Combine graham cracker crumbs, butter and sugar; mix well. Press into bottom of 9 x 13-inch baking dish.

title: favorite brownies
directions: In small saucepan, melt butter and blend in chocolate.
Beat eggs well.
Gradually add sugar to egg mixture until light and fluffy (about 10 minutes with electric mixer).
Stir in chocolate mixture and vanilla.
Fold in just until blended the flour, salt and walnuts, if desired.
Pour into greased pan (13 x 9 x 2-inch). Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until shiny and firm on top.
Cool completely.
Frost, if desired.
Makes 24 brownies.

title: pie crust(nine-inch)
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Combine flour and salt in mixing bowl. Blend with fork; cut in Crisco until uniform.
(Mixture should be fairly coarse.)
Sprinkle in water; toss with fork.
Work dough into ball, roll out in circle.
Put on pie plate and bake.

title: lemon pepper pork, noodles and veggies
directions: Preheat broiler to 500°.
Arrange pork chops and mushrooms on rack of broiler pan.
Drizzle chops and mushrooms with soy sauce, then sprinkle lightly with garlic powder and heavily with lemon pepper to taste.
Allow to marinate at room temperature up to 30 minutes to allow flavors to develop or prepare ahead of time and marinate in refrigerator up to 1 day in advance, if desired.

Broil chops and mushrooms, turning once, about 4 to 5 minutes on each side or to desired state of doneness (after turning first time, drizzle chops and mushrooms with additional soy sauce, garlic powder and lemon pepper).

title: pecan pie
directions: In medium bowl with mixer at medium speed, beat eggs slightly. Beat in next 5 ingredients.
Stir in pecans.
Pour into pie shell. Bake at 350° for 55 to 65 minutes or until knife inserted between center and edge comes out clean.
Cool.
Makes 1 (9-inch) pie.

title: oven-barbecued pork ribs
directions: Coat a large nonstick skillet with cooking spray.
Place over medium heat until hot.
Brown ribs on both sides.
Add sherry and 1/2 cup water.
Cover, reduce heat and simmer for 1 1/2 hours. Combine remaining ingredients in a saucepan.
Simmer, uncovered, over medium heat for 1 hour.
Transfer ribs to a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Pour sauce over ribs and bake at 300°
for 1 hour.

title: scalloped tomatoes
directions: Spread 2 tablespoons margarine over toast.
Sprinkle with garlic salt and cut into cubes.
Combine tomatoes, onion, salt and pepper.
Place cubes in a greased 1 1/2-quart casserole and add tomato mixture.
Pour remaining melted margarine over top.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.
Yields 6 servings.

title: shrimp mold
directions: Soften gelatine in 1/4 cup cold water; set aside.
Heat soup; add cheese until it boils (low heat).
Stir in gelatine until dissolved.
Mix all other ingredients; add soup mixture.
Blend. Oil a mold; let set 4 to 6 hours.

title: corned beef quiche
directions: Saute green peppers with butter. Add drained mushrooms. Set aside to cool.

title: green bean corn casserole
directions: Mix green beans, corn and onion in 9 x 9-inch pan.
Spread celery soup, Cheddar cheese and sour cream over vegetables. Place Ritz crackers and oleo on top.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: chris' famous hot fudge sauce
directions: Melt butter and chocolate in double boiler.
Stir in sugar, 1/4 cup at a time.
(Mixture becomes dry.)
Add salt, then milk slowly.
Cook 7 or 8 minutes.
Add vanilla.
Makes 1 quart of yummy sauce.
Never fails, never crystallizes.
Store in refrigerator.

title: ham pinwheels
directions: Blend first 5 ingredients in small bowl.
Separate 1 package rolls into 4 rectangles.
Pinch dough at markings to seal.
Spread each rectangle with 3 tablespoons ham mixture.
Starting at short end, roll-up.
Pinch dough to seal.
Cut each roll into 8 slices. Place on large cookie sheet.
Repeat with remaining package of rolls and ham filling.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes or until golden brown.
Serve hot or cold.

title: chived stuffed eggs
directions: Boil eggs 12 minutes, shell and halve.
Remove and mash yolks. Add yolks to other ingredients.
Mince fresh chives and sprinkle on top.

title: instant cocoa mix
directions: Combine all ingredients well. Store in an airtight container. To serve, use 1/4 cup cocoa mix per cup of hot water.

title: pocket sandwich
directions: In a small bowl combine all ingredients except lettuce and pita bread.
Refrigerate to chill.
Fill pita pockets with ham salad and shredded lettuce.
Makes 2 cups of spread.

title: squash relish
directions: Mix squash, onions, bell pepper, hot pepper and salt; set overnight.
Rinse in 2 water baths.
Mix sugar, vinegar, nutmeg, turmeric, celery salt and black pepper.
Boil both mixtures together for 20 minutes.
Put in hot jars.

title: rice with green chilies
directions: Saute onion, celery and green pepper in butter, adding more butter, if needed.
Combine with cooked rice, sour cream, salt and chilies (seeded and chopped).
Spread mixture in a greased casserole, saving half the mixture.
Sprinkle cheese and half the Monterey Jack cheese over top of mixture.
Add remaining rice mixture and top with remaining Monterey Jack.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: party punch
directions: Mix well.
Garnish with orange slices, strawberries or maraschino cherries.
Makes 25 cups.

title: bacon roll-ups
directions: Melt butter in water; remove from heat.
Add stuffing, egg and sausage.
Chill one hour.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Lay crescent rolls out on a cookie sheet to form a crust. Bake as directed on package.
Cool.
Mix cream cheese, mayo and dressing mix.
Spread on crust.
Top with vegetables and sprinkle with your choice of cheese.
You can use any vegetable you like.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Add enough water to the pineapple juice to make 2 cups.
Bring this to a boil and add jello.
Stir until dissolved, then add the cold water, pineapple and pie filling.
Mix well.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch Pyrex dish.
Chill until set.
Add topping.

title: hobo bread(raisin roll)
directions: Mix raisins, soda and boiling water.
Let stand 8 hours or overnight.
Add sugar, flour, cooking oil, and salt.
Bake at 350° in coffee cans.
Be sure to grease and flour the cans.

title: skewered grilled potatoes
directions: Place potatoes in water in a 2-quart casserole dish and cover. Microwave on High 12 to 15 minutes, stirring after 8 minutes. Drain.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Stir in potatoes.
Cover. Refrigerate 1 hour.
Drain, reserving salad mixture.
Arrange potatoes on grill with tongs or on skewers over coals.
Grill, covered, for 4 minutes.
Rotate skewers or turn on grill.
Brush with reserved salad dressing mixture.
Continue grilling for 4 minutes.
This recipe gets lots of rave reviews!
Makes a great summer dish.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: finger licking sweet potato pie
directions: Blend potatoes and sugar with mixer.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Beat after each addition. Add butter, milk and vanilla. Pour into pie crust and bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: oatmeal pancakes
directions: In mixing bowl, combine all dry ingredients.
Add buttermilk; blend well.
Lastly, add beaten eggs and mix well.
Cook pancakes in usual manner.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown hamburger meat and onion in skillet.
Boil macaroni according to package directions and drain.
Mix soups and water; add to hamburger.
Bring to a boil then mix in macaroni.
Pour in casserole dish and bake at 425° for 30 minutes.

title: italian cream cake
directions: Combine buttermilk and soda. Let stand.
Beat egg whites stiff.
Cream oleo and shortening slightly.
Add sugar.
Add egg yolks, one at a time, beating after each addition.
Add buttermilk, alternately with the flour to cream mixture.
Stir in vanilla.
Fold in egg white.
Gently add pecans and coconut.
Bake in 3 layer pans for 35 to 45 minutes.
Check with toothpick.

title: egg quiche
directions: Butter baking dish (9 x 13-inch).
Place bread pieces in bottom of dish.
Mix onions and ham, then place over bread.
next, spread grated cheese over ham, then sprinkle with flour.
Beat together eggs, mustard, milk and garlic salt; pour over cheese. Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serves 8 people.

title: champagne salad
directions: Cream sugar and cream cheese.
Add strawberries, pineapple, bananas and nuts.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Freeze.
Set out 1/2 hour before serving.
Use 9 x 13-inch Pyrex dish.

title: beef and potato casserole
directions: Place potatoes on bottom of an 8 x 12-inch dish.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.
Brown beef; drain.
Layer meat, broccoli, 1/2 can onions and tomato.
Mix soup, milk, 1/2 cheese and seasonings. Pour over meat mixture.
Bake, covered, at 400° for 20 minutes. Top with rest of cheese and onions.
Bake, uncovered, for 2 or 3 minutes.

title: oyster crackers snack
directions: Mix all ingredients until liquid is absorbed. Shake or stir. Toast 10 minutes at 400°.
Stir after 5 minutes.

title: shrimp louis
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Chill.
Mound on tray and surround with crackers.
Serves approximately 35.

title: "cary's hot dog surprise"
directions: Mix all ingredients, except rolls, together in bowl.
To make sauce, may add more or less mayo and mustard.
Fill hot dog rolls with mixture and roll in foil.
Bake in oven at 425° for 20 minutes.

title: quick & easy salmon patties
directions: Drain salmon; set aside 2 tablespoons of the juice. In a medium bow, l mix salmon, egg and onion until sticky. Stir in flour. Add the 2 tablespoons salmon juice. Form into small patties, and fry until golden brown (about 5 minutes) in hot cooking oil. Serve with tartar sauce or seafood sauce. Serves 4-6.

title: english muffin loaves
directions: *Measure by spooning flour lightly into cup.

title: porcupines
directions: Mix all ingredients together except tomato juice; roll in balls.
Put in a casserole.
Turn 1 can of tomato juice over them. Place in a preheated 350° oven.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes or until done.

title: easy lemon pie
directions: Mix together. Pour into a graham cracker pie crust. Refrigerate about 1 hour before serving.

title: barclay's herbed chicken
directions: Sprinkle chicken with salt and pepper and brown well in margarine.
Place chicken pieces in baking pan (9-inch square or 9 x 13-inch cake pan).
Let drippings cool a bit and add soup and wine, stirring until smooth.
Add remaining ingredients and bring to a boil over medium heat.
Pour over chicken pieces. Bake in 350° oven for 25 minutes, covered, and 20 minutes, uncovered.
Serve with rice.

title: bacon bobs(hot appetizers)
directions: Cut bacon slices in half; dip into mixture of Sauterne and soy sauce.
Wrap around chicken livers and potato bites.
Each appetizer should have a piece of liver and a potato bite with the bacon wrapped around.
Thread on skewers or fasten each with a wooden pick.

title: chocolate chip cake
directions: Mix well and cook in greased Bundt pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Put on rack to cool 10 to 15 minutes.
Do not let cool completely.
Turn out.

title: potato sauerkraut casserole
directions: Brown ground beef.
In 9 x 9-inch pan, layer 1/2 of the potatoes, then the sauerkraut and ground beef.
Cover with rest of potatoes.
Cover mixture with chicken soup mixed with 1 cup milk. Lightly salt and pepper, then sprinkle cheese over the top.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for about 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: double boiler bread pudding
directions: Spray bottom and sides of double boiler with vegetable spray coating.
Put brown sugar in prepared pan, then put bread cubes over sugar.
Do not stir.
Beat eggs with milk.
Pour over bread. Do not stir.
Sprinkle with nutmeg.
Steam for 1 hour; cool. Serve warm or cold.

title: chicken breasts with orange glaze
directions: Melt margarine in 8-inch skillet over medium heat.

Cook chicken in margarine about 15 minutes, turning once, until juice of chicken is no longer pink when center of thickest piece is cut. While chicken cooks, mix cornstarch and mustard in small bowl. Stir in remaining ingredients.
Place chicken on serving plate. Cover to keep warm.
Discard any juices left in skillet.

title: cherry jello salad
directions: Pour pineapple with juice into saucepan.
Cook over medium heat until juice boils.
Remove from heat and carefully pour over cherry Jell-O in bowl.
Stir until dissolved.
Chill in refrigerator until cool and starts to thicken.
Remove from refrigerator.
Stir in oranges, cottage cheese and topping.
Pour into square dish; refrigerate until firm.

title: carrot cake
directions: Combine all ingredients and bake at 350° for 45 minutes in a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Brown and drain sausage.
Pour eggs over sausage in pie shell. Sprinkle grated cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: arabian peach salad
directions: Drain peaches!
Combine vinegar, sugar, peach juice and all spices.
Simmer for 10 minutes (covered).
Then strain!
Add hot water (1/2 cup) to dissolve gelatin and add 1 cup cold water. Chill slightly until salad begins to thicken and then fold in peaches and nuts.

title: "philly" miracle whip cheese ball
directions: Combine cream cheese and salad dressing, mixing until well blended.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well.
Roll into a ball and chill. Garnish with chopped parsley and pimento just before serving, if desired. Serve with crackers.

title: beef tips
directions: Cook, covered, 4 hours at 275° in electric skillet.
Serve over rice or noodles!!!!!!

title: sweet and sour mustard sauce(microwave)
directions: Combine sugar, salt and cornstarch.
Mix in mustard, oil and vinegar.
Mix all together well and add 3/4 cup hot water. Microwave 30 seconds on High; stir, then 1 minute on High; stir, then 1 minute more.
Delicious over cauliflower or other vegetables.

title: apple butter
directions: Make applesauce from the apples to your own preference.
Add the cider vinegar and sugar.
Bake at 350° or 400° for 4 hours or until the proper consistency is obtained.
Remove from oven and add the spices.
Mix well.
Pour into jars and seal immediately.

title: easy pecan pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°; place pie shell in 9-inch deep dish pie plate.
Combine all ingredients except 1/2 cup of pecans.
Pour into pie shell; arrange 1/2 cup of pecans on top of pie.
Bake for 1 hour.

title: tutti-fruitti punch
directions: Combine lemon, pineapple, orange and cherry juices.
Mix well. Pour over ice in punch bowl.
Add ginger ale.
Garnish with cherries.
Makes 25 cups.

title: seeded parmesan pull-aparts
directions: In oven, melt margarine in 8-inch or 9-inch round cake pan, tilting pan to cover bottom.
Sprinkle onion, dill seed, poppy seed and celery seed evenly over melted margarine.
Separate dough into 10 biscuits.
Cut into 4 pieces.
Place biscuit pieces and cheese in a bag; shake to coat.
Arrange coated biscuit pieces evenly in prepared pan.
Sprinkle with any remaining Parmesan cheese from bag.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 18 minutes or until golden brown. Turn onto serving plate.
Serve warm.
Makes 10 servings.

title: potato pancakes
directions: Wash and peel potatoes.
Then drop them into cold water and let stand 1 to 2 hours or overnight, if desired.
Grate potatoes with a fine grater and press to squeeze out excess liquid.
Peel and grate onion into the potatoes.
Add the egg, seasonings and soda.
Mix well.
Heat 1 1/2 teaspoons butter in a large skillet and add one spoonful of the mixture for each pancake.
They should not be too thick.
Cook gently until golden brown on the bottoms, then turn and brown the other side.
Add more butter to the skillet and continue cooking the pancakes until all the mixture is used.
Serves 4.

title: peach dump
directions: Dump peaches with juice in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Sprinkle cake mix over peaches.
Sprinkle walnuts over top.
Melt butter and pour over top.
All cake mix should be moist.
Bake at 350°
for 35 minutes.
Cool.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: chicken stroganoff(weight watchers; crock-pot)
directions: Put frozen chicken in bottom of crock-pot. Mix soup, sour cream and onion soup mix and pour over chicken.
Cook on low for 7 hours. Makes 6 servings.

title: chicken casserole(my kids favorite)
directions: Combine all ingredients reserving 1/4 cup cheese into a 3-quart casserole dish.
Sprinkle with seasoned salt and cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or microwave on High about 15 minutes.

title: salsa layer dip
directions: Mix sour cream, cream cheese and dry Ranch mix and salsa. Spread beans in 9 x 13-inch dish.
Add salsa mixture.
Layer tomatoes, green onions and olives.
Top with Cheddar cheese. Serve with corn chips.

title: blue cheese dressing
directions: Add chilled milk to lemon juice, stir until thick.
Add remaining ingredients, stir well.
Makes 3 cups.

title: impossible pie
directions: Mix eggs well; blend in sugar and flour.
Add remaining ingredients.
Beat well.
Pour into two greased pie plates.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: franks on a stick
directions: You will also need 12 wooden sticks.

title: microwave strawberry-rhubarb jam
directions: Slice rhubarb into 1/2-inch slices.
Hull and slice strawberries.
Combine rhubarb, strawberries and pectin in a 3-quart casserole dish.
Cover loosely.
Microwave on High for 8 to 10 minutes or until full boil.
Stir occasionally.
Stir in sugar until dissolved.
Cover and microwave on High 8 to 10 minutes or to a full boil.
Uncover and microwave on High 1 to 2 minutes until mixture sheets from spoon.
Skim off foam.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Pour into hot jars.
Seal.
Makes three (8-ounce) jars.

title: seafood mousse
directions: Combine tomato soup and cream cheese in top of double boiler. Heat until cheese is melted.
Soften gelatin in cold water; add to soup mixture, stirring until dissolved.
Cool.
When mixture begins to thicken, add other ingredients and pour into a mold and chill until firm.
This can be used as a luncheon dish or spread on crackers for finger food entertaining.

title: bran muffins
directions: Soak Bran Buds in boiling water.
Cream sugar and shortening. Add eggs, one at a time, beating.
Combine flour, salt and soda. Add to first mixture alternately with buttermilk.
Add Bran Flakes and Bran Buds.
Raisins and nuts may be added to taste.
Pour into greased muffin tins.
Cook at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Makes 2 quarts.
May be refrigerated.

title: sausage-egg-hash brown casserole
directions: Brown sausage and drain.
Line a casserole dish with hash browns; sprinkle sausage over all.
Add beaten eggs that you have added 1/2 milk, salt and pepper.
Pour over hash browns and sausage.
Bake at 350° for approximately 1 hour.

title: banana nut cake
directions: Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Bake in tube or Bundt pan.
We eat this like a pound cake with no frosting.
You can use frosting if desired.
Use frosting recipe below.

title: cider egg nog
directions: Whip together first 6 ingredients.
In a crock-pot, heat apple cider.
Add the ingredients you whipped together.
Take your whipping cream and whip it.
Put on top of cider mixture.
Serve hot.

title: peanut butter and jelly quesadilla
directions: Spread the peanut butter and jelly between two tortillas. Place the tortillas on the grill, medium range, until both sides turn golden brown on both sides.
Make sure to flip the tortillas. Serves 1 to 2.

title: holly cookies(christmas)
directions: Melt marshmallows and butter over low heat.
Stir in vanilla and coloring.
Pour over corn flakes.
Mix carefully until all flakes are coated.
Drop by buttered teaspoonful onto waxed paper. Decorate with red hots candies.

title: potato chip cookies
directions: Cream the margarine and sugar.
Add vanilla.
Slowly add flour, mixing well.
Add chips.
Put rounded teaspoonful on ungreased cookie sheet.
Flatten with fork dipped in flour.

title: chicken beer bake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Dredge chicken in flour, salt and pepper.
Brown in butter, then place in casserole dish.
Combine other ingredients and pour over chicken.
Bake until tender, about 1 hour.

title: corn casserole
directions: Beat all of the ingredients in 2-quart oven-safe casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Makes a delicious side dish for most meals.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: smoked christmas turkey
directions: Rub turkey with all the ingredients.
Place turkey in shallow pan.
Bake at 400° in cup of boiling water and oleo.
Bake 4 hours. Bake until tender.

title: super diet malt
directions: Put all in blender and let whip until thick.
Umm good.

title: black bottoms
directions: Add cream cheese, egg, 1/2 cup sugar, 1/8 teaspoon salt and chocolate chips.
Set aside.
Sift together flour, sugar, cocoa, baking soda, 1 teaspoon salt, cooking oil, water, vinegar and vanilla; beat well.

title: spritz (butter) cookies
directions: Cream all ingredients together. Put through cookie press onto greased cookie sheet. Bake 10 minutes at 400°. Keep an eye on these toward end of baking, as they burn easily.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Make graham cracker crust; place in 13 x 9-inch pan or springboard pan.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Grate rind from lemon and squeeze juice.
Mix rind and juice of lemon, applesauce, canned milk, pineapple and egg yolks.
Set aside.
Beat egg whites and gradually add sugar.
Fold this into the filling mixture.
Pour into crust.
Sprinkle an additional 1 to 2 tablespoons graham cracker crumbs on top.
Bake for 45 minutes.
Test with toothpick. Cool well before removing spring-board side.

title: peach jelly
directions: Blend peaches and measure.
Add sugar; cook 20 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add dry orange jello and peach or apricot jello.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash in salt water; drain and mash.
Add margarine while squash is still hot, then add rest of ingredients and mix well.
Pour into baking dish.
Sprinkle top with bread crumbs. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: potato cheese soup
directions: Clean the carrots (cut larger carrots into 2-inch sticks and quarter them lengthwise).
Scrub the new potatoes to remove the thin peel, but peel the larger ones.
Put the carrots, peas, beans, onions and potatoes into a pot.
Add boiling water just to cover.
Boil the cauliflower separately because it does not take as much time as the other vegetables (do not let them get overcooked).
Cook for 5 minutes or until the vegetables are almost tender.

title: caramel corn(microwave)
directions: Place popcorn in a 4 to 6-quart microwave-safe utensil. Combine sugar, margarine, syrup and salt in a 1-quart glass bowl. Microwave on High for 1 1/2 minutes.
Stir.
Microwave on High for 2 to 2 1/2 minutes more.
Add baking soda and vanilla.
Stir well. Pour mixture over popcorn, stirring to coat evenly.
Microwave on High for 2 minutes, stirring midway through.
Turn out on a piece of waxed paper to cool.

title: vanilla ice cream
directions: Beat eggs at medium speed.
Mix all ingredients until sugar dissolves.
Pour in freezer tank.
Add more milk to fill tank.

title: sad cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until golden brown. Can be frosted if so desired.

title: cracker pudding with strawberry topping
directions: Heat milk to boiling.
Mix finely rolled cracker crumbs and sugar.
Stir into hot milk, stirring, until it thickens.
Beat eggs; add a little hot pudding to eggs, then stir into pudding. Bring to a boil.
Remove from heat and add vanilla.
Cool.

title: triple chocolate cake
directions: Mix together cake mix and pudding mix.
Add oil, eggs and water, mixing well.
Add chocolate chips.
Put in a Bundt pan that has been sprayed with Baker's Joy.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: bacon cheese potatoes
directions: Peel the potatoes; place in a saucepan and cover with water. Cook until tender, but firm; drain and cube.
In a bowl, mix potatoes with the onion, cheese and mayonnaise.
Transfer to an ungreased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle with bacon and olives.
Cover and bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until heated through.
If desired, sprinkle with parsley and paprika.
Yields 8 to 10 servings.

title: crockpot tacos
directions: Brown ground beef and drain well. Place in crockpot, add remaining ingredients except taco shells, lettuce and taco sauce. Cover and cook on low for 8-12 hours. Fill taco shells with meat mixture, top with sauce, shredded lettuce and other toppings of your choice.

title: zucchini-pineapple bread
directions: In large bowl, mix together first 7 ingredients and set aside. In another bowl, cream eggs, sugar, oil and vanilla together.
Fold in zucchini and crushed pineapple.
Next, fold in dry ingredients. Preheat oven to 350° and bake in 2 greased loaf pans for 40 to 45 minutes.
Let cool 20 minutes before removing from pans.

title: yellow rice casserole
directions: Cook rice according to package directions, omitting oil or margarine. When done, mix with all other ingredients and pour into casserole dish. Add more cheese on top, if desired. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: kolaches
directions: Beat eggs first, then add sugar, salt and milk.
Dissolve yeast in 1 cup lukewarm water, then add 3 cups flour.
Beat well, then add 1/2 cup oil.
Mix good.
Add rest of flour a little at a time. Let dough stand 1 hour.
Make into kolaches (about the size of a dinner roll with a "well" in the middle).

title: chocolate ice cream roll
directions: Line 15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch jelly roll pan with foil. Generously grease foil.
Preheat oven to 375°.
Beat egg yolks 3 minutes on medium speed.
Gradually add 1/2 cup sugar; continue beating 2 minutes.
Combine flour, cocoa and 1/4 cup sugar.
Add to egg yolks alternately until smooth.
Add vanilla and set aside. Beat egg whites until foamy, add 1 teaspoon sugar.
Beat until stiff peaks form.
Carefully fold in chocolate mixture; until well blended.
Spread evenly into prepared pan.
Bake 14-16 minutes or until top springs back when touched.
Invert onto slightly dampened towel.
Carefully remove foil.
Immediately roll cake and towel together from narrow end.
Let stand 1 minute.
Unroll. Reroll without towel.
Cool completely.
Unroll and spread with Ice cream.
Reroll immediately.
Freeze for several hours or overnight.
Slice and serve with chocolate sauce.

title: crab mold
directions: Heat soup.
Add gelatine to water and add to soup.
Add the next 5 ingredients to soup.
Drain and flake crab before adding. Grease a 4-cup mold.
Cool overnight.
Garnish with parsley.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Combine stuffing mix, margarine, chicken broth and soups with stewed chicken, removing meat from bones.
Place 1/2 stuffing mix in bottom of 9 x 12-inch casserole dish.
Put in all of chicken. Pour soup and broth mixture over chicken.
Put remaining stuffing mixture on top.
Bake for 30 minutes at 325°.

title: stuffed eggplant
directions: Parboil eggplant until
tender,
but
not soft.
Cut in half and scoop out
the
inside,
but
do
not break the skin. Heat the drippings; add
onion
and
gruond
beef and let them brown and partially cook.
Add the bits of eggplant and refill the shells. Lay bacon
strips
over the top.
Place in a 350° oven for 10 minutes or until finished cooking.

title: chocolate chip meringue cookies
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff.
Slowly add sugar as you continue to beat.
Add vanilla and chocolate chips.
Drop by teaspoon on foil covered cookie sheets.
Bake 35-45 minutes at 250° oven. Turn off oven, but leave cookies in oven until cool.

title: harvest cake
directions: Mix sugar and apples; let set 1 hour. Add eggs; stir in remaining ingredients. Mix well and beat for 2 or 3 minutes. Add nuts. Pour into a large greased and floured tube pan. Bake 1 hour at 325° until cake tests done. Yield: 10 to 12 servings.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix together all ingredients and form into a ball.
Roll in chopped pecans.
Serve with crackers.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix by hand and pour in unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350°. Center will not shake.

title: "lite" caraway swiss chicken(serves 4)
directions: In frying pan, use spray or a little oil to brown chicken. Turn down heat and simmer in its own juice until done (45 minutes to 1 hour).
Add a little water to pan if chicken gets dry cooking.
As chicken simmers, cook spinach; drain well.
Also make sauce.
(You can double sauce recipe if you want to have sauce to pour over rice or noodles as part of menu.)
Combine and whisk milk, cornstarch, bouillon, caraway seed and pepper until smooth. Cook and stir on medium heat until thickened and bubbly.
Add cheese and blend until melted.
Carefully watch because sauce may burn, so adjust heat lower if needed.
Use serving platter and arrange spinach on platter.
Place chicken on top and spoon sauce over chicken.
Slices of lemon added on each side makes a colorful presentation.
Good for when company comes.

title: white texas sheet cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour a 15 x 11-inch jelly roll pan.
Put margarine and water in large saucepan.
Bring to a boil.
Add sugar and beat well.
Remove from heat and stir in flour, salt and eggs.
Beat to mix.
Add buttermilk, baking soda and vanilla, beat thoroughly.
Pour into prepared pan.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes or until cake springs back at touch.
Pour on frosting immediately.

title: pecan cream candy
directions: Mix and cook
until
small
ball
forms.
Beat until it starts to thicken.
Add 1 quart shelled pecans.
Beat until it forms by spooning on waxed paper.

title: tabbouleh (salad)
directions: Wash burghul twice in cold water and pick up hulls, if any. Soak the burghul 1/2 hour in lemon juice.
Prepare the vegetables and place in a large bowl.
Add the burghul to the vegetables and mix in the dressing made by combining the oil, lemon juice and seasonings, just before serving.
Place the Tabbouleh in a large bowl and surround it with romaine lettuce leaves standing on end. Put the center leaves on a separate plate for use in scooping up the salad.
Fresh grape leaves make a delicious substitute for the lettuce.
Thr proportion of vegetables and wheat can vary greatly according to taste.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Boil the first 4 ingredients on top of stove for 1 minute. Remove from stove. Add the peanut butter.
Mix until melted. Add the vanilla, oatmeal or Rice Krispies, coconut and walnuts.
Drop on wax paper.

title: clam chowder
directions: Cook potatoes, onion and seasonings in kettle until tender. (Cover potato mixture to about 1-inch over the mixture with water.)
When done, add milk, clams and corn.
Bring to a boil slowly.
Simmer 20 minutes.

title: chicken salad
directions: Remove bones from breast.
Cut breast in small cubes.
Add bell pepper, onion, celery, salt, pepper and vinegar to breast and mix well.
Add Miracle Whip.
Refrigerate for 30 minutes.

title: tuna macaroni casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Saute celery, onion and green pepper in oil until tender; stir in flour, salt and pepper until smooth. Gradually stir in milk.
Cook, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Add cheese and stir until melted.
Add macaroni, tomatoes, tuna, parsley and lemon juice.
Pour into casserole and sprinkle paprika over top.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: breakfast ham and egg casserole
directions: Spread butter on both sides of bread and cut into small cubes. Combine bread cubes, ham, cheese, salt and pepper; stir well. Beat eggs until foamy; add the milk.
Add to ham mixture; stir well.

title: gloria's crumb apple pie
directions: Mix 1/2 cup of the sugar and 1 teaspoon cinnamon and sprinkle over thinly sliced apples that are filling the pastry shell.
Mix 3/4 cup flour,
the remaining 1/2 cup sugar and cut 1/2 cup of butter or margarine into the sugar and flour mixture until crumbly. Sprinkle over top of apples. Bake in a 400 degree oven for 40 minutes.

title: potato salad
directions: Place potatoes in a large salad bowl.
Separate eggs.
Chop whites and add to potatoes with onion.
Toss gently.

title: texas hash
directions: Saute onion and green pepper in fat.
Add beef and fry until beef is done.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Pour into greased 2-quart casserole.
Cover.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Remove cover last 15 minutes.

title: cheeseburger 'n' fries casserole
directions: In a large skillet, brown ground beef; drain well.
Stir in soups.
Pour into a greased 13x9x2 baking dish.
Arrange French fries on top.
Bake uncovered, at 350 degrees for 50 minutes or until fries are golden brown.

title: orange salad
directions: Blend with mixer the cottage cheese and Jell-O. Use spoon to blend in Cool Whip and pineapple, then blend in the mandarin oranges. Pour into oblong dish and refrigerate until set.

title: sugar free strawberry pie
directions: Add Jell-O, pudding and lemon juice to 2 cups water; bring to a boil.
Cool for at least 30 minutes.
Add Cool Whip and strawberries to mixture.
Pour into a cool baked pie crust; garnish with Cool Whip and strawberries.

title: banana pudding
directions: Makes one large or two small puddings.

title: grandma's blitz torte
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add egg yolks.
Alternate milk and flour.
Mix this dough gradually and spread in 2 (9-inch round tins).
Beat the egg whites stiff.
Add the powdered sugar or granulated sugar gradually; spread on top of batter.
Sprinkle nuts on top.
Bake for 25 minutes at 350°.
(Do not make a day ahead, as this torte is best served the same day as it is made.)

title: orange cake-candy slice
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs one at a time.
Add flour alternately with buttermilk.
Roll nuts, candy and dates in 1/2 cup flour (1/2 cup in addition to the listed amount).
Add to mixture along with coconut.
Bake in tube pan at 250° for 2 1/2 hours.
After the cake is done, mix 1 cup orange juice with 2 cups confectioners sugar and pour over cake while hot.
Let set in pan overnight.
(Grease and flour pan.)

title: basic bread pudding
directions: Spread	 bread	cubes
evenly
in
8-inch
round
dish. Sprinkle
evenly
with
brown
sugar
and
salt, then raisins. Measure milk into
quart measuring cup or bowl.	Add butter and microwave at
High	4
minutes
until butter is melted and milk is warm.
Rapidly
stir in eggs with a fork and mix well. Pour over bread
cubes in dish.
Microwave at Medium-high 9 to 12 minutes, rotating
dish
turn
after 6 minutes.
When cooked, center may
still	be slightly soft but it will set up as pudding cools.

title: tuna burgers
directions: Mix all ingredients. Fill hamburger buns and heat in oven at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix sugar,
flour,
salt
and cocoa, then add egg yolks and milk.
Cook in double boiler until thick.

title: date-nut fingers
directions: Add salt to egg whites, beat to stiff foam.
Sift sugar with flour, add to egg whites, one tablespoon at a time.
Continue beating until very stiff.
Fold in nuts, dates and vanilla.
Drop from teaspoon onto cookie sheet covered with plain paper, shape in fingers; bake in slow oven at 300° for 30 minutes.
Makes 2 dozen.

title: mini sausage and cheese muffins
directions: Mix all ingredients and spoon into mini muffin tins.
(I use Baker's secret pans and they don't need any preparation like oil or spray.)
Bake at 350° until nice and golden brown, approximately 15 minutes.
Makes approximately 40 muffins.

title: japanese fruit pie
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix meal, salt and onion.
Add boiling water to moisten. Beat egg and baking powder until light and fluffy and add to meal mixture.
Form into small balls and fry in deep fat.

title: ham cooked in wine
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients.
Cook ham at 325°.
Baste every 10 minutes.
When ham is done, remove skin from top and apply jam. Score.
Turn oven to 450°.
Brown.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Put all ingredients, except pie shells, in mixing bowl; beat until well blended.
Pour into two 9-inch pie crusts.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, or until firm when tested.
Serve with whipped cream topping, if desired.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Mix rice, soup, vegetables and water together.
Put into baking dish and lay pork chops on top.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour, until meat is tender.

title: quick homemade chili
directions: Lightly brown beef in skillet.
Add onion and garlic.
Cook until tender and clear; drain fat.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer, stirring occasionally, for 45 minutes.

title: hoppin john soup(kentucky recipe)
directions: Brown sausage and onion until color changes, breaking up sausage mixture. Add vegetables.

Cook rice and add to the meat mixture along with the black-eyed peas. Cover with water or chicken broth about 1-inch above mixture. Salt and pepper. Cover and simmer about 2 hours. Most of the liquid should be absorbed.

title: mock champagne punch
directions: Combine all ingredients in a punch bowl; add an ice ring, if desired.
Yields 6 1/2 quarts.

title: mashed turnips
directions: Melt butter and saute minced onion until brown.
Add turnips, salt, sugar, paprika, cayenne pepper and egg.
Beat well.
Stir and heat the turnips over low heat and serve piled in a mound garnished with fresh parsley.

title: for the hunter - rabbit-sausage
directions: Cook meats together until well done.
Take off bone. Mix well. Add pepper, salt and sage.
Make in balls.
Fry until golden brown.

title: magic finger jello
directions: Dissolve gelatin in 1/2 cup cold water.
Bring 1 cup water to a boil and add jello.
Bring to boil again and remove from heat. Add gelatin mixture and 1/2 cup cold water.
Pour into lightly greased pan.
(I use Pam.)
Chill in refrigerator until solid. Cut with cookie cutters and store in an airtight container in the refrigerator.

title: asparagus souffle
directions: Beat eggs in blender; add remaining ingredients and blend. Pour into lightly greased 1 1/2-quart souffle dish.
Place souffle dish in a second pan and add 2 inches of water.
Bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes or until a knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Serves 6.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Mix by hand.
Pour into ungreased sheet pan (10 x 15-inch). Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: clubhouse chicken salad with honey mustard dressing
directions: Heat oil in skillet. Cook chicken until lightly browned, about 5 minutes. Combine chicken, rice, onion, pepper, artichokes, salt and pepper in a large bowl. Toss with dressing. Serve warm or at room temperature.

title: almond or mounds bars
directions: Mix well.
Press into an oblong pan.
Freeze about 1 1/2 hours.
Cut.

title: ranch style beef
directions: Brown beef and drain.
Stir in beans.
Heat until beans are hot.
Place chips on plate.
Cover with beef, beans and picante sauce.
Enjoy.

title: wassail(beverage)
directions: Stir and cook over low heat for 6 hours.

title: apple cake
directions: Blend sugar, eggs, baking powder and salt together.
Add vanilla. Mix in flour, oil and orange juice.
Mix well.
Grease and flour tube pan.
Layer batter, then apples. Bake 1 hour and 10 minutes at 350°.
Let cool 1/2 hour before removing from pan.

title: o'brien potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 1-quart casserole.
Cook potatoes in a little boiling salted water 10 minutes or until just tender.
Drain; turn into casserole.
Add onion, parsley, pimientos and green peppers.
Season with salt and pepper; toss lightly.
Sprinkle with butter.
Bake in a preheated oven 20 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: creamy cheese cake
directions: Combine crumbs, sugar and butter.
Press into 9-inch pan and chill.
Beat cream cheese until soft.
Blend in 1/2 cup milk.
Add remaining milk, sugar, vanilla and pie filling.
Pour into crust and chill.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix all ingredients, adding zucchini last.
Bake at 350° for about 20 to 25 minutes or until golden brown.

title: buffalo hills cake
directions: Bake cake as directed.
Let cake cool for 30 to 35 minutes. Cut 4 bananas in slices over the top of cake.
Spread strawberry filling on bananas.
Mix pudding mix with 1/2 cup milk.
Mix Cool Whip with pudding mixture.
Spread on cake.
Sprinkle pecans on cake.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Boil macaroni.
Mix cheese and macaroni.
Sprinkle with paprika, then put it into the oven until it is a little brown.

title: strawberry pie supreme
directions: Mix sugar and cornstarch.
Add syrup and water; bring to a boil.
Cook for 6 minutes.
Add jello and coloring.
Cool mixture. Wash and stem berries; place in pie shell.
Pour cooled mixture over berries.
Refrigerate.
Serve with whipped cream.
Enjoy!

title: squash pudding
directions: Cook and cream first 4 ingredients and cream like potatoes. Add all other ingredients except spices and mix well.
Sprinkle with nutmeg and cinnamon.
Bake at 350 degrees for 30 to 35 minutes in a 8 x 8 in. pan.

title: mother-in-law treats
directions: Put cheese and bacon in food processor or chopper.
Chop.
Add onion.
Blend to a fine mixture.
Spread over rye bread.
Bake in 400° oven approximately 7 minutes until brown.

title: fat-free honey mustard dressing
directions: In a medium bowl, whisk all ingredients together.
Pour over favorite salad ingredients.

title: broccoli-mushroom noodle casserole
directions: Saute broccoli, mushrooms, onion and salt lightly in margarine. Drain.
Toss with white wine.
Beat eggs.
Whisk in Ricotta cheese and sour cream.
Boil raw noodles; drain.
Mix together the broccoli mixture, egg mixture, the noodles and 2 tablespoons bread crumbs.
Spread into a buttered 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Top with Cheddar and 2 tablespoons bread crumbs.
Bake, covered, for 30 minutes and uncovered 15 minutes more in a 350° oven.

title: italiano zucchini(serves 4.)
directions: Chop onions, peppers and celery.
Place in a pan with garlic; saute in oil.
Add remaining ingredients; cook, covered, until zucchini is done.
Remove cover and evaporate tomato water.
Serve with sprigs of parsley on top.

title: whipped cream
directions: Chill undiluted Carnation milk in refrigerator or tray until soft ice forms around edges of tray, 15 to 20 minutes.
Pour into bowl; whip until it begins to thicken, about 1 minute and add lemon juice.
Whip very stiff, about 2 minutes longer.
Add sugar to taste and vanilla.
Use as topping on desserts.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix in order given; drop by teaspoonfuls on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake in a 325° oven until as brown as desired.

title: cream cheese mints
directions: Combine cream cheese, half and half and butter in a heavy saucepan.
Stir over low heat until cheese mixture is soft, creamy and butter is melted.
Blend in the frosting mix and stir to blend well.
Add peppermint extract and food coloring of your choice. You may divide the complete batch to make different colors.

title: homemade peach ice cream
directions: Put in blender the eggs, sugar and 1 can of milk.
Blend well. Pour into freezer tub.
Add peaches to blender and 1 can of milk and blend well.
Add salt and vanilla.
Pour into freezer tub and finish filling with milk.
Stir well and taste for flavoring. Freeze according to directions for your ice cream freezer.
Makes 1 gallon.

title: chicken salad
directions: Mix last 5 ingredients. Pour over chicken mixture. Refrigerate.

title: ed's creation
directions: Drain spinach to dry.
In baking dish, place artichokes and Italian dressing.
Pack spinach on top.
Blend margarine and cream cheese.
Cover spinach mix with margarine/cream cheese mix.
Put Parmesan cheese on top.
Bake until golden.

title: tiramisu
directions: In large bowl, beat together mascarpone and sugar until smooth, about 3 minutes.
beat in coffee liqueur.

title: swiss chicken
directions: Place chicken breasts in casserole.
Cover each with a cheese slice.
Combine soup and water, pour over chicken. Cover with stuffing.
Drizzle with melted butter.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: cornflake cookies
directions: Cream butter and both sugars.
Add beaten egg; mix.
Combine dry ingredients with creamed mixture.
Stir in cornflakes and coconut.
Drop by teaspoons onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake for 10 minutes at 350°.

title: krystal salad(aunt beach)
directions: Make red, green and orange jello in separate pans according to package directions.
Mix lemon jello, pineapple juice, sugar and water; heat until syrupy.
Make Dream Whip and fold into lemon jello mix.
Cut jellos in cubes and fold into Dream Whip, lemon jello mix.
Serve in glass bowl.
Keep refrigerated until ready to serve.

title: black forest cheesecake(light dessert, low-fat)
directions: Spread cookie crumbs on bottom of a 9-inch spring-form pan with cooking spray.
Set aside.

title: gazpacho(mexican soup, cold)
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large container.
Cover and chill for at least 24 hours.
It gets better and hotter the longer it sets.
Serves 50.

title: chicken with rice
directions: Place the water, salt and margarine in a 2-quart pan with a tight lid.
Bring the water to a boil.
Add the rice and stir; put the lid on the pan and turn the heat to low.
Simmer for 20 minutes.
Do not take off the lid and do not stir again.

title: bess' butterscotch pies
directions: Mix and cook until thick.
Pour in baked shells.

title: spiced pineapple pickles
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving 3/4 cup syrup (or use 3/4 cup pineapple juice).
Mix this with the rest of the ingredients. Heat to boiling and simmer for 10 to 15 minutes.
Pour over pineapple chunks.
Cover and chill.
Serve well drained.
Keeps indefinitely in "fridge."

title: pickled shrimp
directions: Layer shrimp and onions.
Pour marinade over shrimp and onions.
Refrigerate 1 to 3 days stirring occasionally.
Lift shrimp, onions and capers using a slotted spoon, into a serving dish.
Serve with crackers or on a lettuce leaf as an individual serving.

title: easy sherbet
directions: Dissolve gelatin in hot water.
Add other ingredients.
Freeze until thick 1/2 inch from edge of refrigerator tray.
Empty into mixing bowl and beat.
Return to freezer.

title: easy yeast rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in water; add remaining ingredients.
Mix well after each addition.
Spoon into muffin tins sprayed with Pam. Bake at 400° until brown, about 15 minutes.
Refrigerate unused portion.
It will keep about 1 week.

title: peppermint roll
directions: Mix cake as per box.
Pour into a wax paper-lined jelly roll pan.
You will not use all the batter.
Bake, keeping close eye, so that it does not burn.
Remove cake by inverting onto a tea towel.
Remove wax paper and roll up from short end with towel inside.
Let cool.

title: pineapple salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water and cut marshmallows in small pieces.
Stir into jello.
Cool slightly and mix in cream cheese. Set aside to stiffen.
Just before mixture is congealed, whip with rotary beater.
Add pineapple, mayonnaise and fold in whipped cream.
Chill until set.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: steak rolls (grilled)(tender, marinated flank steak!)
directions: Cut flank steak into 1/2-inch strips.
Roll each strip into a roll approximately 3-inches in diameter.
Fasten each roll with a toothpick.
Combine all remaining ingredients in a blender and blend until smooth.
Place meat in a glass dish.
Top with marinade and allow to marinate overnight.
When ready to cook, place steak rolls over a hot fire and cook 5 to 6 minutes per side for medium done.
Do not overcook.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Mix together in baking pan.
Then add salt, pepper and sugar to taste.
Sprinkle cracker crumbs on top.
Melt 2 sticks butter. Pour over top.
Let bake until top is brown in 350°
oven.

title: low-fat pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta according to package directions.
Drain, rinse and chill pasta.
Toss remaining ingredients with pasta.
Chill and serve.

title: cattail corn bread
directions: Cream honey and margarine together.
Add remaining ingredients in given order.
Pour into well-greased pan.
Bake at 425° for 25 minutes.

title: go-further hamburgers
directions: Mix ingredients except	beef and fat.
Add beef and mix thoroughly.
Shape into
12 thin or 6 thick burgers.
Heat fat in a heavy
frypan
over moderate heat.
Brown burgers on both sides, turning once.
Reduce
heat
and
continue	cooking, if needed, until meat is
no longer pink when a knife is inserted into its center.
Thin
burgers
take
about
minutes total cooking time and thick ones, about 16 minutes.

title: easy banana bread
directions: Mash bananas and sugar together with a fork; stir in the melted shortening and beaten egg.
Add the dry ingredients and a dash of vanilla; also 1/2 cup broken walnuts, if desired.
Bake in greased loaf pan at 350° for 1 hour.

title: hot tamale pie
directions: Brown onion and meat in hot fat.
Add remaining ingredients. Pour into greased casserole dish.
Cover and bake in moderate oven at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Spread with corn bread batter and bake, uncovered, in hot oven at 425° for 22 minutes.

title: blueberry tea cakes
directions: Cream butter and sugar until blended.
Beat egg yolks and add. Add flour, alternating with milk.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Pour 1/2 batter into greased pan.
Cover with flour coated berries; add remaining batter.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: easy lemon pie
directions: Place eggs, sugar, margarine and lemon in blender.
Whip until well blended.
Divide in 2 pie shells.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
This recipe will make 12 tarts using the small tart shells.

title: spinach and cheese squares
directions: In large bowl, beat eggs; mix in bread crumbs.
Add remaining ingredients, leaving out Parmesan cheese.
Mix well.
Pour mixture into greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Sprinkle top with Parmesan cheese. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Let stand about 10 minutes before cutting.

title: apple dip
directions: In bowl, beat cream cheese, sugar and vanilla until smooth. Spread mixture on small plate.
Top with nuts.
Serve with apple wedges.

title: dad's favorite baked beans
directions: Wash and clean beans.
Cover with 2 inches of water.
Let stand overnight.
Next day, put in large pot.
Add water to cover. Bring to a boil and boil 2 minutes; remove from heat and let stand 1 hour.
Drain beans and add water to cover.
Bring to boil, lower heat and simmer, covered, for 1 to 1 1/2 hours, until tender (add more water, if necessary).
Drain.

title: hot spinach salad
directions: In a skillet, fry bacon as you like it.
Remove from fat.
To the fat skimmings (only as much as you desire), add 1/2 cup sugar, 2 tablespoons of vinegar and 1 1/2 tablespoons of flour.
Stir and bring to a boil.
Put in with the desired amount of spinach.
With a spatula, turn spinach in this mixture only once.
Immediately put into a dish.
Garnish with sliced, hard-boiled eggs.
Ready to serve.

title: pumpkin dessert
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix together Basic Mix, oats, 2/3 cup brown sugar and 1/4 cup margarine until crumbly.
Press into a 10 x 13-inch baking pan.
Bake for 8 minutes.
Beat together pumpkin, milk, eggs, sugar, salt, cinnamon, ginger and cloves.
Pour over hot oat mixture and bake for fifteen minutes.
Mix nuts, remaining brown sugar and margarine.
Sprinkle over hot pumpkin mixture and bake for 15 to 20 minutes, or until knife inserted in the center comes out clean.
Cool and serve with Spiced Whipped Cream, if desired.
Yield: 12 to 16 servings.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Mix milk with eggs.
Add salt, pepper and any other spice desired.
Crush 10 or 12 soda crackers.
Mix together with corn and top with more crackers.
Bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes (covered).
Uncover the last 10 minutes.

title: fettuccine supreme
directions: Beat cream cheese and 1/4 cup softened butter or margarine on low speed of electric mixer until blended.
Add parsley, basil and pepper; mix well.
Add boiling water.
Beat until mixture is smooth.

title: spinach balls
directions: Mix all together; chill well.
(Can be made a day or two ahead.)
Form into balls, walnut side.
Place on cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until set.
Can be frozen.
Makes at least 60 walnut size balls.

title: baked butternut or acorn squash(clara deariso's)
directions: Pare, remove seeds and fiber and cut into 1-inch cubes. Place squash
cubes
in
a
2-quart
buttered casserole dish. Sprinkle with
spices
and
brown sugar.
Drizzle with melted butter and lemon juice.
Bake, uncovered, in 375° oven for 45 minutes or until tender.

title: meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 300°. Put meat and onions in a bowl. Mix everything else together and then add to meat and onion. Mix well and shape into a loaf pan. Spices may be adjusted to taste, increasing the cayenne to really spice it up. Bake for about 1 1/2 hours. Cool and slice.

title: sweet and sour devil dogs
directions: Slice the hot dogs crossways into thirds.
Drain the pineapple, reserving 1/2 cup of the juice.
Blend the juice with the cornstarch.
Combine the catsup, onion slices, brown sugar, garlic and lemon juice in a 2-quart microwave-safe dish.
Stir the pineapple juice and cornstarch mixture.
Add the hot dogs, stirring to coat.
Cover with the casserole lid or vented heavy-duty safe plastic wrap.
Microwave on Full power for 5 to 6 minutes or until the sauce is bubbly and hot.
Add the pineapple chunks.
Cover the casserole.
Microwave on Full power for 3 to 4 minutes or until heated through-out.
Garnish the top of the casserole with lattice of mustard, if you wish.
Microwave on Full power for 10 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: lemon fluff
directions: Chill unopened can of milk in refrigerator until icy cold. Dissolve Jell-O in hot water.
Chill until partially set.
Whip Jell-O until light and fluffy.
Add lemon juice and sugar.
Whip chilled milk in another bowl until fluffy.
Fold in Jell-O mixture.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Combine celery, onion and green pepper in large bowl.
Chop sauerkraut and add to vegetables.
Add celery seed, sugar, vinegar, oil, salt and pepper.
Toss until well mixed.
Let marinate overnight.

title: gloria's cheese and spinach casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients reserving onions and grated cheese. Sprinkle cheese and Durkee onions over mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Dissolve the yeast in warm water and set aside.
Mix the dry ingredients in the order given, cutting in the shortening as normally done for biscuits or pie dough.
Stir in the buttermilk, also the water and yeast mixture.
Blend thoroughly and the dough is ready to be refrigerated in a large, covered bowl or made into biscuits.

title: custard pie
directions: Mix all together and bake 15 minutes at 415°.
Lower to 350°. Bake 45 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean. Shake nutmeg on top of pie.

title: glazed onions
directions: Peel onions; cook in boiling, salted water for 15 to 20 minutes or until tender.
Drain onions well, reserving 3/4 cup liquid.
In 10-inch skillet, combine butter, sugar and reserved liquid.
Cook and stir until blended.
Add onions.
Cook, uncovered, over low heat for about 25 to 30 minutes or until mixture glazes onions.
Garnish with chopped pimento.

title: super moist coconut cake
directions: Bake cake according to package directions.
Cool.
Mix sour cream, sugar and coconut.
Remove 1 cup of mixture and mix with Cool Whip.
Split cake into 4 layers using thread.
Frost 3 layers with sour cream mixture.
Place fourth layer on top and frost top and sides with Cool Whip mixture.
Store in Tupperware cake container in refrigerator at least 24 hours before serving.
Will keep 2 weeks.

title: chicken and veggie casserole
directions: Layer cooked, diced chicken in casserole.
Layer cooked vegetables on top.
Melt cheese and soup in water.
Pour this mixture over chicken and vegetables.
Prepare Stove Top as per box.
Layer on top of chicken.
Bake 1/2 hour at 350°.

title: tomato soup
directions: Melt butter in a medium saucepan, over medium heat.
Add onion and garlic and cook, stirring 6 minutes.
Add tomatoes, stock and oregano; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer for 45 minutes. Slowly add half and half, stirring constantly.
Season with salt and pepper.

title: southern pecan pie
directions: Mix sugar, syrup and butter together.
Add eggs and pecans. Fill unbaked pie shell with mixture.
Bake for 10 minutes at 400°. Reduce oven temperature to 350°.
Bake for 30 to 35 minutes longer.
Serve cold or hot.
Top with whipped cream, if desired.

title: chicken cordon bleu
directions: Place each chicken breast half between waxed paper; flatten to 1/4-inch thickness with mallet or rolling pin.
Place 1 slice ham and 1 slice cheese in center of each breast.
Sprinkle evenly with parsley.
Roll up lengthwise and secure with toothpick.
Dip each chicken roll in egg.
Coat well with bread crumbs.
Melt butter in heavy skillet; brown chicken on all sides.
Remove chicken to a 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish, reserving drippings in skillet.
Add remaining ingredients to drippings; stir well.
Pour sauce over chicken.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: lemon pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In mixing bowl, beat egg yolks.
Add condensed milk, ReaLemon juice and coloring.
Pour into crust.
In mixer bowl, beat egg whites with cream of tartar to soften peaks. Gradually add sugar.
Beat until stiff.
Spread on pie; seal to edges.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes.
Cool and chill.

title: spinach balls
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Spoon onto ungreased cookie sheet.
(Refrigerate for shapes.)
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: mexican layered dip
directions: Use party, flat dish (I've used a pie dish).
Spread out refried beans for bottom layer.
For next layer, spread olives. Mix the sour cream and taco powder and spread on for the next layer.
Next, layer the shredded Cheddar cheese.
Spread the avocado mixture for the next layer.
For top layer, spread cut up tomatoes with scallions.
Place nachos around the base of the dish.

title: french toast casserole
directions: Cut loaf into 1-inch cubes. Place into sprayed 9 x 12 baking dish. Whisk eggs in a bowl. Add sugar, vanilla, cinnamon and syrup; whisk again. Add milk and whisk again. Cover bread with chosen fruit (optional).
Pour egg mixture over the bread cubes and fruit (if used). Be sure to cover ALL pieces. Allow to soak overnight. Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Sprinkle with powdered sugar. Serve with warm syrup.

title: sweet cherry salad
directions: Stir all the ingredients together in a large bowl and chill well.

title: chicken divan
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook broccoli according to directions. Drain excess liquid.
Put in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Place chicken on top of broccoli.

title: baked cheese cake
directions: Beat the cream cheese until fluffy.
Then add the milk, eggs and lemon juice.
Pour this mixture into two graham crusts and bake 45 minutes or until set.
Cool.
Top with favorite pie filling.

title: venison meatballs
directions: Mix well.
Roll in balls.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes (turn after 10 minutes).
Cool, then freeze.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Place in ungreased casserole dish. Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: easy potato soup
directions: Add potatoes, onions and spices to broth.
Cook until tender. Add vegetables and cook.
Add milk, cheese and chicken.
Heat until cheese is melted.
Serve with crackers or crusty bread.

title: hershey kiss cookies
directions: Combine all ingredients except chocolate kisses.
Mix on low speed until dough firms.
Roll into balls and roll in sugar.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Remove from oven; place a kiss on each cookie.
Press until cookie cracks and place in oven for 1 to 2 minutes.

title: vanilla butternut cake
directions: Cream Crisco, sugar and oleo.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition.
Add flour and salt with milk.
Add flavoring.
Pour in a greased and floured tube pan.
Put in cold oven.
Set oven temperature at 350°. Bake for 1 hour and 45 minutes.
Do not open the oven door while baking!

title: mini pizzas
directions: Use as many biscuits as you need.
Pull each individual biscuit apart to make two.
Flatten biscuits in pan.
Brown sausage and hamburger, drain.
Spoon sauce over biscuits and add meats and any other desired toppings.
Top off with Mozzarella cheese.
Bake as stated on can of biscuits.
Great for meals or just as snacks.
Easy for children to prepare.

title: new england clam chowder
directions: Cube
pork
and fry out with onions.
Stir in flour and mix well.
Add clam juice.
Place in soup pot and add potatoes and garlic.
When
potatoes
are
nearly
done,
add hot milk gradually
and stirring constantly until thickened.
Add clams last. Season to taste.

title: spicy beef and vegetable stir-fry
directions: Cut beef into thin bite-sized strips.
Cut onion into thin wedges.
Cut zucchini into 2 x 1/4 x 1/4 inch strips and cut pepper into thin strips.
Spray large nonstick skillet with nonstick cooking spray.
Heat over medium-high heat until hot. Add beef and onion; cook and stir 3 to 5 minutes or until beef is no longer pink and onion is crisp-tender.
Add zucchini, bell pepper and garlic; cook and stir 2 to 4 minutes or until vegetables are crisp-tender.

title: punch
directions: Use Kool-Aid to add color (lime/green).

title: french bread dinner
directions: Slice off top of Italian bread.
Hollow out interior of loaf and set aside.
Brown beef, onion, celery, salt and pepper; drain. Mix together beef mixture, mushrooms, mustard, evaporated milk, bread crumbs from Italian bread and egg.
Place mixture into Italian bread.
Cover Italian loaf with aluminum foil.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.
Serves 4 to 5.

title: corn fritters
directions: Cook corn in pan of boiling water until tender, about 5 minutes.
Drain well.
Melt butter in heavy large skillet over medium heat.
Add corn and saute 3 minutes.
Add sugar and stir 2 minutes.
Transfer corn to small bowl using slotted spoon.
Set aside.
Mix dry ingredients in large bowl.
Stir in eggs, cream, chives and corn.
Heat 1 inch oil in heavy large skillet to 350°. Carefully drop by heaping tablespoonfuls into oil.
Cook in batches until deep golden brown and drain.

title: sweet chow chow
directions: Grind tomatoes, peppers, cabbage and onions.
Pour salt over mixture and mix all together.
Place mixture in cloth bag (pillow case) and hang outside (if not freezing) to drain overnight.

title: apple dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Serve with slices of Granny Smith apples. Better made a day ahead. DELICIOUS.

title: lazy fruit dessert
directions: Mix flour, sugar, and milk for the batter.
Melt butter in square baking dish (approximately 10 x 10 inches).
Pour batter mixture into the melted butter.
Add can of fruit pie filling. Bake at 350 degrees for 30 minutes.

title: english trifle
directions: Cover bottom of glass bowl with cake.
Sprinkle cake with sherry and set overnight.
Next morning, pour Jell-O, prepared with 3/4 require liquid, over cake.
Let set.
Cover with drained fruit cocktail.
Cover with pudding, prepared with 3/4 required liquid. Let set.
Cover with Dream Whip.
Decorate with cherries and nuts.

title: chicken and spaghetti casserole
directions: Cook chicken; keep broth to cook spaghetti in until done. Drain.
Cook broccoli as directed on package.
Mix all other ingredients in large bowl.
Place chicken in baking dish; add broccoli.
Pour over broccoli and chicken; salt and pepper to taste.
Cook 30 minutes at 350°.

title: milky clam chowder
directions: Drain the clams and add 1/2 cup water, chopped onion and (cut) potatoes in a small saucepan and cook until slightly tender.
(Or precook the onion and salt pork and then add to the liquid.)
Add the clams and cook gently (do not boil), then add evaporated milk and 1 can of water.
Add butter and salt and pepper to taste.

title: jimmy carter dessert
directions: Blend together flour, butter and crushed peanuts.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Cool.
Cream together cream cheese, peanut butter, powdered sugar and Cool Whip.
Spread on top of crust.
Mix vanilla and chocolate together and add the milk.
Mix until thickened.
Put on top of cream cheese layer.
Top with the remaining Cool Whip.
Keep refrigerated.

title: banana bread
directions: Sift dry ingredients in a bowl.
Cut in shortening.
Puree the bananas and add to the flour and shortening along with well beaten eggs.
Do not over beat.
Place in a 350° oven and bake 40 to 45 minutes.
Remove from oven and let stand 5 minutes.
Cool before slicing.

title: amazing coconut pie
directions: Combine in a blender for 3 minutes.
Pour into a greased 9-inch pie pan.
Let stand for 5 minutes and then sprinkle with 1 1/3 cups flaked coconut.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: sweet potato pudding
directions: Melt butter in glass dish, 9 x 9 in oven.
Mix butter and all other ingredients together.
Pour into glass dish and bake 45 minutes to 1 hour at 375°.
Stir 2 times while cooking.

title: pumpkin bars
directions: Bake in cookie sheet at 350° for 20 minutes (30 for long big pan).

title: quick and easy fudge
directions: Combine sugar, butter, salt and milk in 2 or 3-quart saucepan. Bring mixture to a full rolling boil over medium heat, stirring constantly, for 5 minutes. Remove from heat.
Add marshmallows, chocolate, vanilla and pecans.
Stir vigorously or beat with a spoon until marshmallows and chocolate are melted and mixture is smoothly blended.
Pour into buttered pan. Cool and cut into squares.
Yields 2 pounds.

title: pineapple pie
directions: Cook all until thick; pour into pie shell and bake at 400° until brown.

title: baked beans
directions: Combine all ingredients in a greased 1 1/2-quart casserole; stir well.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Warm cheese to room temperature.
Blend sugar and horseradish well with mixer.
Add fruit and pineapple.
Mix well, using a big spoon.
Pour into 8 muffin cups and put in freezer.
Take out when frozen and serve on lettuce leaf.
Top with poppy seed dressing.

title: chicken-italian style
directions: Place chicken in Pyrex dish.
Pour dressing over chicken. Salt and pepper.
Bake in oven for 1 hour at 350°.

title: soupe a l'oignon(french onion soup; france.)
directions: In a heavy 4 to 5-quart saucepan or soup kettle, melt the butter with the oil over moderate heat. Stir in the onions and teaspoon salt and cook, uncovered, over low heat, stirring occasionally for 20 to 30 minutes or until the onions are a rich golden brown. Sprinkle flour over the onions and cook, stirring, for 2 or 3 minutes. Remove the pan from the heat. In a separate saucepan, bring the stock to a simmer, then stir the hot stock into the onions. Return the soup to low heat and simmer, partially covered, for another 30 to 40 minutes, occasionally skimming off the fat. Taste for seasoning and add salt and pepper if needed.

title: pittsburgh potatoes
directions: Cook first 3 ingredients in boiling water to cover in a saucepan 15 minutes; drain and add pimiento strips.
