Cook cheese and next 4 ingredients in a saucepan over low heat, stirring constantly, until thoroughly heated and cheese melts.
Pour cheese sauce over potato mixture and spoon into a baking dish.
Top with breadcrumbs and dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Yield:
6 to 8 servings.

title: iced tea
directions: Boil approximately 2 quarts of water.
Pour into a glass bowl along with the tea bags and cover with glass plate.
Let stand 2 to 3 hours.
Squeeze out tea bags and pour liquid into a pitcher. Add sugar and lemon.
If not enough water, add some to bring it to 2 quart level.
Stir well.
Serve well chilled.

title: angel cookies
directions: Cream shortening; gradually add sugars, beating well.
Add egg, beat well.
Combine flour, soda and cream of tartar; gradually add dry ingredients to creamed mixture, mix well.
Add vanilla, mix well.
Chill dough, shape dough into 1-inch balls, roll in powdered sugar.
Place on lightly greased cookie sheet. Bake at 275° for 10 to 12 minutes; cool on rack.
Yields 4 dozen.

title: wild rice soup
directions: Melt butter in saucepan; saute onion until tender.
Blend in flour; gradually add broth.
Cook, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens slightly.
Stir in rice, ham, carrots and almonds.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Blend in half and half and sherry; heat to serving temperature.
Garnish with parsley or chives.

title: sauteed cherry potatoes
directions: Heat margarine in 12-inch skillet until melted.
Stir in water and honey.
Add tomatoes.
Cook and stir over medium heat until skins begin to split, about 3 minutes.
Carefully toss with parsley and basil.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water; set aside.
Cut Crisco into dry ingredients.
Place in covered container and store in refrigerator.
Pinch dough as needed.
Place biscuits on cookie sheet in cold oven.
Turn oven to 450°.
This will keep well in refrigerator.

title: copper pennies
directions: Cook the sliced carrots in simmering water about 20 minutes until crisp-tender.
Drain.
Blend the remaining ingredients, except chow chow, to make a salad dressing.
Combine carrots and chow chow with it.
Allow to marinate before serving.
Refrigerate.

title: chunky italian soup
directions: Brown ground beef and onions; drain. Add other ingredients and simmer for 30 minutes or longer. Stir in: kidney beans, green beans, carrot, and zucchini. Simmer at least 15 minutes.
Add rotini noodles, stir.

title: cornbread dressing
directions: Bake cornbread; crumble when cool.
Brown onions and celery in butter.
Add ground meat and brown.
Season well.
Add mixture to cornbread along with 1 dozen boiled eggs.
Moisten with milk adequately to wet cornbread.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until brown on top.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Wash, peel and cook carrots.
Set aside.
In a saucepan, mix and cook remaining ingredients for 7 minutes.
Pour over carrots. Let set overnight.

title: meat balls
directions: Mix ground chuck, bread crumbs, onion soup mix and eggs.
Shape into balls.
Place in dish.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour over meatballs.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: hash for barbecue
directions: Cook hog head or Boston butt and liver until tender. Grind up and put the rest of the ingredients in a large pot.
Cook real slow for 5 to 6 hours.
Stir often.
Will stick if cooked too hot and not stirred often.

title: k~f~c coleslaw
directions: Be sure cabbage and carrots are chopped up into very fine pieces (almost the size of rice).
Combine sugar, salt, pepper, milk, mayo, vinegar, and lemon juice in a large bowl and beat until smooth.
Add the cabbage, carrot and onion, mix well.
Cover and refrigerate at least 2 hours before serving.
Serves 10-12.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Cook beef with onion and celery until meat loses its red color.
Pour off fat.
Combine meat, onion and celery with remaining ingredients.
Cover and cook on low 3 to 4 hours. Serves 4 to 6.

title: low-fat carrot cake
directions: In a bowl, combine dry ingredients.
Add oil, puree, carrots and vanilla; beat until combined.
Stir in pineapple and coconut. Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes, until cake tests done.

title: calico baked beans
directions: Fry bacon, drain and crumble. Cook hamburger and onion together and drain.
Add catsup, salt, sugar, mustard and vinegar and mix well.
Add partially drained beans and bacon, mix well and pour into a 2 1/2-quart baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: baked macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni as label directs; drain.	Preheat oven to 350°. Grease 2 quart casserole.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Mix soup, milk, soy, pepper, beans and 2/3 c. onion in 1 1/2 qt. casserole dish.
Bake at 350 degrees for 25 minutes or until hot.
Stir then sprinkle with remaining onions.
Bake for 5 more minutes.
Serves 6.

title: scalloped eggplant
directions: Peel and cube eggplant.
Cook in boiling water until tender. Drain well.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Bake in greased casserole dish at 350°
for 30 minutes.

title: coconut pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into two unbaked pie shells.
Bake at 350°.

title: hungarian cabbage noodles
directions: In skillet, brown bacon until crisp.
Remove.
Stir in sugar and salt to drippings.
Add cabbage.
Stir until coated.
Cover and cook until tender 10 minutes.
Combine cabbage mix, cooked noodles and bacon.
Put in 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Cover and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Uncover and spoon sour cream over top. Sprinkle with paprika and bake 5 or 10 minutes more.

title: pea, cheese and meat salad
directions: In bowl blend mayonnaise, salt, pepper and minced onion.
Add thawed raw peas, cheese, meat, olives and mushrooms.
Blend well. If mixture is too dry, add small amount more of mayonnaise.
Place a leaf of lettuce on each salad plate and spoon a couple of tablespoons of mixture onto each leaf.
Garnish top with sliced egg and minced pickle.
Boneless ham or leftover pork or beef roast can be substituted in place of turkey ham.

title: banana nut bread(heart healthy)
directions: Fold flour and soda together.
Add sugar, melted margarine, egg white, bananas and nuts.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Put 1/2 of cornbread dressing in bottom of 9 x 9-inch square dish.
Add 1/2 of margarine and 1 cup of broth.
Layer pieces of chicken on top. Mix sour cream and soup together; spoon over top of chicken.
Add remaining cornbread dressing mix, margarine and broth. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: egg and bacon casserole
directions: Place butter in 11 x 7-inch dish.
Heat margarine in microwave enough to coat dish.
Remove from microwave.
Pour croutons over butter.
Sprinkle cheese over croutons; set aside.

title: simple ice cream pie squares
directions: Soften vanilla ice cream.
Mix with Cool Whip, nuts and 2/3 of cookies.
Spread in large shallow dish.
Sprinkle with remaining cookies.
Freeze.
Cut in squares when ready to serve.

title: green tomato relish
directions: Put tomatoes in bowl and cover with salt. Refrigerate over night. Mix celery seed, mustard & pickling spices. Tie in bag and add to the tomatoes that have been drained well. Add all others ingredients. Cook about 1 hour. Pack in jars and process about 10 minutes.

title: sally's szechuan string beans
directions: Cut string beans into 5-inch sections.
Soak shrimp in warm water for 5 minutes and chop into small pieces.
Heat oil in wok until very hot (315°) and deep fry string beans until just wrinkled, about 1 minute.
Remove beans and drain oil.
Put 3 tablespoons oil back into skillet and stir-fry pork.
Add ginger, shrimp, Szechuan, soy sauce, salt, sugar, sherry, water and string beans.
Stir well over high heat until sauce is gone.
Add vinegar and sesame oil and sprinkle chopped scallions over all, stirring evenly.
Remove from heat and serve.
Serves 6.

title: banana strawberry shake
directions: In blender, process all ingredients.
Place container in freezer for 30 minutes.
Process again for 1/2 second.
Pour into chilled glasses.

title: polynesian chicken
directions: Mix all together; pour over chicken to coat it.
Cover and cook at 350° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: good vegetables
directions: Cook cauliflower whole; cook broccoli; cook carrot slices.
Do not overcook.
Barely steam red pepper slices.
Arrange cauliflower in the middle of large dish.
Arrange broccoli, carrots and pepper around it.
Make cream sauce with salad mustard added, and some dill weed.
Add cheese too, if desired.
Pour over vegetables. Very good and attractive.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: vanilla ice cream(custard base)
directions: For extra rich ice cream, use all cream and omit milk.
Combine sugar, flour and salt in saucepan.
Slowly stir in hot milk, cook over low heat for about 10 minutes, stirring constantly, until mixture is thickened.
Mix small amount of hot mixture into beaten eggs.
Add to hot mixture and cook 1 minute longer.
Chill in refrigerator.
Add cream and vanilla.
Pour into gallon electric freezer.
Fill freezer about 2/3 full.
Serves 12 to 16.

title: salsa guadalajhara
directions: Finely chop fresh cilantro; add to juice of 2 limes and the olive oil.
Add salt and pepper.
Blend ingredients; set aside. Finely chop remaining ingredients.
Add oil mixture; blend.
Let marinate for several hours.
Can be served with tortilla chips or with crusty bread.
Great heated and served over pasta.
Enjoy many ways.
Refreshing and healthy!
Great for diets.

title: lemon bisque
directions: Dissolve jello in 1 1/4 cups hot water.
Let cool.
Chill milk until crystals form around edge.
Beat until stiff.
Add juice and grated lemon rind; add sugar, salt, then jello and beat thoroughly. Crumble graham crackers and line bottom of 10 x 10 x 2-inch Pyrex dish with crumbs.
Pour on mixture and sprinkle graham cracker crumbs on top.
Chill.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: broccoli cheese salad
directions: Toss broccoli, cheese, bacon and onion.
Make dressing with mayo, sugar and vinegar.
Toss together and refrigerate for several hours.

title: mushroom and tuna supreme
directions: Soak gelatin in 1/4 cup cold water for 5 minutes.
Stir 1/2 cup water and 2 egg yolks into soup and mix.
Cook 4 minutes in doubler boiler.
Add gelatin and stir until dissolved; cool slightly.
When it begins to set, add tuna, sprinkled with lemon juice.
Add stiffly beaten egg whites and pimento.
Pour into mold.

title: nanny girl's oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients. Place dough in freezer for 1 hour or refrigerate overnight.
Drop by teaspoonful on cookie sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 350°.

title: vegetable salad
directions: Use a large 9 x 13-inch pan.
Place layers in order given. Refrigerate 8 hours or more and cut into squares and serve.

title: hilo tuna casserole
directions: Melt butter.
Stir in flour, salt and paprika.
Add milk and cook until thickened.

title: michael's carrot soup
directions: In large pot, cook onions in butter until translucent.
Add all remaining ingredients.
Cook until carrots are soft.
Put in blender and blend until smooth.
Best if prepared a day ahead.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients together.
Mix dry ingredients and combine. Add chopped nuts.
Grease 2 loaf pans.
Divide batter and bake at 325° for 1 hour.
(Instead of loaf pans, a 9 x 14-inch oblong cake pan can be used.)

title: cheese filled peppers
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Cut and save tops of peppers.
Clean and chop together the parsley and garlic.
Trim crust off bread and shred it.
Moisten bread with enough milk to make about 1 1/2 cups of damp bread.
Put the bread-milk mix into a bowl.
Add garlic, parsley, cheese, salt and egg; mix well.
Add enough olive oil to make a soft paste.
Fill peppers; dot with butter.
Grease bottom of baking dish big enough to hold all peppers upright.
Put tops on peppers and bake for 30 minutes.

title: frontier hamburger soup
directions: Brown ground beef in
4-quart saucepan or Dutch oven over medium heat; drain.
Stir in remaining ingredients except cheese. Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer 15 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Sprinkle each serving with cheddar cheese, if desired.

title: poppy seed bread
directions: Mix first four ingredients together.
Add remaining ingredients and mix together.
Bake 1 hour and 15 minutes at 325°.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix and simmer for 10 or 15 minutes before using.

title: apple cake
directions: Combine apples, oil and sugar.
Add beaten eggs.
Sift together flour, soda, salt and cinnamon and add to batter.
Stir in vanilla and nuts.
Bake in greased 9 x 13-inch pan in 375° oven about 45 minutes.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Mix cream cheese,
sugar,
drained crushed pineapple, thawed strawberries, nuts and bananas.
Add whipped topping.
Mix well.
Freeze.
This will keep indefinitely.
It makes a wonderful light dessert.

title: tasty apple pudding
directions: Sift together flour, soda, cinnamon, nutmeg and salt.
Cream together sugar, butter and egg.
Cream until light and fluffy. Add shredded apples.
Blend in dry ingredients.
Stir in chopped nuts.
Pour into 8 or 9-inch square pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Cut into squares.
Serve hot with Pudding Sauce.

title: tea cakes
directions: Cream margarine and sugar well.
Beat in eggs and milk.
Add salt and flavoring. Sift flour and stir in enough to make stiff dough. Roll and cut out. Bake at 350° until brown.

title: t-gateau sec
directions: Beat sugar and eggs.
Cream with Crisco.
Add baking soda, vinegar and salt.
Add flavoring.
Start mixing flour and add milk alternately with baking powder.
Refrigerate mixture four days. This is done to harden the batter in order to form the cookies.

title: shrimp salad
directions: Boil noodles, cool in cold water.
Add celery, onions, pepper, eggs, shrimp and mayonnaise.
Mix well and salt to taste.

title: taco soup
directions: Brown meat in a large Dutch oven; drain.
Add rest of ingredients.
Do not drain liquid from cans.
Simmer for 2 hours.

title: lasagna
directions: In a large saucepan mix browned ground beef, garlic, parsley, basil, salt, tomatoes and tomato paste.
Bring to a boil, then reduce heat.
Simmer, uncovered, for 30 minutes, stirring frequently.
Cook noodles until al dente (firm to the bite); drain.
Combine cottage cheese, eggs, pepper, parsley flakes and Parmesan cheese.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Boil hen
with onion; add butter, milk and seasoning to taste.

title: mondo banana nut bread
directions: Combine sugar, shortening and egg; blend until creamy.
Stir in milk.
Blend in dry ingredients from sifter.
Add bananas and nuts. Bake at 350° for 60 to 70 minutes.

title: banana split cake
directions: Beat butter, sugar and eggs together; pour into a graham cracker crust in a 9 x 13-inch pan (2 1/2 cups graham cracker crumbs and 1 1/2 sticks of butter for the crust).
Then add a layer of pineapple.
Add a layer of sliced bananas.
Then top with Cool Whip.
Refrigerate.

title: microwave chicken casserole
directions: Mix Miracle Whip and milk together.
Pour mixture over everything in a glass container that will fit in your microwave. Mix until well coated.
Cook on High 20 minutes.

title: chicken spaghetti 2
directions: Saute celery, onion and green pepper in approximately 2 tablespoons oil.
Cook spaghetti in chicken broth.
Mix chicken and other ingredients together.
Add canned tomatoes, mushroom soup and cheese and English peas.
Keep a little of the cheese to sprinkle on top.
Bake in casserole dish 30 minutes at 350°.

title: crab soup
directions: Combine ingredients and cook for 1 hour on low.

title: yeast biscuits
directions: Place together in bowl, warm water and yeast.
Sift together flour, sugar, baking soda, baking powder and salt.
Cut into flour mixture the shortening.
Stir in buttermilk.
Next, mix in softened yeast mixture.
Pour out on floured board.
Turn over twice to flour both sides.
Roll to 1/2-inch thickness and cut out desired size biscuits.
Place in buttered baking pan and butter each biscuit on top if desired.
Place in 425° oven for 10 to 12 minutes.
This dough may be placed in refrigerator for use at a later time.

title: old-fashioned meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients in medium-sized bowl; blend by stirring lightly with 2-tined fork.
Spoon mixture into loaf pan (9 x 5 x 3-inches).
Bake in moderate (350°) oven about 1 hour or until meat is cooked to desired doneness.
Transfer to heated platter.
If desired, garnish with onion rings and additional chili sauce.

title: prize winning meat loaf
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Combine all ingredients except ground beef.
Mix well.
Add ground beef.
Mix lightly but thoroughly. Make into loaf.
Put in greased pan or dish.
Put several slices of bacon across top.
Bake for 1 hour.
Let stand 5 minutes before cutting.

title: turkey fruit salad
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Mix well.
Cover and chill for 2 to 3 hours.
Serve on a bed of lettuce with cantaloupe halves.

title: lemon creme bars
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Cream together butter and confectioners sugar; gradually stir in 1 cup pecans.
Using floured hands, put dough into ungreased 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Press down.
Bake 15 minutes.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: To form crust, press crescent rolls evenly onto an 11 x 17-inch jelly roll pan.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.
Let cool.

title: unbaked chocolate cookies
directions: Cook the first 4 ingredients 2 minutes, no longer.
Have remaining ingredients ready in bowl.
Mix all and drop on wax paper by teaspoon.

title: mexican bean salad
directions: Drain beans well, then add celery, onion, walnuts and pickles. Shake oil, vinegar, salt and pepper; toss with mixture.
Serve on lettuce.

title: taco pie
directions: Take a 9 x 13-inch pan; spray with Pam.
Spread beans on bottom.
Brown hamburg and onion; drain.
Add taco seasoning and water according to package directions.
Simmer until liquid is reduced.
Place this mixture over beans.
Place in microwave until hot or bake in a 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes.
Place Velveeta cheese slices on top until cheese melts.
Serve on bed of lettuce and tomato.
Top with favorite sauce.

title: special k candies
directions: Mix sugar and Karo syrup.
Bring to a boil.
Remove from heat. Stir in peanut butter.
Mix well.
Fold in cereal.
Drop on wax paper by spoonfuls.
Let cool and set.

title: rice pudding
directions: Pour milk into a 4-cup measuring bowl.
Microwave on High for 3 to 4 minutes or until steaming.
Mix together remaining ingredients in a 2-quart casserole until well blended.
Stir in hot milk.
Cover with a tight-fitting lid or plastic wrap. Microwave on Low for 20 to 25 minutes, or until a knife inserted near edge comes out clean.
Remove cover immediately and allow to stand on a solid surface until center is set.
Serve warm or cool.

title: risotto
directions: Saute onion in butter until golden brown.
Add tomatoes and simmer 10 minutes.
Add orzo (uncooked), water and cheese.
Season if desired.
Pour into 1 3/4-quart casserole dish.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: spinach dip
directions: Combine ingredients.
Stir to blend.
Chill at least one hour. Serve in hollowed round loaf of French bread.
Use hollowed section to make bread cubes for dipping.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Fix Jell-O by directions; cool.
Mix Cool Whip and sour cream. Mix with fruit; add to cooled Jell-O.
Chill and serve.

title: quickie dip
directions: In a bowl, gently blend spaghetti sauce mix into sour cream. Cover and chill.

title: lemon cream pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour and cornstarch. Add hot milk and cook in double boiler for 20 minutes.
Add beaten egg yolks, juice of lemons and rind of one. Take from heat and add butter.
Fold in 1 egg white.
Make meringue with the other two whites and spread on pie. Bake in high oven.

title: chocolate mousse
directions: Combine milk and gelatin; let stand.
Melt chocolate over low heat.
Stir in sugar and milk mixture into chocolate.
Beat in egg yolks (save egg whites) and salt.
Cook over medium heat, stirring, until mixture thickens slightly and coats a metal spoon. Add vanilla and let cool.

title: quiche(a french dish)
directions: Fry bacon and drain.
Grate Cheddar cheese into pie shells. Crumble bacon into shells.
Cut Swiss cheese into pieces.
Beat eggs and milk with salt and pepper.
Pour over cheese mixture in pie shells.
Bake at 350° for approximately 30 minutes.

title: chocolate gravy
directions: Mix sugar, flour, cocoa and salt well.
Heat milk over low heat.
Add small amount of hot milk to cocoa mixture.
Return cocoa mixture to hot milk, stirring well.
Cook until mixture thickens to desired consistency.
Add margarine and vanilla.
Stir gently.
Serve over hot biscuits.
Homemade is good but canned will do.

title: frosty sour
directions: Put all ingredients, except ice, into blender.
Cover and blend until smooth.
With motor running, remove feeder cap and add ice cubes.
Continue to blend until smooth.
Garnish with an orange slice and a maraschino cherry.
Yield: 3 cups.

title: parmesan broccoli
directions: Cook broccoli until nearly done. Fry onion in 3 Tbsp. butter. Blend in flour, salt and pepper. Add milk and cook until boiling, thickened and smooth, stirring constantly. Beat egg yolk lightly and add about half of the hot mixture to it gradually. Add rest of hot mixture and then cheese. Lay vegetables in a buttered casserole and pour sauce over. Mix melted butter and bread crumbs with a fork. Sprinkle all over. Bake for 15 to 20 minutes at 375 degrees or until crumbs are lightly browned and mix.

title: play clay
directions: Cook on medium heat until consistency of mashed potatoes, 10 to 15 minutes.
Put in bowl and cover while cooling.
Roll out and cut with cookie cutter.
Poke hole with toothpick for hanging. Paint with any paints to personalize.

title: hardee's biscuits
directions: Combine flour and baking powder. Cut in shortening. Stir in the sugar and add buttermilk. Stir until dough sticks together. Roll out 1/2-inch thick on well floured board. Cut out and bake in preheated 425° oven for 10 minutes.

title: milky way ice cream
directions: Melt candy bars in 2 cups whole milk in double boiler.
Cool and add to mixture of eggs, sugar, vanilla and evaporated milk. Pour into ice cream churn.
Finish filling container with whole milk.
Churn as usual.
Makes 1 gallon.

title: venison roast
directions: Take roast and make 4 slices about 1 1/2 inches deep and 2 inches apart in top side of roast.
Put bacon slices in the 4 slices you made.
Use wooden toothpicks to hold bacon in place while cooking.
Put salt and pepper on roast.
Put roast in a roasting bag.
Sit bag and roast in roasting pan.
Put water, butter and soy sauce in with roast.
Close bag.
Roast in oven at 325° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Open bag.
Put chopped carrots, mushrooms, potatoes and onion in bag with roast.
Cook for another 45 to 60 minutes.

title: poppin fresh barbecups
directions: Brown meat and drain.
Add sauce, onion and sugar to meat. Separate dough into 12 biscuits.
Place 1 biscuit in each cup of an ungreased muffin pan, pressing up to edge of cup.
Spoon meat mixture into cups.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: slaw
directions: Marinade overnight if possible.
Toss lightly and serve.

title: butternut pound cake
directions: Mix Crisco and sugar about 5 minutes.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add flour and milk.
Beat at medium speed for 2 minutes. Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli.
Drain, chop and if using chestnuts, add to broccoli.
Combine soup, mayonnaise, eggs and cheese.
Add to broccoli mixture.
Put in 9-inch square baking dish or 2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle cracker crumbs on top and dot with butter. Bake 35 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: oven bologna
directions: Mix hamburg and Tender Quick together.
Let stand overnight. Next morning, add the remaining ingredients.
Divide into 4 rolls. Bake at 250° for 2 hours.
Turn rolls every 1/2 hour.

title: fragrant carrot puree
directions: Scrape carrots and slice thinly.
Peel onion and slice thinly. Combine vegetables in saucepan and add just enough water to cook; boil, covered, until very soft.
Strain water from vegetables and place vegetables in food processor or blender.
Add all remaining ingredients and puree until smooth.

title: corn bread cakes
directions: Beat egg well; add salt, baking powder and milk.
Beat well. Add flour and meal (about 4 to 6 tablespoons) to desired thickness.
Batter should be thin.
Pour into hot greased baker and bake.

title: candy bar cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. In large bowl, cream the butter, eggs and vanilla. Add all of the dry ingredients. Stir until well blended. Drop by tablespoons onto greased cookie sheet. Bake 10 to 12 minutes. Transfer on wire rack.

title: steak pie
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Put in pie shell.
Top with top crust. Bake at 350° for 1/2 hours, then at
300° for 1 1/2 more hours. May have to lower to 275°.

title: rice salad
directions: Cook rice in water for 20 minutes.
Make sure it's dry before adding sugar and jello.
Cool for 2 hours.
Then add remaining ingredients.
Stir just before serving.

title: spiced pecans
directions: Beat
the
egg
white and water;
add spices and sugar. Mix thoroughly.
Add pecan halves and mix gently until all are coated. Spread
on
a cookie sheet.
Bake at 250° for 1 hour, stirring occasionally.

title: swiss steak
directions: Place meat on a cutting board and cover with seasoned flour and pound with meat hammer. Turn steak several times, pounding until all the flour is taken up by the meat.
Brown on both sides in drippings.
Add tomatoes and onions, cover pan and cook to boiling.
Reduce heat and simmer about 2 hours or until meat is tender.
Top with green pepper the last 10 minutes of cooking. Place meat on platter.
Blend cornstarch and water and stir into liquid; cook until slightly thickened.
Serve with rice while hot.

title: easy butterscotch sticky buns
directions: Grease Bundt pan.
Distribute walnuts or pecans over the bottom.
Arrange frozen bread dough rolls in pan.
Sprinkle butterscotch pudding over rolls.
Melt butter and mix brown sugar and cinnamon.
Drizzle mixture over rolls and pudding.
Cover with wax paper and let rolls thaw and rise overnight.
Bake in the morning at 350° for 30 minutes.
Immediately invert onto serving plate.

title: icebox fruit cake
directions: Put milk and marshmallows in double boiler.
Melt marshmallows and pour over the following: pecans, raisins, coconut and vanilla wafers.
Mash vanilla wafers real fine.
Put all in large pan. Mix well.
Pack in cake pan.

title: apricot salad
directions: Mix jello and pineapple (juice and all) in saucepan.
Heat to simmer.
Mix sugar, apricots and softened cream cheese with pineapple and jello.
When well blended, put in refrigerator and chill a bit.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Let chill for several hours.

title: squash dressing
directions: Fry bacon until brown.
Add onions and green pepper and cook until limp.
Add squash, cornmeal and flour mixture, crumbs, eggs, sage and salt and pepper.
Mix well.
Pour into buttered casserole dish.
Dot with butter.
Bake 15 minutes at 425°
or until brown.

title: cheese biscuits
directions: Combine flour, baking powder and salt.
Cut in shortening until it feels like cornmeal.
Stir in cheese.
Add milk; blend just to combine ingredients.
Roll out dough on floured surface. Cut with cutters and place on greased sheet.
Bake at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Makes 18 biscuits.

title: mushroom rice
directions: Melt butter and brown rice.
Remove to 1 1/2-quart casserole dish and pour remaining ingredients.
Add salt to taste.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: v-8 stew
directions: Season ground beef to your liking.
Roll into bite size meat balls.
Roll meat balls in flour.
Cut vegetables in bite size pieces and place in baking dish.
Cover vegetables with V-8 juice. Place floured meat balls on top.
Cover and bake until vegetables are tender.
Bake at 325° for about 1 hour.

title: hash brown dish
directions: Spread hash browns in pan.
When they thaw, mix the other ingredients in a separate bowl.
Pour over potatoes and top with butter and bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Let set for 6 hours or overnight.
Serve with raw vegetables or rye crackers or hollow out center of pumpernickel bread and use remaining bread for dipping.

title: elephant stew
directions: Cut elephant into bite size pieces.
This should take about 2 months. Cover with brown gravy and cook over a kerosene fire about 4 weeks at 450°.
If more than 3,800 people are present, add the rabbits. Do this only if necessary as most people do not like to find "hare" in their stew.

title: sweet potato waffles
directions: Beat egg whites to soft peaks.
Mix all other ingredients together and fold in beaten egg whites.
Cook on waffle iron.

title: shrimp mold
directions: Drain and mash shrimp with a fork.
In a double boiler, cream tomato soup and cream cheese.
In a large bowl, mix celery, onions, shrimp and mayonnaise.
Mix well.
Add soup mixture.
Add 2 or 3 dashes Worcestershire sauce and red pepper to taste.
Stir well.
Pour into well-greased mold and chill for 3 to 4 hours (preferably overnight).
Serve with crackers.

title: purple paradise
directions: Stir boiling water into gelatin in medium bowl for 2 minutes or until completely dissolved.
Measure one cup into small bowl; stir in cold water.
Refrigerate for 1 1/4 hours or until slightly thickened (consistency of unbeaten egg whites).

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: Mix Jell-O and 1 1/2 cups water.
Bring to a boil.
Add cornstarch mixed with 1/2 cup cold water to Jell-O and stir until it becomes clear and mixed well.
Set aside and let cool.

title: holiday salad
directions: Mix altogether and sit in refrigerator.
Serve when chilled.

title: crab-stuffed snow peas
directions: Combine all ingredients, except snow peas, mixing well. Chill.
Trim ends from snow peas. Using a sharp knife, carefully slit one side of each pod.
Spoon crab mixture into a decorating bag fitted with a tip with a large opening.
Pipe crab mixture into each snow pea.
Cover and chill.
Yield: 2 1/2 dozen.

title: blue cheese dressing
directions: Beat until fluffy and chill.

title: mrs. carter's soup
directions: Cook beans until done.
Drain off water.
Add all other ingredients.
Cook for 30 minutes.

title: ambrosia
directions: In
large
bowl mix pineapple and sprinkle the powdered pudding on top.
Let sit for about 3 minutes then combine nuts and coconut
and fold into mixture.
Blend in whipped topping and marshmallows
and refrigerate for at least 2 hours before serving. It serves 12 or more.

title: great barbecue sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients in saucepan.
Heat to boiling.
Let simmer 30 minutes.
Makes enough for basting 4 pounds loin back ribs.

title: strawberries and cream shortcake
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
In medium bowl, combine flour, sugar, baking powder, rind (if desired) and salt.
Cut in shortening until mixture is crumbly.
In a medium bowl, combine milk, egg and vanilla.
Add to dry ingredients, stirring just until moistened. Spread into 2 greased 8 or 9-inch round layer cake pans.
Bake for 10 minutes or until golden brown.
Remove from pans.
Cool completely.

title: buttercream frosting
directions: In a large mixing bowl, add 2 boxes of sugar and water; blend at low speed and work up to high speed.
Scrape bowl sides often. Add salt and flavorings.
Beat in Crisco, a little at a time, until all of it has been added.
Gradually add the last pound of sugar.
If the icing is too soft, add more sugar a little at a time.
If it is too stiff, add water a few drops at a time.

title: george's favorite bill martin's shrimp gumbo
directions: Saute celery, green onion, parsley, bell pepper, onion and okra in butter and water until tender.
Add tomatoes, tomato juice, soup, mushrooms, rice and shrimp.
Stir and simmer until well blended.
Add spices and stir.
Simmer 5 more minutes.

title: cream cheese fruit squares
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.

title: corn patch spam bake
directions: Mix these ingredients together in a casserole dish. Add cheese on top and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chocolate salad dressing cake
directions: Mix sugar and salad dressing.
Add cold water then dry ingredients; add vanilla.
Bake at 375° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: layer dip
directions: Mix in a bowl the sour cream and package of taco mix.
In a bowl or deep dish plate, layer bean dip, then pour over sour cream and taco mix mixture.
Shred lettuce and put on next.
Next, chop onion and also layer that.
Apply avocado dip. Top that with grated cheese. Apply chopped olives and then garnish with some chopped tomatoes.

title: company potatoes
directions: Coarsely shred the potatoes. Add cheese and melted butter. Add onions, salt, pepper and sour cream. Top
with melted butter. Bake in
a 350° oven until heated through.

title: 5-up salad
directions: Drain fruit.
Mix well and sprinkle nuts over top.

title: ann lander's meat loaf
directions: Thoroughly mix the ground round, eggs, bread crumbs, ketchup, Accent, water and soup mix.
Put into loaf pan, cover with strips of bacon, if desired.
Pour tomato sauce over top.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Serves 6.

title: peanut butter easies
directions: Melt oleo and peanut butter.
Mix in sugar.
Press into 13 x 9-inch pan.
Melt Hershey bars and pour mixture on top.
Let cool at room temperature.
Slice.

title: the ultimate chocolate chip cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Combine butter flavor Crisco, brown sugar, milk and vanilla in a large bowl.
Beat at medium speed until creamy.
Beat egg into creamed mixture.
Combine flour, salt and baking soda and mix into creamed mixture until just blended.
Stir in chocolate chips.
Drop 1 teaspoonful of dough about 2 inches apart onto ungreased cookie sheet.

title: mexican style salsa
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Refrigerate for several hours or overnight.

title: veggy surprise
directions: Spread roll dough in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake per package directions and cool.
Spread with cream cheese.
Cover with vegetables and sprinkle with seasoned salt.
Add alfalfa sprouts and cheese.
Pat down.
When cool, cut into squares and serve.

title: cocktail meatballs
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In large bowl, mix beef, cornflakes, parsley flakes, eggs, soy sauce, pepper, garlic powder, ketchup and onion.
Make meatballs the size of walnuts.
In another pan, combine cranberry sauce, chili sauce, brown sugar and lemon juice. Cook over moderate heat; stir occasionally until smooth and cranberry sauce is melted.
Pour over meatballs in baking dish. Bake uncovered 30 minutes.
Makes 60 meatballs.

title: sausage-bean chowder
directions: Brown bulk turkey sausage in large Dutch oven or stewpot. Stir to crumble.
Drain any excess fat.
Stir in remaining ingredients; bring to a boil.
Cover, reduce heat
and simmer for 1 hour.
Remove bay leaf before serving.
Yields 3 quarts.

title: white surprise
directions: Combine melted butter and dry cake mix.
Reserve 1 1/2 cups of this.
Put remaining crumb mixture into ungreased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Top that with combined peanut butter and Marshmallow Creme and spread evenly.
Crumble remaining 1 1/2 cups over.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken parmesan
directions: Fry chicken breasts in large skillet until done.
Pour sauce in baking pan.
Place chicken in sauce.
Sprinkle Parmesan cheese over chicken.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Place Mozzarella cheese on chicken and return to oven until cheese melts.

title: knox double decker blox
directions: In a large bowl, combine unflavored gelatine and flavored gelatine; add boiling water and stir until gelatine is completely dissolved.
Add cream; stir well.
Pour into shallow baking dish about 9 x 13-inches; chill until firm.

title: heavenly hash
directions: Cook rice in water.
Add sugar, salt and milk.
Cook until soft.
Set aside.
Mix together marshmallows and pineapple.
Mix rice mixture and marshmallow mixture together.
Whip the whipping cream and add to mixture.
Chill thoroughly before serving.
Good with angel food cake or nut bread.
This is an old recipe, but very good.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix corn and eggs together.
Add flour, salt and pepper. Slowly add milk, then butter.
Pour mixture into a buttered 2-quart casserole.
Set in a pan of water and bake 1 hour and 20 minutes at 325°.

title: hot sauce
directions: Brown meat in a little oil on stove or bake meatballs in oven, pouring off grease.
After adding roux, add meat.
(For meatball stew, cook down somewhat before adding meatballs, then season to taste and turn fire down to medium-low; cover and cook 30 minutes.)
Cook until meat is tender.
Serve over rice.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch pan.
Heat oven to 350°.
Blend ingredients together.
Bake 50 to 60 minutes.
Let cool and serve.

title: candied sweet potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Spray a 9 x 12 glass ovenproof baking dish with non-stick cooking spray, such as PAM.
Place sweet potato pieces in dish.
Pour corn syrup and honey over potatoes; sprinkle sugar over potatoes.
Dissolve cornstarch in 1/4 c. water.
Melt butter in small saucepan;
add orange juice and bring to boil.
Slowly stir cornstarch into mixture until slightly thickened.
Pour over sweet potatoes.
Lightly sprinkle nutmeg over potatoes.
Cover loosely with foil and bake about 1 to 1 1/2 hours or until potatoes are tender.
Remove foil, top with marshmallows if desired.
Cook until marshmallows are brown and slightly melted.

title: easy plum cake(baby food cake)
directions: Sift flour, salt, cloves and cinnamon together.
Combine oil, sugar and eggs; beat until blended.
Beat in plums.
Add flour mixture; mix well.
Fold in nuts.
Turn batter into a greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: country fried chicken
directions: Wash and pat dry chicken.
Roll in flour.
Put in 350 degree skillet with the skin side down.
Fry till brown, turn and add salt.
Put lid on skillet and fry until other side is brown.
Fry about 1/2 hour.
During the last 11 minutes remove the lid and let the chicken cook with the skin side up.

title: buttermilk pound cake
directions: Cream together sugar, shortening and butter until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Stir in vanilla and lemon or orange extract.
Stir together flour and baking soda.
Add to creamed mixture alternately with buttermilk. Pour into greased and floured 10-inch tube pan or Bundt pan.
Bake 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Cool in pan 10 minutes; remove from pan and cool on rack.
Freezes beautifully!

title: shrimp gumbo
directions: Melt oleo. Stir in garlic, onion, pepper and flour.
Cook until tender.
Combine tomatoes and paste with water. Add this, plus remaining ingredients (except shrimp and rice).
Simmer 45 minutes. Cool.
Add shrimp and simmer, covered, 5 minutes or until shrimp are pink and tender. Serve over rice.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Combine sugar and milk in saucepan and boil until a soft ball is formed.
Remove from heat and add remaining ingredients.
Beat until creamy.
Pour into buttered dish.
Allow to cool completely and cut into squares.

title: coconut pie
directions: Cream together butter, sugar and Karo.
Add vanilla, eggs and coconut.
Pour into pie crust.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: yummy chicken
directions: Combine rice, seasoning package, mushroom soup and milk. Spread in bottom of 9 x 13 pan that has been well-greased. Cover with chicken, then sprinkle onion soup mix on top. Cover tightly with foil. Bake 2 hours at 350°.

title: chili cheese nachos
directions: Prepare meat and taco mix by package directions.
Line large broiling pan with foil.
Spread chips on pan.
Heat chili and pour onto chips.
Pour hot taco mixture on top of chili; spread evenly. Top with sliced cheese.
Bake in oven at 400° until cheese is melted.
Serve hot.

title: potato cheese soup
directions: In a large saucepan, saute celery and onion in butter until tender. Add potatoes and broth. Simmer until potatoes are tender; stir in milk and seasonings. Heat through. Add cheese, stirring until melted. Garnish.

title: purple lady salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in hot water.
Stir to dissolve.
Add blueberries with syrup and pineapple with juice.
Refrigerate until almost set.
Whip the cream and fold into Jell-O along with pecans. Refrigerate until serving time.

title: black bean soup
directions: Soak beans overnight.
Drain and add 8 cups cold water.
Cover and simmer 1 1/2 hours.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer until beans and vegetables are tender.
Serve with dollops of sour cream.

title: texas barbecue sauce
directions: Brown hamburger and onion. In a saucepan, add all other ingredients. Then add brown hamburger and onions and simmer until all liquid is reduced to a Sloppy Joe mixture.

title: lemon chess pie
directions: Beat eggs, add melted oleo and other ingredients.
Pour into a 9-inch deep unbaked pie crust.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: heavenly fillets
directions: Place fillets in single layer on well-greased baking platter. Brush with lemon juice.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Broil fish 4 inches from source of heat for 6 minutes or until fish flakes easily when tested with a fork.
Remove from heat and spread with cheese mixture.
Broil 2 more minutes or until browned lightly.
Makes 6 servings.

title: lou's spaghetti
directions: Brown ground meat in skillet with onion and green pepper. Salt and pepper.
Generously use Worcestershire and Tabasco sauces, stirring well.
Add drained corn to skillet and stir.
Add tomato sauce; stir and lower heat to simmer.
Cook spaghetti according to directions, adding 1 tablespoon Wesson oil to keep from boiling over.
Drain spaghetti; mix thoroughly with meat mixture.
Place into a large Dutch oven.
Mix in 1 cup of grated cheese.
Top with 1 cup of grated cheese.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.

title: shrimp salad
directions: Mix together Jell-O, water, salt and vinegar.
Chill.
Beat in Miracle Whip, celery, sweet pickle, pimento, shrimp and onion. Chill until set.
Serve on lettuce with Cheddar cheese grated on top.

title: french onion quiche
directions: Microwave pie shell for 2 minutes on High; turn dish and cook 2 minutes more.
(Prick pie shell with a fork before cooking.)

title: egg casserole
directions: Put eggs and sour cream in blender until well mixed.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch greased glass pan and bake at 350° for 6 to 10 minutes or until set.
Brown sausage, add salt, pepper and onion.
Drizzle taco sauce over eggs.
Cover eggs with sausage and cheeses.
Heat in oven until cheese is melted through.

title: marinated tomato slices
directions: Arrange tomato and onion slices in a shallow container and any other vegetable you would like to put in.
Combine oil, vinegar and garlic powder.
Stir well and pour over vegetables; stir until well coated and sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Cover and refrigerate for 10 minutes or overnight.

title: cherry crunch
directions: In a 13 x 9-inch baking pan, pour cherry pie filling, then crushed pineapple.
Sprinkle dry cake mix on top of fruit.
Melt butter and pour on top of cake mixture.
Top with chopped nuts. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
You may cover with foil loosely to avoid nuts getting too brown.

title: baked pork chops with potatoes
directions: Butter bottom and sides of 9 x 13-inch glass baking dish. Season potatoes with Tony's. Lay potatoes on bottom of baking dish. Spread one can of mushroom soup over potatoes. Lay pork chops on potatoes; sprinkle onions and bell pepper on top of meat. Mix second can of soup with water; pour over meat. Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours to 1 hour and 45 minutes.

title: party ham biscuits
directions: Buy ham and Swiss cheese.
Cut to fit into brown ready to serve biscuits (24 to pack).
Mix remaining ingredients.
Mix and spread on top and bottom of biscuits.
Put ham and cheese in the middle. Bake until cheese melts and serve.

title: cabbage-bean soup
directions: In 3-quart saucepan, saute onion, celery and potatoes in oil 5 minutes or until onion is tender.
Stir in cabbage; cover and cook over moderate heat, stirring occasionally, 10 minutes or until cabbage cooks down and is crisp-tender.
Add remaining ingredients, except beans.
Cover and simmer, stirring occasionally, 20 minutes or until potatoes and cabbage are tender. Stir in beans; cook 10 minutes longer for beans to heat through and flavors to blend.
Makes 4 generous servings.

title: quick nacho dip
directions: Combine first 2 ingredients in a large skillet and cook until meat is browned; drain.
Add beans, sauce and taco mix.
Stir well.
Cook over medium heat until thoroughly heated.
Spoon into baking dish and sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 400° until cheese melts.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: oyster stew(serves 4 generously)
directions: Melt butter in heavy saucepan.
Wash all grit off oysters.
Put into hot butter and simmer a few minutes.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Add a pint of milk; bring to a near boil.
Boil and serve at once with oyster crackers.

title: cheese soup
directions: Put veggies in food processor. Then saut them in about 1/2 stick butter until clear. Add soups and broth, then add chunks of Velveeta and cook until melted and bubbly.

title: barbara's cookies
directions: Use mini cupcake pan.
Spray with shortening.
Slice cold dough and fit into pan.
Bake for 15 minutes at 350°.
Take cookies out of oven and quickly push one candy into each cookie until it melts.
Let cool and remove from pan.

title: crock-pot beef stew
directions: Trim all fat from meat.
Put all ingredients into crock-pot and mix thoroughly.
Cover and cook on low for 8 to 10 hours.

title: strawberry frosting
directions: Cream butter or oleo with powdered sugar.
Add other ingredients.

title: christmas breakfast(serves 6)
directions: Trim crust from bread and crumble.
Mix bread and cheese and spread in bottom of greased 7 1/2 x 12 1/2-inch baking dish.
Beat eggs and milk together and stir in salt, pepper and mustard.
Pour over bread and cheese.
Lay bacon on top and refrigerate overnight.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.
Serve immediately.

title: pepper chuck steak
directions: Brown beef on both sides. Put one slice of beef in roaster. Put half of green pepper on first slice.
Add salt and pepper.
Put second slice on top and add rest of green pepper. Put sliced onions on top of all that.
Add tomatoes, tomato sauce and beef stock or bouillon.
Put bay leaves, celery leaves, parsley and thyme in cheesecloth or soup spice holder.
Cover tightly.
Bake at 350° for 2 to 2 1/2 hours.

title: mock fruit soup
directions: Cook to medium heat until mixture boils.
Simmer 1 to 2 minutes.
Stir liqueur with.
Serve warm or chilled.
Makes 4 to 5 servings.

title: macaroni cheese
directions: In 1 quart pan boil water and 1 tablespoon salt.
Bring to boil; add macaroni.
Cook until tender.
In 2-quart casserole bowl dice margarine in the bottom of the bowl.
Drain macaroni and pour in the bowl with margarine.
Then put the cheese on top of the macaroni.
Put in microwave for 3 minutes to melt cheese.

title: whipping cream pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each one.
Add flour and cream alternately.
Grease and flour a tube pan.
Put in cold oven.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.
Serves 16.

title: fudge
directions: Mix all ingredients in saucepan.
Cook for 7 minutes on gas burner or 6 minutes on electric burner.
Add 1 teaspoon vanilla.

title: coffee ice cream pie
directions: Brush beaten egg white onto crust and bake at 375° about 5 minutes sealing the bottom of crust.
Cool.
Dissolve coffee in warm water until clear and cool.
Blend into soft ice cream, fold in the Cool Whip.
Fill and freeze.
May be garnished with strawberries.

title: funfetti cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
In large bowl, combine cake mix, oil and eggs; stir by hand until thoroughly moistened.
Stir in sprinkles from cake mix.
Shape dough into 1-inch balls.
Place 2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Flatten to 1/4-inch with bottom of glass dipped in flour.
Bake 6 to 8 minutes until light golden brown.
Cool 1 minute and remove from cookie sheet.
Spread frosting over warm cookies.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: chicken paprikas and dumplings(nokedli)
directions: Cut chicken into serving pieces.
Into moderately hot fat, put onions and stir constantly for 3 minutes or until a light golden color.
Add paprika and stir 1 minute.
Add cut up chicken, salt and 1/2 cup cold water.
Bring to a boil, lower flame, cover pan and cook 1/2 hour, stirring occasionally.
Add 3 cups water; cover and simmer slowly 1 1/2 hours or until tender.
Add chopped pepper and simmer another 1/2 hour.
When chicken is fully cooked, prepare a smooth mixture of flour and 1/2 cup water; add to chicken, stirring while combining and bring to a boil.
Add 1/2 pint sour cream.
Bring only up to a boiling point.
Serve with dumplings.

title: squash casserole
directions: Add squash, salt and sugar to water in saucepan; cook for 20 minutes or until tender, then drain in a colander.
Return squash to saucepan, add butter and mash with a potato masher.
Blend in sour cream, cheese and pepper.
Turn into baking dish, top with crumbs.
Bake in a 350° oven for 20 minutes or until bubbly and crumbs are browned.
Yields 6.

title: lemon bisque(makes two pies or one 9 x 12-inch glass dish.  no baking)
directions: Dissolve lemon Jell-O in boiling water.
Add 1 cup sugar, juice and grated rind of lemon.
Mix well.
Cool until thickened.
Whip can of chilled evaporated milk.
Add lemon mixture; mix well.
Pour into two graham cracker pie shells (or make a graham cracker mixture and put into a 9 x 12-inch glass dish with graham cracker crumbs).

title: tea bread
directions: Beat
eggs.
Add sugar.
Beat until smooth.
Add flour, salt and baking powder.
Stir in dates, nuts and vanilla.
Mix well. Put
in greased small loaf pan.
Bake at 275° for about 1 1/2 hours.
Cool completely before turning out.

title: breakfast casserole(strata)
directions: Put buttered bread in a buttered baking dish.
Cook sausage until brown, stirring until crumbled.
Drain and spoon over bread slices.
Sprinkle cheese over meat.
Combine eggs, salt and cream in a bowl.
Mix well and pour over cheese. Refrigerate overnight.
Remove from refrigerator 15 minutes before baking.
Heat oven to 350° and bake, uncovered, for 45 minutes or until set.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Brown ground meat.
Boil twists; drain.
Add meats, twists and sauces together.
Layer with cheese and pepperoni.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: fat-free no guilt mud pie
directions: Crush Snackwell graham snacks.
In a large bowl, blend graham crackers, sugar, Nestle Quik and liquid Butter Buds.
Press the mixture onto a deep dish pie pan that has been sprayed with nonfat vegetable cooking spray (Pam).
Pour softened frozen ice cream or yogurt into crust.
Place in freezer for 1 hour.
Once the ice cream has hardened, spread the fudge topping on top of it.
Place in freezer until you are ready to serve.
You might take it out of freezer about 10 minutes before serving so it will be easier to cut.
Yields 10 servings.

title: chinese sweet 'n sour beef
directions: Trim fat from meat and tenderize.
Cut into thin slices on diagonal across grain.
Heat 3 tablespoons oil in a large skillet until hot.
Quickly brown beef, over high heat, stirring rapidly, for 3 to 4 minutes.
Remove to platter with drippings.

title: rhubarb crisp
directions: Mix rhubarb, egg, sugar and flour; put in a buttered casserole. Add butter, brown sugar and flour; mix and sprinkle on top.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Grease 9 x 12-inch baking dish.
Mix all ingredients together; spread into crust.
Bake until golden brown, about 30 minutes at 350°.

title: northwest tacos
directions: Slice (Julian style) beef into thin strips and saute in 1 tablespoon olive oil.
Add 1 tablespoon olive oil, cabbage, cilantro and mushrooms.
Continue to saute for 3 to 5 minutes. Fill heated soft tortillas with mixture.
Add carrots, sour cream and salsa.
Roll up and enjoy.

title: applesauce cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs and applesauce; blend well.
Sift and add dry ingredients; fold in nuts and raisins. Chill dough at least 1 hour.
Drop by teaspoon on greased cookie sheet.
Bake 15 minutes at 400°.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Mix all together and refrigerate overnight.
Serve spread on crackers.

title: baked devil's float
directions: Cook 1/2 cup sugar in water for 5 minutes. Pour into a square pan. Top with marshmallows. Cream shortening and 1/2 cup sugar. Add vanilla. Add dry ingredients alternately with milk. Add nuts. Drop mixture over marshmallows. Mix in pan with spoon. Cover. Bake at 350° about 45 minutes.

title: korean beef barbecue(bul go gi)
directions: Place meat in bowl with all ingredients. Cover.
Mix until meat is covered. Chill in refrigerator 4 hours.
Cook on grill.

title: french silk pie
directions: Cream butter and sugar with electric mixer; add salt and vanilla.
Melt chocolate and add it to creamed mixture.
Add 1 egg and beat at high speed for 3 minutes.
Add 1 more egg and beat an additional 5 minutes.
Scrape sides of bowl occasionally.
Pour into any type pie crust, regular, graham or Oreo cookie.
Top with Cool Whip and shredded chocolate or chopped pecans.
Refrigerate 2 hours before serving.

title: chicken caccitore
directions: Saute chicken breasts in a little butter.
Sprinkle the chicken with pepper, basil and oregano on both sides while cooking.
While chicken is cooking, saute in olive oil, onions, peppers and mushrooms until cooked.
Place chicken breasts in greased casserole in single layer.
Divide vegetables evenly over chicken.
Spoon spaghetti sauce on top to cover.
Bake at 350° until hot.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Mix macaroni or shells, green pepper and celery.
Mix and beat salad dressing, milk and sugar and add to macaroni mixture.

title: aunt jean's sloppy joes
directions: Brown meat, onion and celery slowly.
Drain fat.
Add chili sauce and tomato soup.
Simmer for 2 hours.

title: cherry crunch
directions: Spread the pie filling in the bottom of a 9-inch square pan. Sprinkle with lemon juice.
In a small bowl, mix dry cake mix, melted butter and nuts into a crumbly mixture and spread on pie filling.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Serve topped with whipped cream.

title: pizza snacks
directions: Brown hamburger, salt and pepper; drain grease from pan. Flatten biscuits with a glass and roll thin.
Brush on pizza sauce.
Sprinkle hamburger on top.
Top with cheeses.
Bake for 10 minutes in 425° oven.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Sift
flour
with
corn
meal and sugar in large mixing bowl. Combine
eggs and milk in a separate bowl.	Make a well in	center of dry ingredients.
Add liquid ingredients all at once;
stir until
smooth, then add cheese, hot pepper, corn, bell
pepper and
onion.
Add
oil; stir that together.	Pour into an
iron skillet
and bake at 425° for 20 to 25 minutes, until golden brown.
Cut; serve immediately.

title: ginger cookies
directions: Cook the first 4 ingredients, stirring constantly, until the mixture boils, then remove from heat and add graham cracker crumbs, coconut and nuts.
Spread mixture on top of layer of graham crackers, then put a layer of whole graham crackers over this.
Top with the icing.

title: nacho casserole
directions: Brown ground beef; drain fat.
Add onion, salt and pepper; simmer until onion is soft.
Add all 3 soups; heat and stir well. In medium casserole dish, empty 1/2 bag Doritos in bottom.
Add 1/2 beef mixture.
Add another layer of Doritos, then the rest of the beef mixture and a thin layer of Doritos on top.
Fast and easy!

title: dirty rice dressing
directions: Cover rice with salted water.
Water should be 1-inch above rice.
Cook until rice is fluffy (or you may use Minute rice).
In a skillet, saute ground meat and livers in 1/4 pound of oleo.
Add remaining ingredients and mix together in a large bowl using natural gravy from turkey or hen to moisten.

title: gracie's garlic bread
directions: Slice French bread in half lengthwise.
Mix next 6 ingredients.
Spread on bread.
Heat in 400° oven 10 to 15 minutes.
Yields 1 loaf.

title: spiced tea mix
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Store in tightly covered container. Use 2 teaspoons per cup of hot water.

title: dilled carrots
directions: Peel and julienne carrots.
Boil or steam carrots until tender.
Mix mayonnaise, sour cream and dill to make dressing. Drain and chill carrots.
Toss carrots with dressing and serve.

title: southwest chicken casserole
directions: In a large bowl, combine all ingredients except the cheese. Mix well.
Spread in a greased 8 X 8 baking dish.
Sprinkle with cheese and bake at 400 for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: cinnamon rolls
directions: Separate biscuits.
Twist each biscuit and place in a glass pan.
Combine all other ingredients and pour over biscuits.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: stir-fry peas
directions: Saute onion, pepper and mushrooms in margarine in a wok until barely tender.
Add the frozen peas, pimientos and soy sauce. Stir-fry until peas are thawed and just tender.
Stir constantly. Serve as a side dish.

title: oreo cake
directions: Mix
together in a large bowl, powdered sugar and cream cheese.
Mix pudding and milk, then add to bowl mixture.
Fold in Cool
Whip.
Crush 1 large package Oreo cookies.
Put half into bottom
of	a
9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour mixture over cookie layer. Sprinkle rest of cookies over the top.

title: chow-chow
directions: Grind cabbage, onions and pepper together.
Grind tomatoes, squeeze juice out and mix with peppers.
Mix all together and bring to a boil.
Boil for 25 minutes; pack in jars.

title: cherry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water. Cool, but do not let jello set. Stir in pie filling. Refrigerate until firm. Melt marshmallows. Add cream cheese until well blended. Cool marshmallow mixture. Fold in whipped cream. Spread on jello.

title: beet pickles
directions: Add sugar and spices to vinegar and water.
Let come to a boil.
Add beets and boil 5 minutes.
Pack in jars and seal.

title: old fashioned tea cakes
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add eggs; mix well.
Add 3 cups flour (mixed with baking powder, salt and nutmeg) alternately with milk.
Add enough flour until stiff enough to roll dough.
Roll on floured board; cut out and place on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for approximately 15 minutes, until brown.

title: chicken casserole(6 to 8 servings)
directions: Boil, bone and skin breasts; cut into small pieces.
Place chicken chunks in large casserole.
Mix soup and sour cream.
Pour over chicken.
Crumble crackers and sprinkle over mixture. Drizzle melted oleo over top and sprinkle top with poppy seed. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
This may be prepared the day before you bake.

title: applesauce cupcakes
directions: Wash raisins in lukewarm water and cut into small pieces. Scald nuts and chop coarsely.
Sift flour; measure and return to sifter.
Add soda, salt and spices.
Cream shortening; add sugar gradually.
Add egg and beat until light.
Add dry ingredients alternately with applesauce.
Stir in nuts and raisins.
Fill muffin tins 2/3 full.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: low-fat cheese cake
directions: Heat oven to 325°. Press cracker crumbs onto bottom and sides of 9-inch pie plate coated with nonstick cooking spray. In bowl, beat together cream cheese, sugar and flour until creamy. Beat in sour cream, egg whites and vanilla. Pour into crust and bake 40 minutes. Cool on wire rack and chill for at least 3 hours. Garnish with fresh strawberries or other fruit. Makes 8 servings.

title: red hot salad
directions: Melt red hots in hot water with jello. Add gelatin dissolved in cold water.
Add applesauce.
Pour in lightly greased mold and chill.

title: apple bundles
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Peel, core and slice apples.
Unroll dough and separate into 8 triangles.
Cut in half to make 16 triangle strips.
Place 3 to 4 apple slices at wide end and roll up.
Arrange in baking dish.
Pour juice of orange into dish but not over bundle.
Drizzle bundles with butter; sprinkle cinnamon and sugar on top.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes or until golden brown. Serve warm; plain or with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: Melt margarine in a small saucepan and add flour to make a thick, but still pourable roux.
In large pot, bring stock to a boil.
Add broccoli and simmer until almost done.
Add sauteed onion and seasonings.
Simmer until vegetables are tender. Thicken soup by slowly adding roux, stirring constantly.
Soup should be of a thick consistency.
Heat milk, cream and buttermilk in separate saucepan and add slowly to the soup, stirring constantly.
Soup should be very hot, but not boiling.
Be careful not to scorch the bottom.
Turn heat off and stir in sour cream and butter.
Serves 4-6.

title: aunt mary's frosting
directions: Beat first 3 ingredients together.
Add butter and vanilla and mix well.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Thoroughly mix all ingredients with a fork.
Serve with crackers.

title: chocolate chess pie
directions: Gently heat chocolate and margarine in a saucepan. Stir often until melted. Beat eggs until light and frothy, stir in syrup, sugar and vanilla. Then stir in chocolate and margarine mixture. Pour into 9 inch pie shell. Bake at 350° for 35 - 40 minutes or until top is slightly crunch and filling is set. Do not overcook; the filling should remain soft inside. Excellent warm or cold, with ice cream. We have found it helps to cover edge of crust with foil to avoid burning.

title: oreos-n-creme
directions: Put milk in bowl and dip a few Oreos in the milk.
Make a layer of cookies in a large pan.
Spread whipped topping over cookies.
Repeat the process of layers to the amount desired. Crumble 3 to 4 dry cookies on top of the last layer of whipped topping.

title: sugar-free pineapple pie
directions: Combine crumbs and margarine; press into bottom and up the sides of a 9-inch pie plate. Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes; cool.

title: mock crab mun doo
directions: In medium bowl, combine crab, cream cheese, mayonnaise, green onions, water chestnuts and Worcestershire sauce and mix well.
To form mun doo, put about 2 teaspoons filling in center of pi. Moisten edges with water and fold in half; pinch edges together to seal well.
Repeat until all ingredients are used.
Heat deep fat to 375°.
Fry mun doo until golden brown.
Drain on absorbent paper.
Makes 30 mun doo.

title: peanut butter bread
directions: Combine flour, oats, sugar, baking powder, and salt.
Cut in peanut butter until crumbly.
In separate bowl, combine eggs, milk, and vanilla and stir in dry ingredients.
Transfer to a greased and floured 9 by 5 by 3 inch pan (or 4 small greased and floured loaf pans).
Bake at 350 degrees for 55-60 minutes.
If you are using the small loaf pans, decrease the baking time to 45 minutes.
Test with a toothpick to see if the breads are done. Cool for 10 minutes before removing from the pan to a wire rack.

title: frozen yogurt
directions: Put strawberries in blender.
Mix until pureed.
Mix with yogurt and sweetener to taste.
Freeze.

title: hong kong pork stew
directions: Trim excess fat from pork; place in an electric slow cooker; season with salt, ginger and pepper.
Drain syrup from pineapple, adding water to syrup to make 1 1/2 c.; reserve pineapple chunks. Add syrup mixture to pork; stir in sugar, instant broth, molasses and vinegar; cover.
Cook on low (190-200°) 8 hours, or on high (290-300°) 4 hours.
Turn heat control to high.
Combine cornstarch and 1/4 c. cold water in a cup; stir into pork mixture until well blended.
Add sweet potatoes, tomatoes, pineapple chunks and green pepper; cover; simmer 20 minutes longer.

title: brownie pudding cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Into a bowl, sift flour, cocoa, baking powder and the salt.
In another bowl, whisk together eggs, sugar, milk and vanilla.
Add flour mixture and stir the batter until it is just combined.
Stir in the walnuts and spread the batter evenly in an ungreased 8-inch square baking pan.

title: yalonchee yaprakh(lenten dish; spinach and grape leaves)
directions: Saute minced onions and garlic in hot oil until slightly browned.
Add rice, thawed spinach and parsley to onions and garlic.
Saute for 3 minutes.
Blend in tomato paste and spices. When cooled, roll rice mixture in grape leaves and arrange in layers in pot.
Add lemon juice to 3 cups of water; add to grape leaves.
Place a heavy plate on top of grape leaves.
Bring to a boil; simmer for 45 minutes, or until rice is cooked.
Drain water off.
Serve hot or cold.

title: strawberry cool whip pie
directions: Combine 2/3 Cool Whip, condensed milk, strawberries and pecans until smooth.
Fold in lemon juice and stir until thickened. Spread remaining Cool Whip over top and refrigerate 1 hour.

title: best barbecue sauce
directions: Melt butter in saucepan.
Add rest of ingredients.
Can be used for any recipe calling for barbecue sauce.

title: skillet potatoes
directions: Heat margarine in frypan.
Layer potatoes, season and layer onions.
Add water.
Cover and simmer over low heat until potatoes are tender and liquid is absorbed, about 30 to 45 minutes.

title: date and pineapple bread
directions: Combine milk, egg, shortening, dates, pineapple and nuts. Sift remaining ingredients together; add to first mixture.
Blend only to moisten.
Bake in 1 pound greased loaf pan at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.

title: vegetable rice
directions: In large saucepan, saute drained mushrooms with onion, garlic, oregano and dill weed in oil until onion is tender, about 5 minutes.
Stir in rice and turmeric; reduce heat and simmer, covered, until rice is tender and broth is absorbed, about 25 minutes.
Mix in remaining ingredients during the last 10 minutes of cooking time.
Makes 6 servings, each with 112 calories, 2.4g fat and 0mg cholesterol.

title: pumpkin squares
directions: Mix and spread cake mix, except 1 cup, 1 egg, and 1 stick butter in bottom of pan.
Mix pumpkin granulated sugar, 2 eggs, flour, salt, canned milk, 1 tsp. cinnamon, allspice, and ginger. Pour over crust in pan.
Mix together, 1 cup mix, brown sugar 1/2 stick butter and 1 tsp. cinnamon and sprinkle over mixture in pan. Bake at 350° until done.
Insert knife in center; if it come out clean, the cake is done.

title: chicken pineapple spread
directions: Drain pineapple.
Reserve liquid.
Combine ingredients and mix well.
Add enough of reserved liquid to desired spreading consistency.

title: cheeseburger twist
directions: Soften yeast in warm water.
Combine in a large bowl, sugar, salt, butter and milk.
Cool to lukewarm.
Stir in egg and yeast. Gradually add flour to form a stiff dough.
Knead on a floured surface until smooth and satiny, about 5 minutes.
Place in a greased bowl, covered.
Let rise until light and doubled, 1 to 2 hours.

title: spiced pecans
directions: In small bowl, beat together egg white and water. Stir in pecans, stirring until all surfaces are moistened. Mix together sugar, salt, cinnamon, cloves and nutmeg; sprinkle over pecans, mixing
well. Spread pecans on lightly greased or foil lined cookie sheet and bake in preheated 300 degree oven for 30 minutes. Stir once or twice to crisp and dry pecans evenly.

title: applesauce puffs
directions: Combine Bisquick, 1/4 cup sugar and 1 teaspoon cinnamon.
Add applesauce, milk, egg and oil.
Beat vigorously for 30 seconds. Fill 2-inch muffin papers in tins 2/3 full.
Bake at 400° for 12 minutes; cool.
Dip top in melted butter, then sugar and cinnamon mix.
You may freeze on cookie sheet, then pop in plastic bag. Heat to serve.
Makes 24 or more.

title: wedding punch
directions: Combine sugar and water in saucepan; boil mixture until dissolved.
Let cool.
Add mashed bananas, pineapple juice, orange juice and lemon juice.
Mix well and pour into ice cube trays. Place a maraschino cherry in each cube section; freeze until solid.
When ready to serve, place cubes in punch bowl; add ginger ale.
Stir until punch cubes melt.
Serves 20.

title: taco salad
directions: Layer first 6 ingredients. Break taco chips and add them just before serving with dressing. Toss.

title: crabmeat squares
directions: Mix above ingredients until well blended. Split muffins in half.

Spread mixture on muffins, then cut each half of muffin into 4 pieces. If you are ready to use, just put them on a cookie sheet and bake at 350° until lightly browned, about 15 minutes. If you wish you may spread muffins pieces on cookie sheet and put in freezer for an hour or until hard.
Then toss them into a plastic bag until ready to use.

title: muffin pizzas
directions: Mix tomato sauce, oregano, margarine and garlic salt.
Spoon over muffins; add cheese and, if you would like, you may add sausage or pepperoni.
Put in broiler until cheese melts.

title: apple dumplings
directions: Cut and peel 3 or 4 Granny Smith apples.
Cut apples in eighths.
Wrap in Hungry Jack biscuits pulled in half.

title: hot apple surprise
directions: Brush tortillas on both sides with butter and heat 4 at a time in microwave for 25 seconds each.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain all juice from fruit and save 1 cup juice.
Put fruit in a bowl and dice peaches and pears.
Add to the cup of juice Jell-O French vanilla.
Mix well and pour over fruit.
Add Cool Whip.
Mix well and chill.

title: shrimp mold
directions: Thaw shrimp.
Melt together cream of mushroom soup and cream cheese.
Dissolve Knox unflavored gelatine in cold water.
Add to cream cheese mixture.
Add celery, green onions, mayonnaise and shrimp.
Mix well.
Put into mold or bowl.
Refrigerate overnight. Serve with crackers.

title: chocolate fudge
directions: Melt creme drops in microwave.
Mix in peanut butter while still hot.
Spread in pan; let cool.
It will harden.
Cut into squares.

title: ugly duckling cake
directions: Combine cake mix, fruit cocktail, 1 c coconut and eggs in a bowl. Beat 2 minutes on medium speed. Grease a 13 x 9 pan. Sprinkle with brown sugar. Bake cake at 350 degrees for 45 minutes.

title: garlic potatoes
directions: Cube your potatoes.
Cube your onions.
Mince your garlic. Place all this in a microwave bowl with lid.
Add a little salt and pepper.
Cook at 4 minute intervals, stirring each time, until tender (3 or 4).

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Generously grease a shallow 2 quart baking dish.
Mix undiluted soup and milk in a large bowl until well blended.
Add remaining ingredients except cheese and toss gently to mix.
Turn into prepared dish.
Sprinkle cheese evenly over top.
Bake 15 minutes or until hot and bubbly.
Makes 4 servings.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Cook and drain spaghetti.
Cool.
Add remaining ingredients and put in refrigerator.
Serves 15 to 20.

title: apple raisin walnut cake
directions: Beat eggs and oil in a mixing bowl until foamy.
Add sugar and vanilla and continue to beat.
Add apples, beating slightly; set aside.
Sift flour, soda, salt, cinnamon and cloves.
Add raisins and walnuts to flour.
Add flour mixture to egg mix.
Beat slightly.
Bake at 350° in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Check for doneness after 25 minutes.
Cool cake after toothpick comes out clean and frost with Non-Sweet Frosting.

title: sauerbraten
directions: Place beef in bowl.
Combine next 7 ingredients and blend. Pour over meat.
Marinate 24 hours.
Melt fat in a heavy skillet or Dutch oven.
Add meat.
Brown thoroughly.
Add water to meat liquid and pour over meat.
Cover.
Simmer over low heat 3 hours or until meat is tender.
Remove meat.
Make gravy from juices in pan.

title: roasted cauliflower
directions: Preheat oven to 375 degrees.
Clean and slice cauliflower - 1/4 inch slices and pieces work best.
Toss with oil, garlic, and salt.
Spread cauliflower on cookie sheets - do not overlap pieces.
Roast at 375 degrees until golden brown, stirring every 15 minutes.
Depending on the size of the cauliflower, this will take about 45 minutes.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Sift together flour and baking powder.
Melt butter with 1/2 cup water, chocolate and sugar on low heat until all ingredients are combined.
Remove from heat; transfer to a large mixing bowl. Add sifted dry ingredients to melted mixture; mix thoroughly. Combine buttermilk and baking soda; make sure soda is dissolved. Add to main mixture.
Combine eggs and vanilla; add to main mixture.
Put mixture into greased and floured 8-inch cake pan. Bake in preheated moderate oven for 25 to 35 minutes.
Cool thoroughly, then ice.

title: soda cracker pie
directions: Mix crackers, baking powder and nuts.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Slowly add sugar and vanilla.
Fold into cracker mixture. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: irish potato casserole
directions: Cook and mash potatoes.
Beat cream cheese, sour cream and margarine.
Mix with potatoes, onions and salt.
Spread in a baking dish.
Sprinkle
paprika across top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until heated thoroughly.

title: devine divinity
directions: Boil sugar, syrup, water and salt together until syrup forms a hard ball when dropped in cold water.
If using thermometer, cook to 270°.
Place the unbeaten egg whites in a large mixing bowl and beat until eggs are stiff, but not dry.
Slowly pour the hot syrup over the egg whites (do not pour too fast or the egg whites will curdle).
After the syrup is added, continue to beat until the mixture becomes stiff.
Add vanilla and nuts and continue to beat until mixture will hold its shape.
Drop by teaspoons on a buttered surface.
Top each piece with a pecan half.

title: hot nacho dip
directions: Mix beef with taco seasoning.
Brown and drain and layer ingredients in 13 x 9-inch pan:
beans, beef, sour cream, onion, tomato, 1/2 jar taco sauce, cheeses and 1/2 jar taco sauce.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Serve with nacho chips, Tostitos or Doritos.

title: artichoke appetizer
directions: Bake at 350° until golden.

title: chicken hekka
directions: In skillet, brown chicken with garlic.
Add salt and pepper. Add bamboo shoots and mushrooms, including liquid.
Add carrots and simmer for 3 minutes.
Add sugar and shoyu and simmer for an additional 3 minutes.
Add watercress and green onions until desired tenderness or crispness of watercress.
Season to taste. Yield: 4 to 6 large portions.

title: super duper stuffed potatoes
directions: Bake the potatoes at 400° until done (approximately 1 hour). Do not use aluminum foil.
Cut into and scoop out insides of potatoes with spoon.
Mix with desired amounts of rest of ingredients.
Put back in oven and bake for 15 to 20 minutes or until tops brown.

title: pumpkin mints
directions: Allow margarine to
reach room temperature.
Mix margarine with sugar and milk, using
tips
of fingers.
Add oil of peppermint and food coloring.
Roll
into balls.
Use a toothpick to make grooves.
Place one clove in the top for a stem.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Boil pasta according to directions on box.
In separate pan, combine diet Mazola, chopped onions and celery.
Saute.

title: ground beef casserole
directions: Brown onions and meat.
Season with garlic powder, paprika and parsley flakes.
Boil noodles while meat is browning.
Drain in 3-quart casserole.
Top with grated cheese and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Melt oleomargarine and saute onion.
Add frozen broccoli and heat until	broccoli
is
thawed.
Add Cheez Whiz, soup and rice. Pour into 2 quart casserole and bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: black walnut cookies
directions: Mix shortening, sugars and eggs.
Stir in milk and vanilla. Sift flour, soda and salt.
Add to creamed mixture.
Blend in nuts and chill for 1 hour.
Drop by spoonful onto greased cookie sheet. Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.
When completely cool, ice with the following:

title: mamere's pound cake
directions: Cream the butter and sugar thoroughly. Add egg yolks. Add cake mix and milk. Beat 2 minutes. Add flavorings.
Beat 1 minute. Beat egg whites until stiff.
Fold gently into cake batter. Do not beat.
Pour into ungreased tube pan. Bake about 45 minutes at 350° to 375°.

title: famous oatmeal cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat together the shortening, sugars, egg, water and vanilla until creamy.
Add combined remaining ingredients; mix well.
Drop by rounded teaspoonful onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Makes about 5 dozen.

title: pineapple nut bread
directions: Grease bottom of 8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Blend honey and butter.
Beat in egg.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt together.
Add half to honey mixture.
Mix well.
Add Wheat Chex and pineapple juice.
Mix well.
Add rest of flour and nuts. Blend.
Pour into loaf pan.
Bake 75 minutes at 350° or until golden brown.

title: freezer relish
directions: Mix vinegar, sugar, celery seed and salt and cover the mixture.
Soak overnight in refrigerator.
Next day, freeze in containers.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Shape into ball and roll in chopped pecans.

title: monkey bread
directions: Cut biscuits into fourths.
Mix sugar and cinnamon in a bag. Add biscuit pieces in bag a few at a time.
Place in greased tube pan.
Do not push down.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Wash and drain broccoli; cut off tops and use in salad.
Mix 1 cup mayonnaise and the Ranch dressing together.
Add the rest of ingredients and mix well.

title: home baked beans
directions: Soak beans for 2 hours.
Drain and put in clean water; cook until tender.
Add onion while cooking.
Put into crock-pot with brown sugar and enough ketchup to flavor; top with bacon strips. Cook a long time.

title: veggie pizza
directions: Flatten crescent rolls in pizza pan until brown (bake as directed).
Mix ingredients and spread on cool crust (can be frozen now).
Press in all vegetables desired, chopped onion, radish, carrots, mushrooms, celery, etc.
Keep in refrigerator until ready to use.

title: roxie's raw apple cake
directions: Mix sugar and salad oil.
Whip well.
Then beat in the eggs. Add flour, salt, soda and baking powder, a little at a time.
Then fold in apples and pecans.
Stir until well mixed.
Cook at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: pizza burgers
directions: Grind together pepperoni, Spam, cheese and onion.
Add mushrooms and pizza sauce and mix with hamburger.
Spread on 1/2 hamburger bun.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: layered three cheese nachos
directions: Preheat the oven to 350 degrees.

Put half the nacho chips on an ovenproof platter and sprinkle with half of each cheese followed by a portion of the remaining ingredients. Top with the remaining chips and toppings with a layer of the remaining cheeses. Bake until the cheeses have melted. Serve with salsa and sour cream.

title: low-fat lasagna
directions: Boil noodles, 3 or 4 at a time to prevent breaking.
Brown turkey, onion and garlic in skillet.
Drain.
Add 3/4 can of water to tomato paste and mix.
Add to browned meat and simmer for 15 minutes.
In a separate bowl, slightly beat egg, then blend in cottage cheese.
Add spices to meat mixture the final five minutes of simmering.
Spray large baking dish with Pam.
Layer meat mixture, followed by noodles, then cheese mixture.
Repeat.
Then sprinkle top with Mozzarella cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or microwave for 20 minutes.

title: griddle cakes
directions: Combine sour milk with egg yolks.
Sift and add flour, salt, soda and baking powder.
Add margarine and sugar.
Fold in egg whites.
Cook as usual on hot skillet.

title: homemade clay (for play)
