directions: Sift the flour and salt together.
Add oil and water.
Work with hands.
If clay is too stiff, add more water.
If clay is too wet, add more flour.
Finally, put in the hand lotion.

title: good cookies
directions: Cream the Crisco and oleo. Add sugar. Add flour and salt. Stir in vanilla and
nuts.
Drop or roll in balls onto greased cookie sheet. Bake in a 300° oven until slightly brown.

title: cocoa mix
directions: Mix ingredients thoroughly.
For camping, seal in a plastic bag.
Add 3/4 cup hot or cold water to dry mix, which is approximately 6 tablespoons.

title: spoon bread
directions: Scald milk (not boil).
Add cornmeal, stir constantly until thick.
Add salt and egg yolks.
Beat until well mixed.
Beat egg whites until stiff in a separate bowl, then fold into other mixture. Pour into a buttered pan.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: chinese casserole
directions: Brown sausage.
Lift out of drippings.
Saute vegetables in drippings; lift out.
Place rice and soup mix in large baking dish.
Add hot water.
Mix well.
Add almonds, meat, vegetables and half of noodles; mix well.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Stir every 20 minutes.
Top with rest of noodles last 20 minutes.

title: dump bread
directions: In a large bowl, dissolve the yeast in water.
Add sugar, salt, egg and butter.
Mix in flour; knead for about 5 minutes. Let dough rise for 2 hours, or until doubled.
Punch down risen dough and roll out to 1/4-inch thick.
Then cut the dough into strips.
Melt additional butter and dip each strip.
In a Bundt pan, layer the strips.
Cover and let rise again.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: vidalia onion pie
directions: Combine cracker crumbs and butter.
Mix and pat into a pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 8 minutes. Slice onions thinly.
Saute in oil and pour into pie shell.
Mix milk and eggs.
Pour over onions.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes.

title: fiesta coleslaw
directions: Pat zucchini dry with paper towels; combine with cabbage, carrots, onions and radishes.
Combine mayonnaise, picante sauce, cumin and salt; mixing well.
Add to vegetable mixture, mixing lightly.
Cover and chill.
Makes 4 servings.

title: pizzaburger
directions: Combine rice, butter and egg.
Line bottom of 12-inch skillet or pizza pan with rice mixture, making a rim around the edge about 1/4-inch high.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Arrange sausage. Sprinkle with salt, Italian seasonings and pepper.
Cover with Mozzarella cheese.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: refrigerator pickles
directions: Stir together sugar, vinegar, celery seed and mustard seed. Add remaining ingredients.
Store in tightly covered container in refrigerator.

title: glazed carrots
directions: Wash and cut carrots in 1/2-inch diagonal slices.
Place in 1-quart casserole with butter and brown sugar.
Cover.
Microwave on High for 10 minutes, stirring after 5 minutes.
Mix cornstarch and water together until smooth.
Stir into carrot mixture.
Add pecans and cover.
Microwave on High approximately 3 minutes or until thickened.
Stir before serving.

title: angel pie
directions: Heat chocolate chips, milk and marshmallows in double boiler or in microwave in a large bowl; stir often if done in microwave. Melt.
Let cool.
It's good to even chill it some.
Beat whipping cream until stiff and fold into chocolate mixture.
Add flavorings.
Pour into crust and chill.

title: coconut fizz cake
directions: Cook cake as directed on box in 13 x 9-inch cake pan.
Remove from oven and using a large straw, punch holes all over cake while it is still hot.
Pour cream of coconut and Eagle Brand milk over top of cake letting it seep through holes; let cool.
Top with Cool Whip and coconut.

title: easy pound cake
directions: Beat eggs, sugar, and oil.
Add flour and flavoring.
Beat well and bake in a 325° oven for 1 hour.
Suitable for freezing.

title: cherry-cranberry jello salad
directions: Make cherry jello as normal but add 2 1/2 cups water.
Then add cranberries and crushed pineapple and let set.
(Makes well in 9 x 13 x 2-inch glass dish.)

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Saute broccoli and onion in butter; add Cheez Whiz, soup and rice.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Remove from oven and sprinkle onion rings on top and bake for 10 minutes.
Enjoy!

title: jalapeno butter grilled fish
directions: Make a pan with heavy-duty tinfoil to fit on outdoor grill or inside grill.
Melt butter in pan over fire and add jalapeno juice. Add fish fillets and cook until opaque.

title: cream of mushroom soup
directions: Saute onion in butter.
Add 3 tablespoons flour; slowly add chicken broth, salt and pepper to taste.
Add mushrooms and cook until mushrooms are done.
Add cream and nutmeg; heat through.

title: chocolate delight
directions: Mix and press in pan (8 x 8-inch or 9 x 9-inch).
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: hot fudge sauce
directions: Put all ingredients into 1 quart saucepan; simmer 10 minutes. Stir occasionally.

title: no hassel caramel nut ring
directions: Lightly grease tube pan.
Place rolls, thawed slightly, around bottom of pan.
Mix sugar and cinnamon and pour evenly over rolls. Next, sprinkle brown sugar, nuts and butterscotch pudding in that order.
Top with thin slices of butter.
Cover and let set at room temperature 5 hours or overnight.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Let stand several minutes and invert onto plate.

title: strawberry shortcake
directions: Bake cake according to directions on box. Remove from oven and poke holes in cake with a knife. Mix jello according to directions. Pour over top of warm cake. Let cool and top with strawberries and cool whip. Keep refrigerated.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Mix sugar and cocoa in saucepan, add butter and milk and bring to a boil.
Stirring constantly, boil 1 minute.
Remove from heat. Stir in oats, peanut butter and vanilla.
Mix well.
Drop by teaspoon on wax paper, cool before serving.

title: ranch-style beans
directions: Brown onion, green pepper and ground beef.
Add beans, sugar, catsup, mustard and Worcestershire sauce.
Pour into large baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chicken vegetable casserole
directions: Mix together and put in large greased casserole dish.
Top with buttered bread crumbs or crumbled potato chips.
Bake at 350° for 40-50 minutes.

title: freezer slaw
directions: Cut cabbage as slaw.
Sprinkle salt over cabbage; mix and let set 1 hour.
Add peppers and celery; mix and let set 20 minutes more.
Drain well; squeeze liquid out by hand.

title: party beans
directions: Brown hamburger, onion and celery.
Add other ingredients. Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: supreme chicken
directions: Arrange chicken in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Divide cheese and place on each piece of chicken.
Mix soup and wine; pour over chicken and cheese.
Sprinkle stuffing mix over top.
Drizzle melted butter on top.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Can cook in oven or crock-pot.
Remove top and seeds from pepper and parboil for 5 minutes.
Drain.
Cook onion and celery in butter just until tender.
Add meat and cook until red disappears.
Add chili sauce, bouillon cubes, salt and pepper. Cook until bouillon cubes dissolve.
Stir in toasted cubes.
Fill pepper shells 2/3 full.
Place in a 10 x 6 x 2-inch pan and bake in hot oven (400°) for approximately 25 minutes.
Top with chili sauce.

title: seasoned oyster crackers
directions: Bring first six ingredients to boil and pour over oyster crackers.

title: snowflake cookies
directions: Stack tortillas and wrap in foil; place in 350° oven for 7 minutes to soften.
This can also be done by placing one or two at a time in a microwave oven wrapped in a cloth.
While still warm, fold each tortilla into fourths and with scissors, cut designs from edges and folded sides.
Unfold and fry one at a time in 1/2-inch oil for approximately 20 seconds until golden brown. Drain on paper towels and cool completely and sprinkle with powdered sugar.
Store in tight covered container.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Crush bananas. Mix with sugar and eggs. Mix soda, baking powder, salt and flour and add to first mixture. Add oil and nuts. Bake in loaf pan 35 to 45 minutes in 350° oven.

title: butter-creme filling
directions: Beat egg white, slowly adding sugar. Cream together butter with shortening. Add vanilla. Beat into the mixture with warm milk. Slide onto first cake layer. Top with second. Refrigerate frosted cake.

title: gingerbread
directions: Sift soda and baking powder into the flour, add egg, molasses and sugar together, then beat in flour and milk and flavoring. Bake in a cake mold which insures thorough cooking through the center.

title: sausage biscuits
directions: Mix together sausage, Bisquick and poultry seasoning.
Add grated cheese.
Roll into balls.
Place on cookie sheet.
Bake for 30 minutes or golden brown at 350°.
Serve hot.

title: creamy chicken casserole
directions: Cook pasta until tender (15 minutes), stirring occasionally or until desired tenderness.
Rinse with cold water, drain.
Combine chicken, 4 ounces cheese, soup, milk, pimiento and pasta.
Turn into a 2-quart casserole dish and bake, covered, at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Uncover, top with remaining cheese, return to oven and bake until cheese melts.

title: savory flan
directions: Line a flan dish with pastry.
Cook onion and turn into pastry case.
Add cheese and seasoning.
Pour over beaten eggs and bake at 375° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: baked beans with franks
directions: In a large bowl, combine all ingredients except bacon.
Mix to blend.
Pour into 2-quart casserole and top with bacon. Bake 20 minutes or until heated through.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs slightly, add sugar. Mix together until well blended. Add butter, syrup, salt, vanilla and pecans. Mix well. Pour into 1 deep dish pie shell or 2 shallow pie shells. Bake for 1 hour at 325 degrees.

title: shauna's sunday supper soup(meatball soup)
directions: Mix together beef, egg, water, bread crumbs, salt and celery. Shape into meatballs.
Brown in butter and after browned, set aside.
Add together all other ingredients and simmer 20 minutes. Add meatballs and simmer 20 minutes longer.
Serve.

title: quick and easy low-fat chicken tenders(breast tenders)
directions: Marinate chicken tenders in dressing 1 to 2 hours in refrigerator.
Put on gas grill and cook 6 to 8 minutes on each side.
Brush with lite butter while cooking.
Shrimp can also be cooked the same way.

title: sweet potatoes and apples
directions: Parboil sweet potatoes for 10 minutes.
Peel and cut in 1/4-inch slices.
Sprinkle sugar and dot with butter.
Alternate layers of potatoes and apples in buttered baking dish, having 3 layers in all, as you sprinkle sugar and dot with butter.
Pour water over all and bake uncovered for 1 hour in a moderate oven (350°).
Just before serving, cover top with marshmallows and put back in oven until they brown.
Serves 8.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Combine all ingredients into a large bowl and mix well.
Beat thoroughly.
Put batter into 8-inch or 9-inch layer pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Makes two large layers.
Cake is very moist.

title: aliya's swordfish
directions: Add all ingredients
to food processor except fish.
Process into sauce consistency.
Marinate fish in sauce for 2 to 4 hours. Grill or broil until flakes with a fork.
Chilean sea bass can be used also!

title: beef cookies(yields 112 cookies)
directions: Mix together brown sugar and shortening.
Add eggs, buttermilk and vanilla.
Sift together flour, soda and salt.
Combine dry ingredients with batter and stir in potato chips and ground roast. Drop by teaspoons on cookie sheet lined with wax paper.
Bake about 10 minutes (or until slightly brown) in a 400° oven.

title: manicotti
directions: Brown meat and onions; drain. Stir in 1/4 cup Parmesan, eggs, 1/2 can sauce and seasonings. Fill shells with meat mixture. Place in dish and pour cornbread, tomatoes, tomato sauce and water over shells. Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese. Cover with foil. Bake 1 hour at 350°. Top with Mozzarella cheese. Put back in the oven until cheese is melted.

title: mushroom salad
directions: Rinse mushrooms and pat dry.
Slice.
Combine oil, vinegar, parsley, salt, sugar, garlic powder and pepper.
Mix and pour over mushrooms.
Add tomatoes and onions.
Cover and refrigerate.

title: quick minestrone soup
directions: Combine first 8 ingredients in large pot.
Bring to boil. Cover and simmer 10 minutes or until pasta is done.
Stirring occasionally, stir in cheese or use as garnish.
Makes 6 servings.

title: the best banana pudding(serves 6 to 8)
directions: Sift first 3 ingredients together into top of double boiler and add milk. Cook, stirring constantly, until medium thick. Separate 1 egg with yolk in a cup. Add some of hot milk mixture to egg yolk and beat together, then add to double boiler. Stir a minute more and add vanilla extract. Layer custard over sliced bananas and vanilla wafers, twice. Top with meringue made from the egg white, a pinch of cream of tartar and 2 tablespoons of sugar beaten together. May broil meringue topped pudding for a skinny minute to turn meringue golden. Serves 6 to 8.

title: golden potato casserole
directions: Cook potatoes in boiling salt water in jackets.
Let cool (do not overcook).
Peel potatoes and grate.
Mix sour cream, cheese, milk and remaining ingredients except bread crumbs.
Put potatoes in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Combine bread crumbs and melted butter and sprinkle on top.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour.

title: cheesecake squares
directions: Preheat oven to 250°.
Combine crumbs, sugar and margarine. Press firmly on bottom of an 8-inch square baking dish.

title: chimney corner dressing
directions: Combine and blend in blender for 10 minutes.
If you do not have a blender, blend ingredients with electric mixer for 30 minutes, using medium speed.
Keep in refrigerator.

title: christmas cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add sherry and the milk in which soda has soaked.
Add well beaten egg yolks and then 2 cups of the flour.
Mix in the flour-coated nuts and fruits.
Fold in the stiffly beaten egg whites.
This is very stiff so you might as well mix with your hands.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 300° for 20 minutes.
Makes lots.

title: miss edna's roasted potatoes
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except potatoes.

title: hot cole slaw
directions: Put in a large pan the oil, sugar and vinegar.
Bring to boil; pour over cabbage.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in mixing bowl.
Make a well in center of mixture.
Combine eggs, oil, sugar and vanilla.
Mix well.
Stir in shredded zucchini.
Add to dry ingredients, stirring until moistened.
Spoon mixture into 2 greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli according to directions, cooking only 4 minutes. Drain, place in 2 qt. baking dish.
Sprinkle nuts.
Combine soup, milk and cheese.
Pour over broccoli.
Bake 350° for 25 minutes uncovered.
Cover with onions and bake 8-10 minutes.

title: easy taco salad
directions: Follow directions on flavor packet for browning meat.
Chop tomatoes and olives.
On a large platter, place meat in center. Put lettuce around meat.
Top lettuce off with tomatoes and olives; put chips around lettuce.
Garnish with cheese, peppers and sour cream.
Salsa or taco sauce on side.

title: rosemary potatoes
directions: Boil potatoes until about half done.
Drain and put in baking dish, cutting potatoes in half.
Mix butter and spices to potatoes and broil for 5 to 10 minutes.

title: apple relish
directions: Put apples, peppers, onions and bell peppers through grinder. Bring remaining ingredients and apple mixture to boil in a large stockpot.
Cook on low heat 30 minutes.
Place in jars and seal.

title: ham and cheese strata
directions: Break bread and cheese into bite-sized pieces.
Arrange bread, ham, cheese and onion in several layers in greased baking dish. Pour melted butter over the mixture.
Add mustard and milk to beaten eggs.
Mix well and pour over casserole contents. Refrigerate, covered, overnight.
Bake uncovered in preheated 350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: rose's chicken mexican
directions: Put chicken in a saucepan (large).
Add water and salt.
Cover and bring to a boil.
Simmer 1/2 to 3/4 hour, until tender.
Let chicken cool in broth.
Remove chicken and with a sharp knife, remove bones and skin.
Return bones and skin to broth.
Boil, uncovered, until it is reduced to 2 1/2 cups.
Strain.

title: chocolate cream pie
directions: Put cream cheese into a bowl and whip with mixer, then slowly add 2 cups of milk.
Mix together.
To that, add chocolate pudding.
Beat together, not too long, it will thicken as it sets. Pour into pie crust and top with Cool Whip.
Take block of semi-sweet chocolate and shave with a potato peeler on the top. Do not cover pie.

title: sweet potato balls
directions: Blend
potatoes and oleo together.
Use small marshmallows for
center;
wrap	potato	around	and roll in coconut. Bake 10 minutes at 300°.

title: old-fashion gingerbread
directions: Add eggs, sugar, molasses and oil in a large bowl and mix well.
Dissolve the baking soda in the 1/8 cup of hot water and add to the mixture.
Sift in the flour, spices and salt; mix well. Add the cup of boiling water and beat lightly and quickly.
Pour into greased and floured pan (13 x 9 x 2-inch) and bake in moderate oven for 45 minutes or until done by testing with a toothpick.
This batter seems thick after making, but do not add anything else.

title: mango chutney
directions: You will also need 4 clear jam jars with twisting lids.

title: baked pineapple
directions: Pour pineapple and juice in buttered baking dish.
Mix sugar and cornstarch and add to pineapple along with eggs and cheese. Stir well.
Dot with butter.
Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Bake 40 minutes at 350°.

title: herbed harvest vegetable casserole
directions: Grease a 2 1/2-quart casserole and arrange half the potatoes in overlapping rows.
Dot with half the butter.
Sprinkle with half of the herbs, peppers, onions, rice and zucchini.
Dot with remaining butter and repeat layering.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours or until potatoes are tender.
Remove cover and top with tomato slices and cheese.
Bake 10 minutes or until tomatoes are warm and cheese is melted.
Remove from oven.
Cover and let stand 10 minutes before serving.
Yield:
6 to 8 servings.

title: fudge krispies
directions: Combine chocolate, margarine and corn syrup in medium saucepan.
Stir over low heat until melted and smooth.
Remove from heat.
Stir in vanilla and confectioners sugar.
Add Rice Krispies, mixing until lightly coated.
Spread in buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
Chill until firm.
Cut into 48 bars.
Store in refrigerator.

title: creamy rice pudding
directions: Cook rice and water until water evaporates.
Add milk and butter.
Then add eggs, sugar and vanilla.
Stir over medium heat until thickened.
Sprinkle with cinnamon.

title: peach slush
directions: The best punch in the world for showers, weddings or parties! Bring water to a boil; remove from heat and add dry ingredients. Stir until dissolved. Stir in almond extract and pineapple juice. Divide mixture in 3 or 4 gallon Ziploc bags and freeze, laying the bags flat.

title: cheese fondue
directions: Chop cheeses into small chunks.
Strain soup mix and use 1/2 to 3/4 teaspoon of just powder.
Put powder in with milk and mix.
Put cheese in fondue pot and pour mixture over top.
Cook until cheeses are melted (approximately 1/2 hour).
Cut up bread into squares and toast.
Dip bread into cheese and enjoy!
Use assorted fruits (grapes, oranges, apples, etc.) for side dish.

title: devil's food cake
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease and flour two 9-inch cake pans. Melt chocolate in microwave or over double-boiler.
Cream butter and brown sugar.
Add eggs (one at a time).
Stir in chocolate. Combine dry ingredients.
Add flour mixture and buttermilk to the chocolate mixture in three stages, ending with flour.
Slowly stir in boiling water and vanilla.
Bake 30 minutes; remove pans from oven and let layers sit for 5 minutes.
Then invert pans over wire racks to cool.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix Ranch dressing to double strength using milk and mayonnaise.
Mix cream cheese and 1/2 cup of the double strength dressing with electric mixer.
Add Cheddar and blend well.
Cover and freeze 30 minutes.
Shape into ball; roll in chopped nuts or bacon bits, if desired.
Refrigerate.
(Use other half of dressing to make a second cheese ball; good for hostess gift!)

title: seafood salad
directions: Grind in food chopper: tuna fish, crabmeat, eggs, pickles, celery and onion.
Blend vinegar, mayonnaise, sugar, Beau Monde seasoning, salt and cream cheese together.
Combine all ingredients and chill well.
Garnish with stuffed olives.
(One can salmon may also be added, if desired.)

title: seafood spread
directions: In small bowl, combine cream cheese, onion, celery and sour cream.
Mix well.
Spread neatly in a circle on serving plate (dinner size).
In same bowl, mix together shrimp and crabmeat. Spread over cream cheese mixture.
Spread cocktail sauce over top. Serve with crackers.
Makes 2 cups.

title: pear ambrosia
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Mix well and chill until serving. Serves 4 to 6.

title: bacon dip
directions: Mix all ingredients and cover. Refrigerate several hours or overnight. Serve with assorted crackers or cut up vegetables. Makes 20 servings.

title: toffee crunch
directions: Boil butter and brown sugar until thickened.
Make 1 layer of saltine crackers, side by side, in bottom of jelly roll pan.
Pour butter-brown sugar mixture over crackers.
Bake for 10 to 15 minutes until bubbling.
Sprinkle chocolate chips and nuts; melt.

title: lentil soup
directions: In an 8 quart stock pot, combine water or broth, lentils, barley, salt, onion, carrot, celery and garlic. Cover and simmer for 20 minutes. Add the rest of the ingredients and simmer for another 20 minutes. Ladle into soup bowls. Serves 8 - 10. You may add left-over ham, if desired.

title: ranch beans
directions: Brown meat and the rest of the ingredients in skillet and simmer.

title: cheese spread
directions: Mix well all cheeses and oleo.
Add remaining ingredients. Keep in covered container.
Serve with crackers!

title: dishpan cookies
directions: Mix all together and drop by spoonfuls on greased cookie sheet.
Mash cookies down with fork.
Bake at 350° or 375° until brown.

title: greek spinach pita
directions: Wash and drain spinach; remove excess moisture with towel. Combine spinach with cheeses, eggs, onions, parsley, dill weed, oil and rice.
Arrange 8 to 10 fillo sheets in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Brush each one with melted oleo.
Pour in spinach mixture. Spread evenly throughout pan.
Cover with 8 to 10 fillo sheets and brush with melted butter (tops, too).
Mark desired pieces by cutting through top layers of fillo with sharp knife.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 to 1 1/4 hours or until golden brown. (Pyrex pans may bake faster.)

title: cinnamon sticky buns
directions: Soften yeast in warm water. Add milk, shortening, sugar and salt.
Cool to lukewarm.
Add 1 cup flour and beat well. Add yeast and egg.
Gradually add remaining flour to make soft dough, mixing well. Cover and let rise until double (1 1/2 hours). Roll out half of the recipe on floured surface.
Put mixture of 1/2 cup sugar, 1/4 cup melted butter and 1 1/2 teaspoons cinnamon over top. Roll like jelly roll and seal ends. Cut into 1 to 2-inch slices and place in prepared pan.

title: blushing pears(lo-cal)
directions: Arrange pears in 4 individual stemmed glasses.
Combine pear juice with remaining ingredients in medium saucepan and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, until reduced by half. Remove from heat; cool slightly.
Pour liquid over pears. Refrigerate until ready to serve.
Calories 76, cholesterol 0 and sodium 6.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine all ingredients and mix well. Drop by a teaspoon onto an ungreased cookie sheet.
Press crisscross on each cookie with fork tines dipped in water.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes until golden.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix salad ingredients together.

title: party punch
directions: Mix Hula Punch and Sprite. Add sherbet by the spoonful.
Mix and serve.
Serves 12 to 24.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Undercook broccoli; drain. Combine soup, butter, bread crumbs, sugar, salt, pepper and onion. Mix together. Add broccoli. Fold in beaten eggs. Bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour or until lightly browned.

title: chicken egg rolls
directions: Parboil sprouts.
Combine chicken, onion, celery, sprouts and mushrooms in skillet and saute.
Add soy sauce and egg and mix together.
Fill skins and seal skins with egg yolk.
Fold skins into squares.
Fry.
Serve with sweet and sour sauce, heated.

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: Melt margarine.
Add cocoa.
Stir in eggs and sugar.
Add flour, salt, nuts and vanilla; mix well.
Bake in greased oblong pan at 350° for about 30 minutes.
As soon as cake is taken from oven, sprinkle marshmallows over entire cake.

title: bean bake
directions: Mix all beans together.
Combine the remaining ingredients, except sausage; add to bean mixture.
Brown the sausage; add to mixture.
Mix well.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: pasta e fagioli
directions: In hot oil in 5-quart Dutch oven or heavy kettle, saute garlic and onion, stirring until golden, about 5 minutes. Add tomatoes, 1 teaspoon salt, the pepper, oregano and parsley. Simmer, covered, 30 minutes; mash tomatoes.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Brown sausage, pepper, onion and celery.
Pour off fat.
Bring water and noodle soup to a boil.
Add rice and cook 10 minutes. Add almonds.
Pour together and bake 30 minutes, covered, at 350° and 15 minutes, uncovered.
Total cooking time:
45 minutes.

title: my friend natalie grossiner's stuffed cabbage
directions: Place the cabbage in a kettle and add boiling water to cover. Let soak 15 minutes and drain.
Carefully remove 12 large leaves or if the leaves are too small, use 18.
Heat the fat in a large deep saucepan or casserole.
Add sliced onions and cook, stirring, until golden.
Add tomatoes, 1/2 salt, 1/2 pepper and bones. Simmer 30 minutes.

title: chicken packets
directions: Mix chicken, cream cheese, chives, milk and salt.
Unroll refrigerated crescent rolls.
Each tube will contain 4 rectangles of dough with a diagonal perforation.
Press dough along each perforation so that the rectangle halves will not separate.
Place 1/4 cup of chicken mixture into the center of each rectangle.
Fold dough over the filling and pinch the edges to seal tightly.
Dip each packet in melted margarine and coat with crouton crumbs. Place on baking sheet and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: chocolate glaze
directions: Melt chocolate and butter in saucepan over low heat.
Remove from heat and stir in sugar and milk.
Beat until smooth. Spread immediately on eclairs.
Yields about 1 cup.

title: potato pancakes
directions: Finely grate potatoes.
Drain any liquid.
Add eggs, onion, flour, salt and baking powder.
In a frying pan, add oil to the depth of 1/8-inch; heat over medium-high temperature.
Drop batter by heaping tablespoonfuls in hot oil.
Flatten to form patties. Fry until golden brown, then turn and cook other side.
May use leftover mashed potatoes instead of grated potatoes.

title: oatmeal drop cookies
directions: Cream shortening; add brown sugar and white sugar.
Blend thoroughly.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each one. Add vanilla.
Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Add to first mixture.
This will be very stiff.
Add oatmeal and stir with a spoon.
After mixing well, drop by teaspoonful on a greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes 8 dozen.

title: chinese chicken salad
directions: Mix desired quantities of chicken, lettuce, onion, sesame seed and cooked saifon noodles (follow directions on package).
Toss with dressing and serve.

title: cheesy sausage quiche
directions: Brown sausage or bacon, drain.
Cook onions and green pepper until crisp-tender, add to meat.
Spoon into pie shell.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Beat eggs until well blended.
Add remaining ingredients, mix well.
Pour over cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean. Cool 5 to 10 minutes before cutting into wedges.

title: onion-beef macaroni casserole
directions: Brown ground beef; drain. Stir in soup mix, flour, tomato sauce and water. Simmer, covered, for 5 minutes. Stir in macaroni. Place into 1 1/2-quart casserole dish. Sprinkle with cheese. Bake 15 minutes at 400°.

title: dirt cake
directions: Crush well (in the blender) one large package of Oreo cookies. Cream together margarine, cream cheese and powdered sugar.
Mix together milk, French vanilla pudding and Cool Whip.
Combine mixtures well.
Layer cookies and pudding, ending with cookies. Use 8-inch clay pot.
Cover holes in bottom with foil. Refrigerate overnight.
Add plastic flowers.
Serve with a new flower trowel.

title: pumpkin cookies
directions: Stir shortening to soften.
Add sugar and cream until smooth. Add eggs and mix well.
Add vanilla and pumpkin.
Stir flour, spices, salt, baking powder and soda together.
Gradually add to first mixture.
Beat after each addition until smooth.
Fold in chips.
Drop by teaspoon onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes or until brown.

title: coconut macaroons
directions: In a bowl, combine flour, coconut and salt.
Add milk and vanilla; mix well (batter will be stiff).
Drop by tablespoonfuls 1 inch apart onto a greased baking sheet.
Bake at 350 degrees for 15-20 minutes or until golden brown.
Remove to a wire rack to cool.

title: irene's christmas cookies
directions: Chop the dates, candied cherries and pineapple and walnuts. Cream thoroughly the butter and sugar. Beat in eggs. Add sifted dry ingredients and fruit and nuts. Drop on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 325-350° for 10 minutes.

title: spaghetti and cheese
directions: Saute onion, bell pepper and mushrooms in butter.
Add all ingredients and mix well in casserole dish.
Bake at 350° until bubbly.

title: pepperoni bread
directions: Roll bread dough to 10 x 18-inches.
Mix seasonings, cheese and egg together.
Spread on dough.
Top with pepperoni.
Roll up dough, seal ends.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes on greased cookie sheet.

title: brunch egg casserole
directions: Combine croutons and cheese in greased 10 x 6 x 2-inch baking dish.
Beat eggs; add milk and seasoning.
Pour over crouton mixture in casserole dish.
Crumble bacon over top.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour, or until eggs are set.
Garnish with bacon curls, if desired.
Yields 6 servings.

title: arnold felcher cake
directions: Mix cake ingredients together and bake at 350° about 25 minutes or until done.
Cool.

title: tamale dip
directions: Combine all ingredients in heavy saucepan over low heat. Simmer until cheese melts.
Serve warm with chips.

title: heavenly biscuits
directions: Sift together dry ingredients, cut in shortening.
Stir in buttermilk and yeast.
Turn out on floured board and knead.
Leave dough in refrigerator and take out as much as needed.
Roll about 1/2-inch thick and cut into biscuits.
Bake at 425° until brown (about 12 to 15 minutes).

title: ginger cake
directions: Mix the molasses, sugar and butter.
Add the egg beating all thoroughly.
Then add the boiling water, soda, ginger, salt and enough flour to make a soft dough.
Roll and cut into small pieces. Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Put fruit between layers.

title: emily's strawberry smoothie
directions: Put all ingredients in blender.
Blend on high till ice is crushed.

title: taco pie
directions: Use greased pie plate.
Brown ground beef and onions.
Drain. Stir taco seasoning in ground beef.
Spread in pie plate.
Top with green chilies.
Beat eggs and mix Bisquick and milk.
Pour over chilies.
Bake 25 minutes on 400°.
Top with tomatoes and Cheddar cheese.
Place back in oven for 8 to 10 minutes.
Remove from oven. Let cool 5 to 10 minutes.
Top with sour cream and lettuce.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Grease bottom and sides of 1 1/2 quart baking dish with butter or margarine.
Crumble 3/4 package crackers fine and place in bottom dish.
Add enough milk to wet crackers.
Add 1/2 can creamed corn.
Add remaining crackers, crumbled on top and repeat procedure.
Add butter on top.
Bake for 1 hour at 400°.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken in water until tender.
Save broth.
Cook rice in broth.
Combine soup, broth and sour cream.
Pour over chicken and rice in a casserole dish.
Top with crackers that are crushed fine.
Drizzle margarine over crackers.
Bake at 325° for 20 minutes.

title: texas straw hats
directions: In a large skillet, brown beef and drain.
Add onion, pepper and celery.
Simmer until tender.
Add all other ingredients except chips and cheese.
Simmer, uncovered, for 1 hour, stirring occasionally.
Serve on chips and top with cheese.

title: spanish rice
directions: Bring water to a boil.
Stir in rice, cheese, & picante sauce; cover and remove from heat.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Add tomato and pepper.
Let stand 10 minutes or to desired consistency.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: In 1-quart glass casserole microwave butter until melted. Combine with bread crumbs and walnuts.
Microwave 2 1/2 to 3 1/2 minutes, stirring halfway through cooking.
Blend with onion, chili sauce, salt, lemon juice and pepper.
Stuff mushrooms using about 1/2 tablespoon stuffing per cap.
Arrange 10 to 12 mushrooms on paper plate.
Microwave covered with wax paper, 6 minutes, rotating dish 1/4 turn halfway through cooking.
Serve hot.

title: golden peanut buster bars
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix all of the ingredients.
Spread in pan.
Before baking, drizzle 3 squares (1 ounce each) semi-sweet chocolate (melted and cooled) over top. Cut through batter to swirl chocolate.

title: no fuss fudge
directions: In a medium sauce pan combine milk and chocolate bits.
Cover over low heat stirring occasionally until bits melt and mixture is smooth.
Stir in wafers and nuts.
Blend until smooth.
Spread in buttered 8-inch square pan.
Refrigerate until firm.
Cut into squares.
Yield:
about 1 pound.

title: 6 week bran muffins
directions: Mix flakes, sugar, flour, salt and soda in large bowl.
Add eggs, oil and buttermilk.
Mix well.
Fill muffin tins 2/3 full. Bake 15 to 18 minutes at 400°.
Batter will keep in the refrigerator up to 6 weeks.

title: lenten applesauce cake
directions: Heat applesauce.
Add margarine, raisins and sugar.
When cool, add spices, salt, flour and soda.
Mix and add chopped nuts. Turn into greased 9 x 9-inch cake pan and bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients, then add the rest.
Put in well greased pan and bake at 400° until brown.
Lower temperature if getting too brown.

title: beer cheese soup
directions: Cook in saucepan the butter and flour.
Add the chicken broth and beer and cook until thick.
Add milk.
Cook and stir.
Add Cheez Whiz and blend.
Stir over medium heat until cooked through. Serves 4.

title: lake charles dip
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Chill well.
Stir before serving. Serve with bagel chips.
Yields 8 servings.

title: hot german rice salad
directions: In a skillet over medium heat, cook bacon until crisp. Drain, reserving 1/3 cup drippings. Crumble bacon and set aside. Add the sugar, vinegar, celery seed and pepper to drippings. Bring to a boil; cook and stir for 1 minute. Stir in pimientos, green pepper, onion, rice and bacon. Garnish with egg. Serve warm. Yield: 4 to 6 servings.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Mix pretzels, sugar and margarine.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake for 10 minutes at 350°.
Let cool completely.
Mix jello, water and strawberries.
Put in refrigerator until thickened.
Mix cream cheese, sugar and Cool Whip.
Spread over pretzel crust after jello and strawberries thicken.
Pour over top of cream cheese.
Refrigerate 3 to 4 hours.

title: grandma's sugar cookies
directions: Combine above ingredients in the order listed.
May be dropped or rolled.
Sprinkle with sugar or ice with glaze.
Bake for approximately 14 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: tallerina
directions: Cook hamburger and onion.
Cook egg noodles as instructions specify.
Mix all together in microwave-safe bowl.
Heat in microwave and serve.

title: buttermilk brownies
directions: In saucepan, combine butter, cocoa and 1 cup water.
Bring to boil; stir constantly.
Remove from heat.
In large bowl, sift together flour, sugar, soda and salt; stir in eggs, buttermilk and vanilla.
Add cocoa mixture; mix until blended.
Pour into greased 15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch baking pan.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.
Immediately pour Frosting over brownies; spread evenly. Cool; cut into bars.
Makes 60.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Combine the sugar and water; bring to a boil.
Mix together the remaining ingredients and pour sugar syrup over all.
Mix well.
Put in 50 Dixie cups or containers of choice.
Freeze.

title: oatmeal crispies
directions: Cream the sugar and shortening. Add egg and beat.
Add dry ingredients slowly and mix together.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: "chicken lynn"(serves 6)
directions: Boil chicken breasts until tender.
Cool slightly, then pull meat away from the bone and cut into bite size pieces.
Cover bottom of casserole with chicken pieces.

title: quick chicken casserole
directions: Cut chicken in bite-size pieces.
Spray 9 x 13-inch glass dish with Pam and mix ingredients well.

title: coconut cheesecake bars
directions: Melt butter and mix with cake mix and 1 egg.
Press mixture onto bottom of a buttered glass cake pan.
Mix cream cheese and 3 eggs until smooth.
Sift sugar in a little at a time.
Pour over crust and cover top with coconut.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes.
Do not let coconut burn.
If cheesecake is not set, let it bake a little longer.

title: moist chocolate cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together with mixer.
Batter will be very thin.
Can be baked in two 8 or 9-inch pans or one 9 x 13-inch baking pan or Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: blue ribbon brownies
directions: Heat oven to 350.
Grease 9 x 13 pan.
Microwave margarine in large glass bowl until melted.
Stir in sugar and vanilla.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well with spoon after each addition. Add flour, cocoa, baking powder, and salt.
Beat until well blended.
Stir in nuts.
Pour into pan and bake 30-35 minutes or until brownies begin to pull away from sides of pan.
Cool completely.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Brown chicken fingers in oil; set aside.
Measure water (add to chicken broth for a total of 4 cups liquid).
Bring to a boil. Add all ingredients; stir.
Lower heat to simmer and cover.
Cook until rice is done.
Serves 4.

title: creme de menthe parfait
directions: Combine all ingredients in container of blender.
Blend at medium speed until well mixed.
Spoon into parfait glasses. Place parfait glasses in freezer 3 or 4 hours.
Remove from freezer a few minutes before serving.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: macaroons
directions: Combine and beat thoroughly the first 7 ingredients.
Stir in walnuts, flour and soda (sifted together).
Blend.
Add rolled oats and mix well.
Measure out 1 level tablespoon of dough on greased baking sheet, leaving space between.
Press with fork. Bake in 350° oven for 12 to 15 minutes.
Cool 2 minutes before removing from sheet.
Makes 5 1/2 dozen.

title: sweet potato puff
directions: Whip cooked potatoes with butter, milk and pepper.
Beat in egg yolks.
Whip egg whites with salt until stiff.
Fold into potato mixture.
Place in greased 1 1/2-quart casserole dish. Bake in a 375° oven for 30 minutes or until top surface is lightly browned.
Makes 4 servings.

title: party cheese wreath
directions: Beat cream cheese and cheddar cheese with electric mixer on medium speed until well blended.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well.
Shape into a wreath.
(Easy if formed around a glass.) Decorate top with red pepper and green onion.

title: easy pineapple sherbet
directions: Drain crushed pineapple, reserving 3/4 cup juice.
Set pineapple aside.
Combine reserved mixture juice, 1 1/4 cups pineapple juice and sugar in a saucepan; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat; simmer, stirring occasionally, 3 minutes, or until sugar dissolves.
Pour into a large bowl; cover and chill.
Stir in carbonated beverage and milk.
Pour into freezer container of a 5-quart hand-turned or electric freezer.
Freeze according to manufacturer's instructions.
Transfer to a large bowl; fold in crushed pineapple.
Store in freezer.
Yields 6 1/4 cups (113 calories, 1% from fat, per 3/4-cup serving).

title: vinegar pie
directions: Mix well.
Pour in unbaked pie shell.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: cajun sauteed chicken
directions: Rub chicken with 3/4 teaspoon of Cajun seasoning mixture.
In a nonstick skillet over medium-high heat, heat oil.
Add chicken; brown for 2 minutes per side.
Remove chicken and reserve.
Add onion and green pepper to skillet.
Saute for 1 to 2 minutes, until vegetables begin to soften.
Add tomatoes, garlic and remaining Cajun seasoning.
Cook, stirring, for 2 to 3 minutes. Reduce heat to medium-low; return chicken to pan.
Cover; simmer for 6 to 12 minutes, turning 2 to 3 times, until chicken is cooked through.

title: caramel dip
directions: Mix all ingredients with a mixer.
Dip apple slices into mixture.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix butter and sugar.
Add eggs; mix thoroughly.
Add flour, salt and soda.
Put in the bananas.
Pour into a greased loaf pan. Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 1 hour, or until done.

title: fudgy brownies
directions: Melt butter and chocolate in microwave approximately 2 minutes and stir.
Whip together eggs, sugar and salt in bowl and add chocolate and butter.
Stir in flour, nuts and vanilla.
Stir all ingredients until just blended.
Pour into greased 7 x 11-inch or 9 x 9-inch baking pan.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes; reduce heat to 300° and bake another 30 minutes.
May ice with chocolate icing and sprinkle with chopped nuts or serve with vanilla ice cream.

title: chili
directions: Brown meat.
Add all other ingredients and simmer about 2 hours.

title: orange surprise salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin and Tang in boiling water; chill until slightly thickened.
Fold in remaining ingredients.
Pour into lightly oiled 5-cup mold and chill until firm.
Yield:
6 servings.

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water (1 cup).
Add 1/2 cup strawberry jam, 1/2 cup cold water and cornstarch.
Blend into dissolved Jell-O and cook over low heat until thick and clear. Cool to lukewarm.
Spoon 1/2 mixture into pie shell.

title: candied sweet potatoes
directions: Peel potatoes.
Cook sweet potatoes until tender.
Drain off water.
Put in casserole dish.
Add butter.
Mix sugars with spices.
Pour over.
Add honey.
Top with red hots.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: snack mix
directions: Mix butter, honey and brown sugar over low heat until well blended.
Mix first 6 ingredients, except raisins, in a large bowl.
Pour liquid over it and stir to coat.
Spread on cookie sheet and bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Put back into bowl and stir in raisins.
Spread out on wax paper to cool.

title: caramels
directions: Melt butter.
Add remaining ingredients except vanilla.
Cook to 238° (candy thermometer), stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla.
Pour into lightly buttered 7 x 11-inch pan. Let stand overnight, preferably in a cool place.
Cut in small pieces and wrap.

title: spinach-sprout salad
directions: Combine vegetables and sprouts in a large bowl. Add oil and toss. Add lemon juice and toss again. Serves 2.

title: mexican cornbread muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400° (375° convection). Mix all ingredients in large bowl. Scoop into preheated greased muffin tins. Bake for 30 minutes or until golden brown. Makes 48 muffins.

title: caramel dip
directions: Mix well and microwave 1 minute.
This is good served with slices of raw apple.

title: cucumber dill dip
directions: Beat cream cheese and stir in remaining ingredients.
Cover and chill.
Makes 2 1/2 cups.

title: potato casserole
directions: Pour hash browns into a 9 x 13 pan or Pyrex dish. Drizzle with 1/2 stick butter. Sprinkle with chopped onion, then salt and pepper. Stir together the soup and sour cream. Spread on the hash browns. Sprinkle with cheese; top with crushed cornflakes or cracker crumbs. Drizzle with remaining butter. Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: coleslaw
directions: Combine vegetables.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Add 1 cup sugar and toss.
Add juice of 1/2 lemon and vinegar.
Toss again.

title: caramel flan
directions: Pour Eagle Brand milk into blender.
Use can to measure fresh milk.
Add eggs, vanilla and 1/4 cup sugar.
Blend 1 minute.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add eggs.
Beat well.
Add other ingredients.
Pour into 1 large or 2 small loaf pans.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Bake just until no fingerprint shows on top.
Do not overbake.

title: peanut butter chocolate chip cheesecake
directions: Heat oven to 300°.
Stir together crumbs, sugar, cocoa and margarine.
Press into bottom of 9-inch spring-form pan.
In large mixer bowl, beat cream cheese until fluffy.
Gradually beat in sweetened milk, then peanut butter chips until smooth.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Beat well.
Stir in chocolate chips.
Pour over crust. Bake 55 to 65 minutes or until center is set.
Cool. Refrigerate.
Garnish as desired.
Cover.

title: wiki wiki stew
directions: Brown meat and drain oil.
Add stew mix and water according to the directions on the package and a dash of garlic powder.
When mixed, add mixed vegetables and simmer until the vegetables are soft.
Add curry powder, if you like.
Serve stew over rice. Tsukemono would be nice to have on the side.

title: onion pizza bread
directions: Saute onions in butter until soft; add brown sugar to taste. Layer on pizza bread.
Heat in oven at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes, until heated through.
Slice and serve warm.

title: salmon supreme
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients and shape into ball.
Roll in parsley or chives and chopped pecans.
Refrigerate overnight.
Serve with crackers.

title: beef burritos
directions: In crock-pot put both arm roasts and season with usual seasonings.
Cook until meat falls apart.
Take meat from pot and place on plate to cool.
Save juice in crock-pot.
Shred beef, removing any fat.
Place shredded beef back in crock-pot and add both packages burrito mix.
Let cook on high about 1 hour, longer if you wish.
Take tortilla shells one at a time and spoon meat mixture into shells.
Roll and place in 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Continue process until all meat is gone, use extra pans if necessary.
Pour remaining juice over burritos.
Shred cheese; cover burritos with cheese.
Cover pan with foil and cook in 350° oven for about 20 minutes or until cheese is melted.
Extra burritos may be put in freezer and used layer.

title: chocolate lush(mmmm-delicious)
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients like pie crust.
Press into a 13 x 9 pan.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Mix together cream cheese and sugar.
Stir in Cool Whip. Spread this mixture over the cooled crust.
Mix pudding and milk. Spread over top of other layer.
Top all layers with remaining Cool Whip.
Sprinkle with chocolate sprinkles.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Wash cucumbers and then slice.
Add onions, peppers and whole garlic cloves.
Add salt, cover with cracked ice and water.
Let stand at least 3 hours.
Drain and rinse thoroughly.
Combine remaining ingredients, pour over cucumber mixture.
Heat just to a boil.
Seal in hot sterilized jars.
Makes 8 pints.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Mix together sugar, flour, soda, salt, eggs and fruit cocktail. Put in a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Then mix brown sugar and chopped nuts; put on top of cake.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: Boil 7-Up, sugar, salt and cornstarch until thick and clear. Remove from heat and add strawberry Jell-O. Cool completely. Line bottom of a baked pie shell with a few strawberries. Add remaining strawberries to the cooked mixture. Top with whipped cream.

title: date nut bread
directions: Mix dates, water and soda.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Add sugar, shortening, egg and vanilla, alternating with flour.
Lastly, fold in nuts.
Bake in greased loaf pans at 350° for 1 hour.

title: green split pea soup
directions: Soak peas in cold water overnight.
Sort and drain.
Add water and bring to a boil.
Skim off top and add vegetables.
Simmer 2 or 3 hours, stirring from time to time.
Add more water if necessary or
if the soup is too thick.
Season according to taste.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Cook noodles as directed and drain.
Add tuna, milk, mushroom soup, salt and pepper.
Mix well.
Put in baking dish.
Top with crushed crackers.
Cook at 350° for about 45 minutes.

title: smooth and creamy frosting
directions: Combine pudding, sugar and milk.
Beat slowly until well blended.
Fold in whipped topping.
Makes about 4 cups.

title: millionaire pie
directions: Cream butter, eggs and sugar.
Add vanilla.
Pour creamed mixture into a baked pie crust and refrigerate until firm.
Drain pineapple.
Mix together whipped topping, pineapple and pecans and cover pie.
Keep refrigerated.

title: fudgy brownie bonbons
directions: Preheat oven to 400°. Line mini-muffin pans with papers.
Melt chocolate with 2 tablespoons of butter on top of a double boiler. Remove from heat and blend.
Reserve.

title: bran muffins
directions: Melt margarine in water and add remaining ingredients in order listed.
Bake in muffin tin at 400° for 20 minutes.
Batter will keep in covered container for 6 weeks in refrigerator.
May add raisins to batter.

title: apple crisp
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch pan.
Put sliced apples on bottom.
Beat up mixture; pour over apples.
Dot with butter.
Sprinkle sugar-cinnamon on top.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: icing
directions: Put all together in bowl.
Beat real good.

title: poppy seed cake
directions: Mix all ingredients in mixer. Pour into greased and floured Bundt pan. Bake 45 to 60 minutes at 350°.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix sugar, oil and eggs.
Sift dry ingredients together. Bake in 2 loaf pans that have been greased and floured for 1 hour at 350°.

title: pot roast with carrots
directions: Season beef with salt, pepper and paprika.
In Dutch oven over high heat sear beef until golden.
Remove and set aside.
In same Dutch oven saute onions in oil 5 minutes.
Stir in undiluted tomato soup, catsup, lemon juice and sugar.
Bring to boil.
Add beef, cover and simmer 3 hours until beef is fork-tender.
Remove beef and place on cutting board.
Add carrots to pan liquid and cook 10 minutes.
Slice beef, place on serving platter.
Separate carrots and onions from sauce.
Place them around beef.
Pour sauce in gravy boat.

title: corn chili
directions: In large heavy saucepan heat oil over moderate heat.
Add onion and garlic.
Stir to coat, then simmer until onion is softened. Add chili powder, cayenne and cumin.
Stir to blend.
Cook for at least 3 minutes, stirring frequently.
Add celery, peppers and tomatoes.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Add beans and corn.
Simmer 20 minutes.
Season with salt.
Serves 4.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix eggs, sugar, salt and pepper.
Boil milk and margarine; add to mixture.
Add corn.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: fresh fruit salad
directions: Butter medium sized casserole dish and arrange fruit in layers.
Combine butter, sugar, flour and sherry in double boiler. Cook, stirring, until smooth and thickened.
Pour over fruit. Top with
pecans; cover and let stand in refrigerator overnight. Before serving, heat in oven at 350°.
Yields 6 servings.

title: burrito favorite
directions: Brown ground meat in 1 tablespoon cooking oil.
Add bell pepper, onion, salt, pepper, Ro-Tel tomatoes and Velveeta cheese. Simmer on low heat for about 15 minutes.

title: speedy salsa dip
directions: Stir and mix ingredients well.
Serve as a dip for raw veggies or chips.

title: sugar nuts
directions: Cook sugar and orange juice to 240° or soft ball stage. Remove from heat; add peel and nuts.
Stir until syrup begins to look cloudy.
Before mixture hardens, drop spoonfuls on waxed paper.
Separate into desired size clusters.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain all fruit except	pineapple.
Put
in
glass bowl with pineapple and juices
and
add
box
(small)
instant vanilla pudding.
Use any size
large
or small cans of fruit. Mix the same way.
Banana can be
used if you are going to eat it all in same day (otherwise, bananas turn dark).
This keeps well in the refrigerator for a week.

title: southern cornbread stuffing
directions: Melt butter in heavy pan.
Add onions and celery; saute until tender.
Add dry ingredients, seasoning and egg; blend well.
Add stock and mix thoroughly.
(Use less liquid when stuffing a turkey.)
Bake at 375° for 30 to 40 minutes in a well-greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.

title: coconut-pecan frosting
directions: In saucepan, combine sugar, evaporated milk, egg yolks, Crisco and vanilla.
Cook and stir over medium heat until it comes to a boil.
Remove from heat and add coconut and pecans.
Beat until frosting is thick.
Cool 15 minutes.

title: french style baked chicken
directions: May use skinless chicken breasts.

title: baked blueberry pudding cake with lemon sauce(weston's mom's favorite)
directions: Mix and pour in greased and floured 9 x 9-inch pan.
Top with blueberries. Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.

title: boiled cookies
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa, milk and butter in a saucepan and bring to a boil over medium heat; boil for 1 minute. Add remaining ingredients; mix well. Drop on foil or waxed paper. Cools quickly. Can substitute crunchy peanut butter and omit nuts.

title: cheese dip
directions: Brown sausage and drain; set aside.
In the crock-pot, place 1 stick butter and break into pieces the Velveeta cheese.
Add Ro-Tel and cover.
Cook on high and stir frequently until melted.
Add the browned sausage.
Stir and keep warm.
Enjoy with tortilla chips or raw veggies.

title: kentucky wonder pound cake
directions: Mix all the ingredients and drop on greased cookie sheet. Bake at 350°.

title: hamburger-noodle casserole
directions: Fry hamburger and onion until brown.
Cook noodles in salted water until tender.
Drain noodles; add meat and soup.
Pour into greased casserole and cover with buttered bread crumbs and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
May add milk or water if too dry.

title: banana chocolate cake
directions: Sift flour, baking soda and salt together. Cream shortening and sugar. Add eggs one at a time. Beat thoroughly after each. Add chocolate and mix. Stir in vanilla. Add dry ingredients alternately with banana and milk. Bake 30 to 35 minutes at 350°. Makes 2 (9-inch) layers.

title: chocolate mayonnaise cake
directions: Grease and flour 2 (9-inch) cake pans.
In large mixing bowl with mixer at low speed, blend all ingredients 30 seconds.
Beat at medium speed 2 more minutes.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: pineapple fluff
directions: Mix
everything
together in a large bowl.
Pour into a large baking dish or pan and freeze. Remove from freezer a few minutes before
ready
to serve and cut into squares.

title: apple crumb dump cake
directions: Dump both cans of pie filling in large buttered casserole dish. Spread it out in bottom of dish. Dump dry cake mix on top of pie filling. Spread evenly. Cut butter into 1/4-inch pads, placing evenly on dry mix. Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours. Add cherries just as butter starts to melt (you can use the juice from the cherries).

title: strawberry glazed cheesecake
directions: To make crust:
In medium bowl, combine crumbs, walnuts and cinnamon.
Add melted butter and mix thoroughly.
Press mixture on bottom and 3 inches up sides of 9-inch spring-form pan.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Mix pretzels, 3 tablespoons sugar and margarine together and press into a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 400° for 6 minutes.
(Do not let pretzels burn.)
Cool.

title: granola
directions: Preheat oven to 275°.
Combine all ingredients in a large bowl, except honey.
Stir in honey to blend evenly.
Spread in shallow pan.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes, until all lightly toasted. Cool completely in pan.
Crumble and store in airtight container. Makes 4 cups.

title: psole (hominy stew)
directions: Cook the meat until done.
Add the hominy and all other ingredients, except the oregano and the saffron.
Simmer about two hours.
Add the oregano and the saffron and let simmer 15 minutes. Serve on dry toast with a side dish of cottage cheese.

title: butterhorns(rolls)
directions: In a large bowl, combine flour, sugar and salt. Cut in butter as for pie crust; set aside. Dissolve yeast in water. Add egg with milk to the flour mixture; mix well.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.

title: spinach and jalapeno cheese casserole
directions: Cook spinach, drain well and reserve liquor.
Melt butter, add flour, onion, milk, reserved spinach liquor, seasonings and cheese.
Stir until smooth and cheese is melted.
Put spinach in bottom of buttered casserole and cover with sauce.
Top with buttered cracker crumbs and bake at 350 degrees for 20 minutes.

title: peach jello salad
directions: Chop peaches and drain well.
Save syrup to use in making Jell-O.
Let Jell-O set to syrup stage.
Mix peaches, cream cheese, mayonnaise and Cool Whip.
Fold into Jell-O.

title: creamy lemon pie
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
In medium bowl, beat egg yolks with Eagle Brand, lemon juice and food coloring (just a few drops). Pour into prepared pastry shell and bake 30 minutes.
Cool and then refrigerate.
Spread with whipped cream and serve.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Mix all together, reserving 1 cup of cheese to sprinkle on top.
Place in 8 x 8 x 2-inch greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serve with crackers.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: Mix sugar, peanuts, salt and syrup.
Cook 7 1/2 minutes on High, then add butter and vanilla.
Cook 2 minutes on High.
Add soda and stir.
Pour onto greased cookie sheet.
When cool, break into chunks.

title: pizza rounds
directions: Mix all together and spread on bread slices. Lay on cookie sheet and bake at 350° until brown.

title: chicken and dressing casserole
directions: Boil chicken
and
spices
for	approximately
45 to 60 minutes. Remove
chicken
from broth and cool completely. Save broth.
Pick chicken
from bone and cut into pieces and spread pieces in any
size
casserole
dish
(9 x 13-inch or larger). Take soup directly	from
can and mix together and spread over chicken. Pour 3/4 cup of broth over the chicken, then take the stuffing mix and
sprinkle	the
whole
bag
evenly
over
the chicken.
Pour 1
1/2 cups broth over the dressing.
Make sure the dressing is
saturated.
Bake
at
for 20 minutes or until dressing is crispy on top.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Cook at 350° for 1 hour.

title: hopkins county stew
directions: Marinate chicken in 3 cans V-8 juice and chili powder.
Bring chicken stock to boil and add chicken, V-8 juice, potatoes and onions.
Simmer 20 minutes or until tender.
Add corn, salt, pepper and sugar.

title: simple chili
directions: Brown and drain ground beef.
Mix together soup, beans, onions, chili powder, salt and pepper.
Add ground beef.
Cook over low heat until ready to serve.
Can simmer all day.

title: lola's pepper jelly
directions: Dissolve sugar in vinegar in a saucepan.
Bring mixture to
a boil
and
add
Certo.
Let
mixture set for 10 minutes before pouring
into
jars.
You
may use your choice of food coloring for color.	Add after the Certo.
If you like it hot, add 1/4 cup red hot peppers.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Break the tortilla chips in bottom of casserole dish that has been sprayed with Pam.
Cook the chicken breasts until tender. Debone and cut in chunks. Save broth (at least 1 cup).
Add to the broth the soup, picante sauce, green chillies and sour cream. Pour all this over chicken chunks and tortilla chips.
Cover with the cheese and bake for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: jelly-tart cookies
directions: Preheat your oven to 350°.
Spoon the jelly into a small bowl and stir until it is smooth; set aside.
In a large bowl, using a wooden spoon, blend together the butter and sugar until the mixture is light and fluffy.

title: strawberry gelatin salad
directions: Drain oranges, reserving syrup.
Add enough water to syrup to make 3/4 cup.
Combine sugar and gelatin.
Add syrup and orange and lemon juices.
Heat over medium heat until gelatin is dissolved.
Gradually stir half of the mixture into the eggs. Return to heat and cook, stirring constantly for 2 minutes or until thickened.
Remove from heat; add sour cream and cream cheese.
Beat until smooth.
Chill until partially set.
Fold in fruit and nuts.
Chill in an 8 x 8-inch casserole dish until firm.

title: quick and easy salmon chowder
directions: Mix everything in a pan. Add the salmon last (2 to 3 minutes before serving). Heat at moderate temperature; do not boil. Serve.

title: yeast rolls
directions: Stir yeast, warm water and sugar together and set aside. Soften Crisco in microwave or on stove top.
Add 1 1/2 cups warm water, salt, egg and flour (more or less, depending on consistency of dough).
Add the two mixtures together.
Knead. Let rise until double (2 hours or so).

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix cream cheese and marshmallow cream together until smooth. Place in a bowl in center of a platter and arrange fruit around it. Strawberries, grapes and cantaloupe work best.
Very simple and extremely delicious.
Dip fruit in bowl and enjoy.

title: chocolate chews
directions: Cream sugar, shortening and vanilla; beat in eggs and chocolate.
Sift dry ingredients, add with milk.
Add walnuts. Chill 2 to 3 hours.
Form in balls and roll in powdered sugar. Place on greased baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: easy chicken and rice casserole
directions: Directions:
Preheat oven to 325-350°.
Grease (with Pam) a large casserole dish and set aside.
Mix soup and water in large bowl.
Add rice and mix thoroughly to make sure rice gets moist. Pour mixture into casserole dish.
Place chicken pieces on top of mixture or cover them with mixture if preferred.
Season with salt & pepper to taste.
Add margarine sparingly before putting in oven. Bake approximately 1 hour and 15 min.
Velveeta cheese can also be added before baking for extra flavor.

title: shrimp rice
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes, uncovered, in greased dish.

title: mini meatballs
directions: Combine soy sauce, water, garlic, ginger and sugar in a large bowl.
Add beef and mix lightly.
Form into balls about 1 inch in diameter.
Arrange on a lightly greased baking dish.
Bake, uncovered, for 15 minutes.
Serve on toothpicks.
Makes 32 meatballs, 32 calories.

title: hot fudge in a hurry
directions: Heat pudding to bubbling; pour over ice cream and add a little instant topping and cherry if desired.

title: seems impossible coconut custard pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat eggs with a mixer for 3 minutes. Add melted oleo, sugar, flour, salt, milk and vanilla.
Beat until well blended.
Stir in coconut.
Pour into a buttered 10-inch glass pie dish.
Bake 40 minutes.
Makes its own crust.
Very good!!

title: spinach salad
directions: Toss all ingredients together.

title: five cup salad
directions: Mix thoroughly and chill overnight.

title: grandma utterback's easy apple crumb pie
directions: Peel, core and slice apples into a glass pie plate.
Over apples, sprinkle 1/2 cup sugar and the cinnamon.
Then, in a separate bowl crumble together 1/2 cup sugar, the flour and the oleo.
Sprinkle over the apples and bake at 375° until brown and bubbly.

title: million dollar pie
directions: Blend milk and lemon juice.
Add remaining ingredients and blend well.
Pour into 3 baked 9-inch pie shells or two 9 x 13-inch graham cracker crusts.
Chill.

title: fast vegetable dip
directions: Mix all together. Store in refrigerator.

title: chocolate angel pie
directions: Put first 3 ingredients in top of double boiler and melt. When mixture is completely cool, fold in whipped topping.
Place in cooled, baked 8-inch pie shell.
Top with additional topping and slivered almonds.

title: fruit pudding for diabetics
directions: Mix pudding by package directions.
Add choice of fruit (sliced strawberries, whole blueberries, blackberries, dewberries, cherries or sliced bananas).
Cooked rhubarb can be used as fruit.
If desired, pour into baked pie shell or add vanilla wafers.

title: grandma's applesauce cake
directions: Grease and flour a 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan or two 7 3/8 x 3 5/8 x 2 1/4-inch loaf pans.
Mix ingredients together; pour into loaf pan(s).
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes or until done.

title: caramel apple salad
directions: Mix apples and chopped candy bars until well blended. Gently stir in whipped topping. Refrigerate one hour or until ready to serve.
Garnish with apple slices. Salad is best made and served the same day. Makes 20 servings.

title: oven swiss steak
directions: Cut meat into serving size portions, dredge meat in flour, salt and pepper mixture.
Brown meat in small amount of hot shortening, remove and place in shallow baking dish.
Put remaining ingredients (except cheese) in skillet and heat to boiling, pour over meat.
Cover and bake at 350° for two hours or until tender.
If desired, top with cheese, return to oven for a few minutes.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream together brown sugar and margarine.
Add eggs, flour, soda, salt and vanilla.
Mix in oats and raisins.
Divide dough into 3 or 4 batches and shape into a roll on wax paper.
Roll up and chill in refrigerator for 1 hour.
Slice and bake at 325° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Cool and remove from baking sheet.
Rolls of dough can be frozen until ready to use.

title: red new potato salad
directions: Clean and boil potatoes with skins.
Cool and cut up with skins.
Add the rest of the ingredients and mix well.

title: great grapefruit pops
directions: In a pitcher, combine all ingredients; stir until mixed.
Pour into twelve 3-ounce paper cups.
Cover each cup with foil.
Make a small hole in the foil with a knife.
Insert a wooden stick through the hole.
Freeze for 6 hours or until firm.
Remove from freezer 5 minutes before serving.
Remove foil and peel paper cups from pops. Makes 12.
Enjoy.

title: hayden's salad
directions: Peel and
chop
tomatoes;
sprinkle
salt over them and let them
stand
hours.
Then
pour into colander and drain well (1 to 2 hours). Chop onions, green pepper, banana peppers and
hot pepper.
Shred
cabbage
and
break cauliflower into small pieces.
Mix with drained tomatoes. Add vinegar, sugar, celery seed and mustard seed. Mix well and heat until sugar is dissolved; bring
to
a rolling boil only.
Remove from heat. Pack into jars and seal.
Makes approximately 15 pints.

title: avocado stuffed with crab louis
directions: In bowl mix egg yolk, mustard, Worcestershire and vinegar. Beat constantly, add oil slowly until smooth and thick. Add chili sauce, scallions and olives, mix well. Season to taste. Add crab to half the sauce. Mix gently. In halved avocados, pile with equal portions of crab mixture. Spoon remaining sauce over.

title: gary's tomato salad
directions: Set bacon aside.
Toss all ingredients except bacon.
Sprinkle bacon on top of each serving.
Serves 8.

title: bonfire lettuce salad
directions: Day before, marinate garlic, oil and lemon juice for dressing. Mix other ingredients and sprinkle with seasoned salt.
Toss with dressing.

title: praline candy
directions: Boil together sugar, milk, syrup and water until soft ball forms when tested in cold water.
Remove from heat; add butter. Cool.
Add vanilla and beat until creamy.
Add pecans and drop by spoonfuls on wax paper.

title: peanut brittle(microwave)
directions: Mix sugar and white Karo; cook 4 minutes on High.
Add peanuts and cook for 3 1/2 minutes.
Add vanilla and butter, then cook 1 1/2 minutes.
Remove from microwave and add soda; stir and mix. Pour onto buttered cookie sheet.
It should make 4 patties.
Let cool and it will come up.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Cook raisins until soft.
Drain.
Save 5 tablespoons of the raisin water for later.

title: tiger butter
directions: Line a 15 1/2 by 10 1/2 inch jelly roll pan with wax paper. Break white chocolate into 1-inch pieces in a 1 1/2 quart bowl. Microwave on high 1 to 2 minutes or until melted.
Stir until smooth.
Add peanut butter and microwave on high for 2 minutes or until melted; stir until smooth.
Spread into pan.
In a 2 cup measuring cup, melt chocolate chips on high 1 to 2 minutes.
Pour melted chocolate over peanut butter mixture; swirl with a knife. refrigerate until firm; cut or break into pieces.

title: sausage and rice
directions: Brown sausage; drain.
Add onion; cook until tender.
Stir in water and oregano.
Bring to boil.
Stir in rice and parsley. Cover and remove from heat.
Let stand for 5 minutes; fluff with fork.
Stir in cheese and mushroom soup.
Heat until cheese is melted.

title: grandma's butter cookies
directions: Sift flour.
Cream butter and sugar; add egg and vanilla.
Add all dry ingredients.
Roll out 1/8-inch thick on floured breadboard.
Cut into desired shapes with cookie cutters.
Bake at 400° for 8 to 12 minutes (or until lightly brown).
Makes 3 to 4 dozen cookies.

title: pop's fruit salad
directions: Drain most of liquid off fruit.
Mix together fruit.
You can add watermelon, cantaloupe, strawberries or any other fruit you prefer.
Add sugar (about 1/4 to 1/2 cup or to taste).
Secret ingredient is Tang.
Add about 1/2 cup or to taste.
This recipe makes a large amount.
You may reduce the recipe if you like, just use 13 ounce cans instead of 29 ounce cans.

title: easy layer bars
directions: Pour melted butter in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle cracker crumbs over butter.
Sprinkle coconut evenly over crumbs.
Top with chocolate chips, butterscotch chips and nuts.
Pour milk over entire mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until lightly browned on top.
Cool and cut into bars.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown meat in skillet.
Add onions and saute until limp.
Drain beans and add to meat.
Refrigerate until chilled.
Add chopped tomatoes, torn lettuce and broken Doritos.
Sprinkle with grated cheese and toss with dressing.
Top with sliced avocados.
Serve immediately.

title: country style spareribs
directions: Place ribs on rack in shallow roasting pan.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes, turning once.
Baste with sauce and bake about 20 minutes more.

title: easy clam chowder
directions: Simmer the first 7 ingredients until vegetables are tender. Then add milk, salt and cheese and heat until hot.

title: caddo pickles
directions: Heat liquid ingredients to a boil; add remaining ingredients. Simmer on low until tomatoes turn gray.
(Do not boil.)
Seal in sterile jars.
Makes 6 pints.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Brown hamburger, peppers and onions; drain.
Mix box of cornbread as directed on box (add a little more liquid to help it spread easier).
Spread 1/2 of cornbread mix in bottom of a baking dish.
Spread hamburger mixture on top of bread, then spread corn, then taco sauce, then cheese.
Spread the rest of cornbread mix on top.
Bake at 450° for 35 minutes or until golden brown.

title: veggie bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Unroll crescent rolls on a 17 x 11 1/2-inch baking sheet.
Press to make 2 sheets of dough (side by side).
Bake 10 minutes and cool.

title: pumpkin fudge
directions: In heavy saucepan, combine sugar, milk, oleo, pumpkin and pumpkin pie spice.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly. Continue boiling until mixture reaches 234° on a candy thermometer.
Remove from heat.
Stir in butterscotch morsels, Marshmallow Creme, nuts and vanilla.
Mix well.
Quickly pour into greased 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Cool at room temperature.
Cut into squares.
Store tightly wrapped in refrigerator.

title: kidney bean coleslaw
directions: Toss all together with mayonnaise to moisten. Serve with rings of green pepper.

title: diet cheese cake
directions: In a blender mix cottage cheese, Equal and vanilla until creamy and smooth.
In 1/4 cup boiling water dissolve Jell-O and add lemon juice.
Stir until well dissolved and set aside to cool.

title: maryland blue crab imperial soup(aka cream of crab soup)
directions: Melt butter, blend in flour and pepper. Stir, simmer for 2 minutes.
Add milk and crushed bouillon cubes.
Simmer and stir constantly until mixture thickens enough to coat spoon.
Salt to taste, add crabmeat and heat but do not boil.

title: doris' creamy olive spread
directions: Beat cream cheese well.
Stir in mayonnaise.
Add remaining ingredients and stir well.
Cover and chill 24 hours.
Serve on rye bread.

title: spanish rice in a pot
directions: Brown ground beef and onion in pot until done.
Drain meat. Set aside in dish.
Brown uncooked rice in meat drippings.
Add all ingredients to rice.
Add meat.
Cover and simmer for 30 minutes.

title: apple salad
directions: Cut apples up.
Pour lemon juice over apples and stir.
Whip whipping cream.
Add mayonnaise to cream.
Pour pecans, marshmallows and celery into apples.
Mix in whipping cream.

title: hazel's candied walnuts
directions: Combine sugar and cinnamon.
Stir in milk and cook to 235° soft ball.
Quickly stir in vanilla and nuts.
Pour onto waxed paper and quickly separate.
Two spoons work best.
Store in an old fruitcake tin.
A nibble no one can resist and the hit of our Elders' and Deacons' retreat.

title: kathy's vegetable salad
directions: Combine all vegetables in a large bowl.

title: roulade
directions: Saute 1 1/2 cups mushrooms, celery, water chestnuts, oysters and chopped green onions in butter about 10 minutes.
Then mix in bread crumbs, mayonnaise, sage to taste, chicken stock, red wine, parsley and salt and pepper to taste.

title: smoke beans
directions: Saute onion and green pepper.
Remove and brown meat.
Drain. Mix remaining ingredients and bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Peel eggplant and parboil for 5 minutes.
Combine eggs, milk, onions, cheese, bread cubes and seasonings.
Add eggplant and mix well. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, or until top browns.

title: old-fashioned rhubarb torte
directions: In a mixing bowl, combine 3/4 cup flour, powdered sugar and salt.
Cut in butter as for pastry.
Pat into a 6 x 10-inch baking pan.
Bake crust at 375° for 10 minutes.

title: chocolate pudding
directions: Use a large frying pan.
Pour
2 3/4 cups of water into frying pan; bring to a boil.
Add sugar.
Add salt.
Combine in a glass and stir until soupy the flour, cocoa and 1/2 cup of hot water. Pour into boiling water in pan; stir.
Add vanilla flavoring and 1/2 stick butter.
Stir.
Sop with homemade biscuits.

title: zucchini "crab cakes"
directions: Mix all ingredients. Form into 8 patties. Saute in small amount of oil until golden brown. Serve with tartar sauce.

title: hamburger rolls
directions: Fry hamburger with green pepper, salt and pepper; drain well. Add hard-boiled eggs, olives and tomato sauce.
Let simmer until mixed well.
While in pan, layer cheese over top and cover.
When cheese starts to boil, stir thoroughly.
Stuff mixture into French rolls and wrap in foil.
Bake at 300° for 20 minutes.
Makes about 18 to 19 rolls.

title: old-fashioned pumpkin bread
directions: *I always drain my pineapple juice into a measuring cup, then add a little water, if needed in order to make up 2/3 cup water.

title: dannon apple spice cake
directions: In large bowl, combine flour, sugar, baking soda, baking powder, cinnamon, allspice, salt and cloves.
Mix applesauce, yogurt, egg and oil.
Blend with dry ingredients.
Stir in raisins.

title: veggie squares
directions: Place dough on jelly roll pan; press together so there are no perforations or breaks in dough.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes. Remove from oven and cool.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Cut in shortening until mixed thoroughly.
Add buttermilk and yeast, dissolved in 1/2 cup lukewarm water.
Work together until flour is moist.
Cover bowl and put in refrigerator until ready to use.
Take out as much dough as needed.
Roll out 1/2-inch thick and cut.
Bake at 400° on greased cookie sheet 12 minutes or until brown.
Makes 6 dozen. Dough will keep several weeks in the refrigerator.

title: fruit salad bowl
directions: Section grapefruits and oranges.
Peel, pit and slice avocado. Put in bowl with salad greens.
Refrigerate while dressing is being made.
Put lemon juice, oil and tangerine juice in blender. Whirl until well mixed.
Pour over salad and mix thoroughly.

title: pepperoni bread
directions: Roll dough to a 9 x 12-inch pan (jelly roll pan).
Combine oregano, salt, parsley flakes and garlic powder with melted butter. Brush lightly on dough.
Save a little for top.
Arrange pepperoni on top of dough and cover with cheese.
Roll like a jelly roll, tightly (to look like a French loaf of bread).
Brush with remaining butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes on cookie sheet. Cool for 15 minutes before cutting.
Great with spaghetti or served alone with a salad.

title: lemon meringue pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour and salt; add water.
Add beaten egg yolks to sugar mixture.
Cook in double boiler over hot water, stirring until thick.
Cover.
Cook 10 minutes.
Add margarine, lemon juice and rind.
Pour into 9-inch pastry shell and top with meringue. Bake in 350° oven for 10 minutes.

title: chipped beef on toast
directions: Melt butter in pan, medium to low heat. Tear or cut up beef and add to butter. Simmer approximately 10 minutes. Whisk 3 tablespoons flour into 3/4 cup milk. Add milk and flour to beef and butter. Cook on low heat approximately 5 to 10 minutes. Slowly add milk while stirring mixture (add 1 cup milk) and stir until mixture gets thick, then add more milk and stir and continue to stir until sauce is creamy. Simmer for approximately 20 minutes. Toast the bread. Put toast or bread and spoon the creamed beef over it.

title: rice with pigeon peas
directions: In large saucepan on medium heat, add olive oil and bacon. Brown bacon.
Add garlic, onion and green pepper.
Stir often until browned.
Add tomatoes and green olives.
Stir in tomato sauce, all-purpose seasoning and cilantro.
Add peas and 2 cups water. Cover pan and boil for 1/2 hour.
Add rice and 1 cup water.
Cook on high, uncovered, for 15 minutes.
Reduce heat, cover pan and simmer until rice is done (about 20 minutes).
Stir occasionally. Yields 6 servings.

title: cheesecake supreme
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.

title: microwave spaghetti and meat sauce
directions: In a 3-quart casserole, mix together the meat, onion, celery and garlic.
Cover; cook on High 10 minutes, stirring twice. Drain off fat.
Stir in tomatoes and liquid, tomato paste, salt, pepper, Worcestershire sauce, parsley, basil, oregano and bay leaf.
Cook on High 25 minutes, stirring twice.
Remove bay leaf. Serve sauce over spaghetti.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese. Freeze remaining sauce.
Makes 2 quarts.

title: brown bread
directions: Sift flours, sugar, soda and salt together.
Add molasses and sour milk; stir well.
Pour into greased loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: green rice salad
directions: Bring rice, water and 1 teaspoon salt to a boil.
Cover and reduce heat; simmer 20 minutes.
Remove from heat and let stand 20 minutes.
