Beat together vinegar and mustard; beat in oil, then sugar, remaining 1/2 teaspoon salt and pepper, stirring until sugar dissolves.
Add rice and toss until well coated with dressing.
Add celery, green onion, dill, mint and parsley and toss.
Add peas and toss again.
Serve at room temperature.

title: hot sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Cook 45 to 60 minutes over medium heat. Pour into jars and seal.

title: vegetarian lentil soup(serves 6 to 8)
directions: Put washed lentils in large pot; add water, prepared vegetables and seasonings.
Bring to a gentle boil over medium heat; reduce heat and allow to simmer until well done, about 1 hour.
Remove bay leaves and serve.

title: cranberry souffle
directions: Butter a glass dish.
Add the following in layers: half cranberries, half apples, half of each kind of sugar, half of oatmeal and nuts.
Repeat.
Pour melted margarine over.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: hurry-up jelly
directions: Pour Kool-Aid, Sure-Jel and water in a heavy pot.
Stir until dissolved.
Place over heat.
Bring to boil, stirring constantly. Add sugar.
Stir and bring to boil again.
Remove from heat.
Pour into jars.
Seal to cover with paraffin.

title: pineapple cottage cheese salad
directions: Place pineapple with juice in a pot and let it heat up to a boil.
Add jello, stir until dissolved.
Set aside until cool. Mix Cool Whip and cottage cheese together.
Add cool pineapple mix. Beat with the mixer until fluffy.
Pour into a bowl and chill. Good as a dessert or part of the main course.

title: seasonal tortillas(can't eat just one!)
directions: Combine ham, chilies, green onion, Cheddar, salsa, salt and sour cream; mix well.
Lay tortilla flat and place 3 tablespoons mixture in one spot about an inch inside the edge of tortilla and then roll semi-tight, spreading mixture as you roll.
Repeat for remaining tortillas.
Wrap in foil (2 rolls per foil package) and refrigerate.
Best served 8 to 24 hours after prepared.
Remove tortilla rolls and cut into 1 1/2-inch portions.
In the summer serve cold.
In winter, bake 15 minutes at 325° (in foil) or microwave 1 minute.
Serve hot and enjoy!

title: biscotti(cookies)
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add egg and almond extract.
Sift in dry ingredients.
Add oil and water.
Add nuts.
This makes a stiff dough.
Divide dough into 3 logs and place on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake 26 to 29 minutes at 350°, until lightly browned.
Remove from oven and slice diagonally into 3/8-inch pieces.
Toast again, if you prefer a crisp cookie.
(If dough seems too creamy, drop by teaspoons onto ungreased sheet; if watching sugar content, decrease sugar to 1/2 cup.)

title: great scots
directions: Sift together sifted flour, salt, cinnamon and baking soda; set aside.
Combine in bowl the sugar, soft butter and eggs; beat until creamy.
Gradually add flour mixture alternately with milk. Stir in rolled oats, butterscotch morsels, raisins and chopped nuts.
Drop by tablespoonfuls onto greased cookie sheets.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 14 minutes.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: honey mustard pork chops
directions: Melt butter.
Pour into shallow baking dish.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix juice, honey and mustard in small bowl.
Sprinkle chops with salt.
Place in dish.
Arrange carrots and potatoes around chops.
Pour honey-mustard mixture over all. Bake 35 to 40 minutes or until chops are tender.

title: barbecued meat balls
directions: Crumble bread in milk; add salt and pepper to ground meat. Form into medium balls; place them in a small casserole dish. Combine remaining ingredients and pour over the meat balls.
Bake 45 minutes at 375°.
Yield:
4 to 6 servings.
Recipe can be doubled.
One-half cup of hickory smoked barbecue sauce may be substituted for 1/2 cup catsup.

title: rustic rub for meat
directions: Combine all ingredients and store in an air tight container.

title: shrimp etouffee
directions: Make a "roux" by mixing 1/2 cup flour with 1 stick melted margarine in heavy pan.
Stir over medium heat until flour begins to brown.
Set aside.

title: peach sweet potato puffs
directions: Measure 2 cups of mashed sweet potatoes.
Combine potatoes and the next 5 ingredients; stir until well mixed.
Spoon mixture into peach halves.
Put in baking dish and bake at 400° for 15 minutes, or until heated.
Top with miniature marshmallows and leave in oven long enough to melt.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in a bowl.
Cook broccoli.
Start with cheese mixture and layer.
Be sure to end with cheese mixture.
Melt butter in a saucepan and stir in stuffing mix.
Put on top of casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: dried fruit stack cake
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In a large bowl, cream butter and sugar.
Stir in molasses, then beat in eggs, one at a time.
In another bowl, combine dry ingredients and add to creamed mixture with the milk.
Spoon half of batter into three greased pans. Bake for 15 to 20 minutes.
Repeat process with remaining batter. Cool on wire rack.
Add spices to taste to cooked dried apples and spread between layers.
Dust top with powdered sugar.
Makes 6 layers.

title: graham cracker crust
directions: Combine and press into pie pan.
(May keep 1/4 cup of this mix to put on top as garnish.)
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: cranberry sauce
directions: Chop cranberries in blender; cover with sugar.
Let set overnight in refrigerator.
Add remaining ingredients.

title: overnight lettuce salad
directions: Chop and mix lettuce, celery, onion and water chestnuts.
Put in 9 x 13-inch pan as a bottom layer.
Add a layer of frozen peas. Frost generously with mayonnaise.
Fry bacon and sprinkle on top. Add shredded cheese.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: homemade salsa
directions: Throw everything together in a 6 to 8-quart pan and bring to a boil. Reduce heat; boil gently, uncovered, 30 minutes. Cook longer if you want it thicker. Great with tortilla chips or other snack food. Makes 6 pints.

title: buttermilk fudge
directions: Combine buttermilk, sugar and soda; let stand for 5 minutes. Add Karo and cook, stirring constantly, until mixture forms soft ball in cold water.
Add margarine, vanilla and nuts; beat well. Spoon onto greased pan.

title: southern potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except margarine.
Pour mixed ingredients into a greased 3-quart baking dish.
Pour margarine over mixture.
Bake at 375°, covered, for 30 minutes and uncovered for 30 minutes.

title: italian quiche
directions: Prebake unpricked pie crust on preheated cookie sheet in 450° oven for 6 minutes.
Remove pie crust from oven; reduce oven temperature to 325°.

title: 7 layer bean dip
directions: In a large glass baking dish, spread ingredients one at a time in layers.
Chill and serve with tortilla chips.

title: chili
directions: Brown first 5 ingredients.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer for 3 to 4 hours.
Serve with grated Cheddar cheese and corn bread.

title: easy supper dish
directions: Melt margarine in saucepan over low heat.
Add macaroni and stir to coat
thoroughly
with
butter.
Add 2 cups tomato juice and bring to a
rapid
boil.
Stir	in ground beef.
Add salt, pepper and sugar.
Cover
and reduce heat and cook 15 to 20 minutes.
Remove cover and stir.
Sprinkle cheese over top. Remove from heat, cover
so
cheese
will	melt.
A
tossed or fruit salad will complete the meal.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Cream together butter and sugar.
Add eggs and beat well.
Mix in powder, soda, salt, cloves, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Add pumpkin. Slowly mix in flour.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream butter and sugar together until fluffy.
Beat in eggs. Blend in bananas.
Sift dry ingredients together and add to the creamed mixture.
Add nuts.
Place in greased loaf pan, 9 x 5 x 3-inches.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 1 hour.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: beef-a-roni
directions: Cook meat, salt to taste, onion and pepper together and drain. Cook the macaroni separately and drain.
Mix together the macaroni and meat mixture.
Put into a casserole dish.
Top with tomato sauce and slices of cheese.
Brown in the oven.
For a richer taste add a jar of Cheez Whiz to the noodles mixture.

title: granny's pickled beets
directions: Cook beets until fork-tender. Slip skins off and slice to desired size. Add beets and remaining ingredients to liquid and bring almost to a boil. Turn heat down but keep everything very hot, including jars, caps and lids. Put beets in hot jars and they will seal.

title: super moist cornbread
directions: Mix corn meal, flour, sugar and soda. Add egg, milk and butter. Mix well and pour into a buttered iron skillet. Bake at 425 degrees for 25 minutes or
until golden brown. Remove cornbread immediately from skillet.

title: lemon pie
directions: Blend together flour, oleo and nuts.
Press in 10 x 10 x 3-inch pan (square).
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes or until brown.
Beat together cheese and sugar and fold in 1 cup Cool Whip.
Spread on cooled crust.
Mix together pudding and milk. Let stand 5 minutes or until thickened.
Pour over cheese 1 layer and top with 1 cup Cool Whip.
Chill 30 minutes or until firm.

title: fours
directions: Place first 5 ingredients in pan.
Bring to boil.
Add whipping cream and cook to medium-hard boil or 232°.
Add nuts and vanilla.
Pour into two greased 9-inch pans.
Cool and cut into squares. Dip in chocolate.

title: pagachi pizza
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease pizza pan.
Follow directions on pizza mix package.
Place dough in pan and work flat.
Spread butter on dough (if desired).
Mix together mashed potatoes and onion dip until smooth.
Place mixture on dough and spread evenly. Add onions, garlic and cheese to taste.
Bake in 400° oven 17 to 22 minutes until golden brown.
Slice and serve.
Makes 8 to 10 slices.

title: cream puffs
directions: Heat water and butter to a rolling boil.
Stir in flour and sugar until mixture forms a ball.
Remove from heat.
Beat in eggs, one at a time with an electric beater until smooth.
Drop 1/4 cupfuls of dough on an ungreased cookie sheet 3 inches apart. Bake at 400° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Remove immediately to cool.

title: hearty lentil stew
directions: In 6-quart Dutch oven, saute carrots, escarole, onion and celery in oil for 3 to 4 minutes.
Add chicken broth, tomato juice, lentils, kielbasa and thyme.
Bring to a boil. Cover and reduce heat.
Simmer 25 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Season to taste.

title: potato bread
directions: Soften yeast in warm water.
Add the potato water and cooled milk.
Next, add the salt, 1/2 cup sugar and 4 cups flour.
Mix well and add shortening and 8 more cups flour.
Mix until smooth. Place dough in large, greased bowl.
Cover and let rise to double.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken until tender.
Place chicken in a greased 9 x 13 baking dish.
Mix sour cream and soup and pour over chicken. Sprinkle with stuffing mix.
Pour broth over stuffing mix.
Add margarine.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: boneless buffalo wings
directions: Combine flour, salt, peppers and paprika in a medium bowl. In another small bowl, whisk together egg and milk.
Slice each chicken breast into 6 pieces. Preheat 4-6 cups of vegetable oil in a deep fryer to 375 degrees.
One or two at a time, dip each piece of chicken into the egg mixture, then into the breading blend; then repeat the process so that each piece of chicken is double-coated.
When all chicken pieces have been breaded, arrange them on a plate and chill for 15 minutes.
When the chicken is done resting, drop each piece into the hot oil and fry for 5-6 minutes or until each piece is browned.

As chicken fries, combine the hot sauce and margarine in a small bowl. Microwave sauce for 20-30 seconds or just until the margarine is melted, then stir to combine. You can also use a small saucepan for this step. Just combine the hot sauce and margarine in the saucepan over low heat and stir until margarine is melted and ingredients are blended. When chicken pieces are done frying, remove them to a plate lined with a couple paper towels.

Place the chicken pieces into a covered container such as a large jar with a lid. Pour the sauce over the chicken in the container, cover, and then shake gently until each piece of chicken is coated with sauce. Pour the chicken onto a plate and serve the dish with bleu cheese dressing and sliced celery on the side.

title: corn salad
directions: Mix together with enough Miracle Whip to moisten.
Add Fritos just before serving.

title: orange cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients well and spoon by tablespoon balls onto cookie sheets about 2-inches apart.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: squash casserole
directions: Brown the sausage patties and place on paper towels to drain and cool.
Slice the onions and squash.
Boil together in a small amount of water until done.
Drain and mash, then add salt and pepper.
Break up the sausage patties and mix with the eggs, tomatoes, onions and squash.
Pour into a casserole and top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes.

title: pineapple cheese cake
directions: Line spring-form pan (bottom and sides) with ladyfingers. Beat together sugar and cream cheese.
Whip the cream until stiff; fold into cream cheese.
Alternate layers of cream cheese and pineapple, ending with pineapple.
Reserve 1 heaping spoonful of cream cheese to dollop on top.
Refrigerate.

title: potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes until done or soft.
Add mayo, pepper, salt, sugar and vinegar.
Chop up 2 hard-cooked eggs.
If you want, add chopped onion.
Mix all together!
Chill in fridge.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients well, except pecans.
Shape into ball or log; roll in nuts.
Keep in refrigerator.

title: peas-asparagus casserole
directions: Melt butter.
Stir in flour.
Gradually add milk and cook, stirring until smooth.
Add cheese and stir until blended.
Place asparagus in bottom of buttered 2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle with 1/4 cup crumbs.
Add peas.
Sprinkle with more crumbs.
Add mushrooms.
Add remaining crumbs.
Pour sauce over all.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 20 minutes or until heated through. Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: golden puffs
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Stir in buttermilk, oil and egg with fork.
Beat until smooth.
Drop by teaspoonful into hot 375° fat.
Do not make too large as they will not cook through.
Fry until golden brown, about 3 minutes.
Drain on brown paper.
Roll while warm in sugar.
Makes 2 1/2 dozen.
You can dip in warm chocolate glaze and sprinkle with coconut or nuts or make an orange glaze.

title: chicken and beans
directions: Sticks chicken in oven and cook 50 minutes.

title: impossible coconut pie
directions: Blend sugar and flour into beaten eggs.
Stir in rest of ingredients.
Pour into greased pie pan, not shell.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until pie is brown.
Makes 2 pies.

title: barm brack("barm" is the old word for yeast.)
directions: All utensils should be warm before starting brack.
Sift flour, spices and salt together, then rub in the butter.
Cream yeast with 1 teaspoon sugar and 1 teaspoon tepid milk.
It should froth up; if it does not it means yeast is old and stale.
Add rest of sugar to flour mixture.
Blend well.
Then pour tepid milk and beaten egg onto yeast mixture and combine with flour, etc.
Beat well with dough hook in warmed bowl of electric mixer.
Batter should be stiff, but elastic.
Fold in dried fruit and chopped peel.
Cover with cloth.
Leave in warm place until dough doubles.
Turn out and divide into 2 portions.
Grease 2 (7-inch) cake tins.
One portion in each tin.
Cover and leave to rise (about 30 minutes).
Bake at 400° for about 1 hour.
Test with skewer.
Glaze top with 1 tablespoon sugar, dissolved in 2 tablespoons boiling water.
Put in hot oven for about 3 minutes.
Turn out to cool on wire tray.
When cool, serve buttered slices.
It keeps very well, but if it gets stale, it is very good toasted and served with butter.

title: baked pineapple
directions: Mix sugar, flour and salt together.
Beat eggs and add pineapple, then add this to the flour mixture.
Put this mixture into casserole dish.
Melt margarine and add bread cubes.
Toss to moisten.
Sprinkle cubes on top of pineapple mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: spicy zucchini bread
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients.
Make a well in the center and add the last 5 ingredients, stirring just until moistened.
Bake in a 350° oven (may vary) for 1 hour.
Cool in pans.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: pecan pie
directions: Cream together butter and sugar.
Add eggs and beat well.
Add Karo syrup and beat well.
Add vanilla flavoring and pecans.
Pour into unbaked pie shells and top with pecan halves.
Cook at 400° for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and cook another hour.
Makes 2 pies.

title: hamburger patties with gravy
directions: Shape beef into 7 patties (1/2-inch thick).
Salt and pepper and dip in flour.
Brown in skillet.
Add water and chipped onion. Simmer for 15 minutes with top on skillet.
Makes 7 servings.

title: clam chowder
directions: Simmer clams in large pot.
Meanwhile, saute onions in 1/4 cup butter until tender; add paprika.
Boil potatoes in separate pot until tender.
Add onions and potatoes to clams, then add evaporated milk and remaining butter.
Extra cans of clams and more potatoes can be added. Cook on low until butter melts. Serves 8.

title: pumpkin cookies
directions: Stir together eggs, sugar, shortening, vanilla and pumpkin. (I use an electric mixer.) Mix in a separate bowl the flour, soda, baking powder, salt and cinnamon. Add flour mixture to pumpkin mixture, a cup at a time, to make sure it gets mixed thoroughly. Drop by spoonfuls onto a greased cookie sheet. (I use Reynolds Wrap nonstick release.) Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: apple-bread pudding
directions: In grease 1-quart baking dish, mix eggs, sugar, cinnamon and salt.
Stir in milk.
Add bread and apple.
Stir gently to combine.
Let stand 5 minutes for bread to absorb liquid.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 45 minutes or until knife inserted comes out clean.
Let stand 15 minutes before serving.
Makes 4 servings.

title: black walnut bars
directions: Mix flour, brown sugar and margarine until crumbly.
Press in well-greased cookie sheet or 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Remove and cool for 10 minutes.
Turn oven to 375°.

title: walnut pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat eggs, vanilla, sugar and butter for 3 minutes at medium speed.
Add milk.
Sift dry ingredients together and add to mixture.
Beat one minute.

title: fresh apple pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Mix sugar, oil and eggs.
Slowly stir in flour, apples and vanilla.
Add nuts and coconut.
Pour into a Bundt pan.
Mixture will be thick.
Bake for approximately 1 hour 20 minutes.

title: sweet and super salad dressing
directions: Combine the first 4 ingredients with wire whip.
Add onions. Gradually add oil while beating.
Add celery seed.
Refrigerate. Good on tossed salads (greens).

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Rinse sauerkraut with cold water; drain well.
Add celery, onions, pepper, sugar, oil and vinegar.
Mix and let stand in refrigerator at least overnight.
Serve.

title: silly putty
directions: In the palm of one hand, sprinkle a small amount of powdered hand soap.
Add a few drops of water to dissolve soap.
Stir with a finger to make a thin paste.
Add a few drops of white glue directly onto soap paste and mix thoroughly.
Paste will soon change properties to those of plastic putty.

title: chocolate peanut butter puffs
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Lightly grease 20 mini muffin cups or large cookie sheet.
Separate dough into 10 biscuits.
Separate each biscuit into 2 layers.
Remove paper from candies; place 1 candy on each biscuit piece.
Fold dough over candy, covering completely.
Seal well.
Place seam side down in prepared pan. Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes or until golden brown.
Remove from pan.
Combine sugar, cocoa and cinnamon.
Roll puffs in sugar mixture to coat.
Makes 20 puffs.

title: cocktail wieners
directions: Cut wieners into 3/4-inch pieces.
Set aside.
Combine sauce, sugar and seasoning in 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Cover. Microwave at High 1 1/2 to 2 1/2 minutes, until hot.
Stir in wieners; cover.
Microwave 4 to 6 minutes, stirring once.
When hot, serve with cocktail picks.

title: fettuccine alfredo(italian)
directions: Cook fettuccine according to package directions. While fettuccine cooks, heat butter (or margarine) and cream in small saucepan until butter melts.
Stir in Parmesan cheese, salt and pepper.
Keep warm over low heat. Drain fettuccine. Return to pan. Pour sauce over noodles. Toss gently until noodles are well coated. Serve.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: chicken arcadia
directions: Combine dressing and oleo and place a little over half in the bottom of a casserole dish, reserving the rest.
Mix together chicken, celery, water chestnuts, onion, cream of mushroom, cream of celery, milk, salt and pepper.
Pour this mixture over dressing mixture and top with reserved crumbs.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Remove foil and bake 15 minutes longer. This can be made ahead and frozen.

title: oatmeal bars
directions: Combine butter and sugar in a saucepan; cook and stir until butter melts.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Pour into greased 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for 20 to 25 minutes.
Cool; cut into 24 bars.

title: strawberry pizza
directions: Blend flour, powdered sugar and margarine.
Pat firmly into 16-inch round pizza pan and bake 12 minutes at 325°.
Beat together cream cheese, vanilla, the 1/2 cup sugar and lemon juice. Spread on cooled crust.
Cook until thick, the strawberries, cornstarch and 8 tablespoons sugar.
Cool and spread on top of cream cheese layer.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: chili
directions: In large pot, brown ground beef.
Add salt and pepper.
Drain grease from meat.
Add tomato juice, tomatoes, kidney beans, onion and celery.
Combine remaining spices.
Cook over medium heat for 1 hour.
Cook on low for 2 hours.
Serve with crackers.

title: dana's chicken and rice
directions: Spray dish with Pam. Place rice/soup mixture into pan and then put chicken on top. Sprinkle dry soup mix on top. Cover with foil. Bake at 350° for 1 1/4 hours.

title: rye bread
directions: Combine scalded milk, salt, sugar, shortening and molasses. Cool to lukewarm.
Soften yeast in 1 cup of lukewarm water and add to milk mixture.
Blend in all flour and knead dough on floured board.
To obtain a fine grain, knead about 7 minutes.
Place dough in greased bowl and cover.
Let rise in a warm place for about 1 1/2 hours.

title: crab claiborne
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease
9 x 9-inch (Corning Ware type) pan with
butter.
Thoroughly
mix together all ingredients, except crab, cheese
and
paprika.	Fold in crab; put in pan. Sprinkle cheese
over the mixture, then sprinkle paprika over all. Bake at
until golden brown.
Enjoy!
This is good hot or cold.

title: chicken roll supreme
directions: Wrap each chicken breast with dried beef.
Wrap 1 strip of bacon around chicken breast and hold with toothpick.
Mix sour cream and soup together.
Spread over chicken.
Cook at 350° for at least 1 hour.

title: calico salad
directions: Drain canned vegetables. Combine all ingredients and chill at least 24 hours.

title: crunchie cookies
directions: Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.

title: chocolate sponge cake supreme
directions: Preheat oven to 350°F.
Butter and flour a 10-inch baking pan.

title: gumbo casserole
directions: Brown in skillet ground beef and onion.
Mix other ingredients and add to ground beef and onion.
Bake in casserole dish for 30 minutes at 300°.
Remove from oven and sprinkle cheese and paprika on top.

title: refrigerator mashed potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes in boiling salted water.
Drain well.
Mash until smooth.
Add cream cheese, sour cream, onion salt, pepper and oleo. Beat until smooth and fluffy.
Refrigerate.
Recommend storage 2 weeks.
Dot with butter.
Bake about 30 or 40 minutes or until heated through.
Makes 8 cups.
I used an 8 x 10-inch Corning Ware.

title: ballerina sugar cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
In a large bowl, cream butter and sugar with electric mixer.
Beat in eggs and vanilla.
Add baking powder and flour, one cup at a time, mixing after each addition.
The dough will be very stiff.
It may be necessary to blend the last flour in by hand.
Roll dough and cut with your favorite cookie cutter.
Sprinkle with colored sugar.
Place cookies on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 6 to 7 minutes until light brown.

title: salsa de baracoa
directions: Cook onion and garlic in oil until tender.
Add remaining ingredients and boil for 3 minutes, or until thick.
Pour over broiling or roasting meat, or use as a sauce for reheating cold meat.
Serve hot.
Makes about 2-1/4 c. sauce.

title: pineapple pound cake
directions: Mix the pineapple and pudding; let stand a few minutes.
Add the Cool Whip.
Spread the mixture between layers of pound cake. After top of cake is spread with mixture, sprinkle with nuts, cherries, etc.
Use your imagination.

title: broccoli & cauliflower salad
directions: Combine chopped ingredients. Toss with dressing.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Layer ingredients in order listed above in a 9 x 12 inch casserole dish.
Bake at 350 degrees for 1 1/2 hours or until golden brown.

title: orange cream pie
directions: Mix all ingredients
together
(can
be mixed by hand). Pour into crust and
freeze
or
refrigerate.
Can
be
served frozen or not.
Also, you may want to decorate top of pie with a little Cool Whip.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix 1 stick of melted margarine with graham cracker crumbs and press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Then beat eggs, powdered sugar and 2 sticks of margarine until creamy (do not underbeat).

Spread this over the graham cracker crumbs, then put your sliced bananas over that, then your well drained pineapple over the sliced bananas. Spread the Cool Whip over pineapple, then sprinkle chopped nuts over that.
Chill.
You can dot with a cherry for every serving.

title: angel hair with sun-dried tomatoes and basil sauce
directions: Heat oil and butter in a large skillet over medium heat.
Add garlic and cook 1 minute.
Add remaining ingredients except pasta and cheese to skillet, making sure peppers are roasted and cut into thin strips.
Toss and just barely heat.
Add to pasta in large bowl; toss to coat.
Pass Romano cheese.
Makes 4 first course servings

title: fudge
directions: Melt chocolate chips in condensed milk.
Add vanilla, salt and walnuts.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Cool in refrigerator.

title: punch
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients together and freeze.
Remove from freezer six hours before serving.
When served, add 1 package frozen strawberries and 1 small can pineapple.

title: carrot cake
directions: In a mixing bowl, combine dry ingredients.
Add eggs, oil, carrots and vanilla.
Beat until combined.
Stir in pineapple, coconut and 1/2 cup nuts.
Pour into greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Frost with Cream Cheese Frosting when cool.

title: one pan sweet potato bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease loaf pan (9 x 5 x 3-inches).
Stir all ingredients, except raisins, in a bowl with fork until moistened.
Beat vigorously for 1 minute.
Stir in raisins.
Pour in loaf pan.
Bake until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean, 45 to 55 minutes.
Cool 5 minutes.

title: potato refrigerator rolls
directions: In bowl, dissolve yeast in water.
Stir in sugar, salt, shortening, eggs and potatoes.
Measure flour and mix with fork. Turn onto floured surface.
Knead until smooth and elastic. Grease bowl and place in refrigerator.
About 2 hours before baking, shape dough into rolls.
Cover and let rise until double in size, about 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Heat oven to 400° and bake 12 to 15 minutes.
Makes 4 dozen medium rolls.

title: strawberry rhubarb cobbler
directions: In large pan combine sugar and cornstarch.
Stir in berries and rhubarb, lemon juice and margarine.
Cook over medium heat, stirring until bubbly and slightly thickened.
Pour into 2-quart casserole.
Separate biscuit dough into 10; cut each in half with scissors.
Arrange cut side down on hot fruit mixture in circle. Sprinkle with sugar-cinnamon.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes until biscuits brown.

title: fruit cake
directions: Cut up fruit and nuts; add coconut.
Dredge in flour.
Cream oleo and sugar; add eggs.
Add flavorings, flour, baking powder and liquid.
Pour over fruit mixture; mix well.
Put in pan or pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: boiled fruit cake
directions: Blend very well, then put mixture into greased and lined cake tin (8-inch in diameter) and bake at 250° for about 2 hours.
This is a good moist cake which keeps very well.
Chopped nuts may be added, if desired.

title: barbecue ribs
directions: Cook ribs 3/4 done; add rest of ingredients and continue cooking until done.

title: lemon chiffon pie
directions: Add
sugar,
juice
and rind and water to the egg yolks. Cook in double boiler, stirring constantly, until thickened and mixture coats
the
spoon.
Remove from heat.
Beat egg whites and salt until stiff but not dry.
Add sugar by tablespoonfuls, beating after each addition.
Pour custard into meringue, when well blended pour into baked pie shell.
Bake in slow 325° oven for about 20 minutes, or until set.
Cool before cutting.

title: fruitcake cookies
directions: Dredge fruit and nuts in flour.
Add salt and coconut.
Add milk and mix thoroughly.
Drop by spoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes in preheated oven at 270°.
Store cooled cookies in an airtight container for about 5 days.
Makes about 4 dozen.

title: squash casserole
directions: Drain squash.
Add vegetables, sour cream and soup.
Mix well. In serving dish, mix stuffing and butter.
Line bottom with stuffing, reserving enough to sprinkle on top.
Add squash mixture and top with remaining stuffing.
Bake in oven at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: cheesy chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cut each chicken wing into 3 sections at joints.
Discard pointed ends.
Place remaining ingredients into a large zipper plastic bag.
Drop chicken in bag to coat each piece.
Place on well-greased baking sheet; bake for 1 hour. Makes about 24 appetizers.

title: funnel cakes
directions: Pour oil 1 1/2 inches in a large skillet.
Heat to 375° over medium-high heat.
Cover bottom opening of funnel with finger. (Funnel with a 3/8-inch opening works best.)
Pour 1/4 cup batter into funnel; hold funnel over skillet.
Remove finger from funnel end to release batter into hot oil, moving funnel in a slow circle so that batter forms a spiral.
Fry 1 minute or until edges are golden brown.
Turn and fry until golden.
Drain on paper towels. Repeat with remaining batter.
Sprinkle with confectioners sugar.

title: deep dish cobbler
directions: Melt margarine in deep baking dish.
Mix flour, sugar and milk and pour over margarine.
Bake at 350° for approximately 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Will brown on top.

title: baked haddock filets with sour cream
directions: Season filets with salt and pepper.
Stir all but filets well. Spread over filets in buttered, shallow dish.
Bake for 10 minutes or until bubbly and fish flakes.

title: chocolate filling
directions: Mix together and spread on cake layers.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together except for 1/2 c. shredded cheese. Spread with pam Bake at 375° for 45 minutes then sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Bake for additional 10 to 25 minutes.

title: chocolate cream cheese fudge
directions: Place cream cheese in bowl and cream until soft and smooth. Slowly blend sugar into cheese. Add vanilla, salt and pecans; mix well until blended. Press into a well-greased shallow pan. Refrigerate until firm. Cut into squares.

title: fettuccine alfredo
directions: Cook fettuccine according to package instructions, omitting salt.
Drain well; place in a large bowl.

title: scripture cake
directions: Beat together the butter, sugar and honey.
Beat the egg yolks and add sifted flour, baking powder, spices and salt alternately with the milk.
Stir in the figs, raisins and almonds.
Fold in the 6 egg whites which have been beaten stiff.
Bake the cake in a well greased 10-inch tube pan.
Lining the pan with greased brown paper may provide added protection.
Bake at 300° for 2 hours.

title: green bean soup
directions: Wash, cut and cook if raw beans are used.
In a frypan add oil; cook onion until tender.
Add ground beef; brown and cook until evenly cooked.
Drain off grease.
Add salt and pepper.
Do not drain beans.
Combine with the tomatoes in saucepan.
Simmer 3/4 of an hour.
(Better the second day.)

title: black bottom cupcakes
directions: Mix cream cheese, egg, 1/2 cup sugar and pinch of salt.
Add chocolate chips; set aside.

title: cheesecake
directions: Mix graham cracker crumbs and margarine together.
Reserve 1/3 cup for topping.
Press remainder into 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan or Pyrex dish.
In large bowl blend (with electric mixer) the pineapple, sugar, dry jello and cream cheese.
Then fold in whipped topping.
Pour over crumb mixture.
Sprinkle top with reserved crumbs.
Refrigerate overnight.
Cut into squares to serve.

title: irish soda bread
directions: Combine flour, soda, powder, 3 tablespoons sugar and caraway seed.
Add shortening, cut until shortening is in fine pieces. Make a well in center of flour mixture.
Pour buttermilk and add raisins, mix lightly.
Turn out on floured board and knead gently. Shape into 5-inch round loaf and place in greased 8 or 9-inch pan.
Using knife, cut dough crosswise into quarters about 1/3 the way through.
Brush with melted butter, sprinkle with cinnamon and remaining sugar.
Bake at 375° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: mother's cookies
directions: Blend shortening, butter, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Sift together in separate bowl the soda, cream of tartar, salt and flour.
Slowly beat dry ingredients into shortening mixture until well blended and texture is creamy.
Drop by 1 teaspoonful on greased cookie sheet.
Press cookie dough with a fork dipped in cold water.
Add sprinkles if desired.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Mix in casserole dish and top with Durkee French fried onions. Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: pecan pie
directions: Cream butter and sugar together.
Add next four ingredients and mix well.
Add coarsely broken nutmeats.
Pour into unbaked pie shell and bake in preheated 450° oven for 5 minutes.
Reduce heat and bake at 350° until filling is firm.
I put strips of foil on edge of pie crust to keep from browning too much.

title: ham and cheese rolls
directions: Mix the last 5 ingredients.
This will make a paste.
Split entire package of rolls at once, lengthwise.
You should have a bottom and top, like a sandwich.
Leave the bottom half in the aluminum pan.
Spread 1/3 of the paste on the bottom half of rolls. Top with 1/3 of chopped ham and 1/3 of cheese.
Do the same with the other 2 packages of rolls.
You can cover and freeze for later use.

title: party cheese ball
directions: Soften cheeses and beat all ingredients, except parsley, together.
Form into a ball and roll in parsley.
Refrigerate 8 hours.

title: mcdonnell's favorite pecan pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Blend eggs.
Add sugar, salt and corn syrup.
Add cooled melted butter and vanilla.
Blend gently.
Pour filling into shell.
Top neatly with pecan halves.
Place pie in oven.
Reduce heat to 350° at once!
Bake 50 to 60 minutes.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: eileen davis' potato casserole
directions: Warm Velveeta, mayonnaise and milk in a big pot on stove, mixing often.
Add onions and bacon; mix well.
Add potatoes and mix well.
Pour in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
May refrigerate to bake later.

title: rice-a-roni salad
directions: Cook Rice-A-Roni according to directions on package; cool. Add remaining ingredients to the rice and mix thoroughly with mayonnaise until moist.

title: butter cookies
directions: Combine ingredients; mix well.
Make into a roll; wrap and refrigerate for about an hour.
Slice about 1/4 inch thick and bake at 375° for 8 minutes.

title: granny durand's red velvet cake
directions: Sift together flour, cocoa and salt 2 or 3 times.
Set aside. Beat together (using electric mixer) the sugar, cooking oil, then beat in red food coloring.
Add eggs one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add buttermilk and flour alternately.
Add vanilla.
Fold in vinegar mixed in soda.
Pour into 3 well-greased and floured cake pans.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Cool and frost. Yield:
1 (3 layer) cake.

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: Put broccoli in water and cook until done and set aside.
In Dutch oven, saute onion in oleo; stir in flour.
Add bouillon packs; add pepper (several shakes).
Add skim milk.
Heat and stir.
Add broccoli mix.
Simmer 25 to 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: chicken in the pot
directions: Put chicken in kettle.
Add water and remaining ingredients. Bring to a boil.
Cover tightly.
Reduce heat and simmer 1 hour or until tender.
Remove from heat.
Strain broth.
Refrigerate chicken and broth at once. When chicken is cool, remove from bone and cut into small pieces.

title: hamburger gravy
directions: In a large skillet, brown meat over medium until it is starting to brown. Add onion soup mix; stir. Cook until meat is brown, about 5 minutes more. Sprinkle flour over the top and mix in. Slowly add water and mix until gravy is as thick as you like. Stir in any veggies.

title: seven layer salad
directions: Layer lettuce, thawed English peas, onion, celery and pepper in this order in a salad bowl.
Mix sour cream, mayonnaise and sugar together.
Pour over vegetables, covering the top. Refrigerate overnight.
Before serving, top with grated cheese and bacon.

title: johnnycake
directions: Mix flour, baking powder, salt, sugar and corn meal.
Mix well.
Combine eggs and milk; add to flour mixture.
Add shortening and mix.
Turn into greased, 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake in hot oven (400°) for 30 minutes.

title: sauerbraten
directions: Mix last 9 ingredients together and marinate meat for 24 to 36 hours.
Strain marinade and put 1 cup over meat; cook in crock-pot until done.
Remove meat and put 12 crushed gingersnaps into the broth to make gravy (use small gingersnaps).

title: chicken vegetable noodle soup
directions: In a large kettle, combine water, chicken, onion, bay leaf, 2 teaspoons salt and 1/4 teaspoon pepper.
Bring to boiling; reduce heat.
Cover; simmer about 2 hours or until chicken is tender. Remove chicken.
When cool enough, cut off meat and cube chicken. Discard bones and skin.
Skim fat from broth and discard.
Add tomatoes, corn and zucchini to broth.
Bring to boiling.
Stir in noodles.
Reduce heat.
Cover; simmer about 3 minutes.
Stir in chicken.
Cover and simmer until noodles are tender and soup is heated through.

title: eggless raisin cake
directions: Boil raisins in 2 cups of water until you have one cup of juice left, then mix your cake with the one cup of raisins and juice.
Add nuts.
Bake very slow to prevent burning at 350°.

title: fantasy fudge
directions: Combine sugar, margarine and milk. Bring to a rolling boil, stirring constantly.
Boil 5 minutes over medium heat, stirring continuously (mixture scorches easily).
Remove from heat; add peanut butter and stir until blended.
Add Marshmallow Creme, nuts and vanilla.
Blend well.
Pour onto a greased cookie sheet. Cool and cut into squares.

title: multi-grain pancake syrup
directions: Blend fruit and juice in blender until smooth.
Simmer for 5 minutes.
Mix water and arrowroot until smooth and add to fruit; simmer 2 more minutes or until thick.
Cool and serve.
Bananas do not work well in syrup.

title: sour milk cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add egg, beating well.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Add alternately with buttermilk and vanilla.
Bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes.
Use 10-inch tube pan for best results.
No icing.
Good served warm with coffee.

title: pink salad
directions: Mix condensed milk and lemon juice until thick.
Mix gently the remaining ingredients in and chill several hours or overnight.

title: caribbean salsa or salad
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients in a large bowl; mix thoroughly.
Add salt, cumin, pepper, lemon juice, minced garlic and cilantro.
Can be used as a salad or a salsa with corn chips.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Drain beans; put into casserole dish.
Place onion rings over beans.
Fry bacon and place over beans and onion.
Sprinkle almonds over bacon.
Pour celery soup over this.
Heat vinegar, sugar and bacon drippings and put on top of all ingredients.
Let set a while, then bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: green chili stew
directions: Brown and drain beef; set aside.
Dice tomatoes, onion and green chilies.
Combine all ingredients except cheese in a 5 quart saucepan and cook without stirring for 1 hour or until potatoes are tender.
Serve with grated cheese over the top.

title: kielbasa casserole
directions: Slice kielbasa up in 1/2-inch slices (bite-size).
Saute in skillet until brown.
Drain kielbasa.
Set aside.
Slice potatoes very thin.
Layer some potatoes on bottom of big casserole dish, then add some meat and 1 can soup.
Keep layering potatoes, meat, soup and potatoes.
Should cover meat on top.
Add 3rd can of soup to top.
Bake at 400° for about 1 1/2 hours or until potatoes are soft.
Stir every 1/2 hour.

title: grandma duryea's ice cream pumpkin pie
directions: Add sugar and vanilla to cream.
Blend.
Add remaining ingredients.
Blend thoroughly.
Put in freezer until frozen around edges.
Beat with electric mixer until smooth and fluffy.
Pour into crust.
Top with a few cracker crumbs.
Keep frozen until ready to serve.

title: chocolate swirl coffee cake
directions: Mix topping and set aside before mixing batter: coconut, chopped nuts, 1/4 c. sugar, 1 Tbsp. butter.

title: dirt cake
directions: Crumble cookies and sprinkle half in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix cream cheese and margarine until smooth.
Add sugar and fold in Cool Whip.

title: fancy fruit pizza
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Slice cookie dough as directed on package. Arrange slices in bottom of ungreased 15 x 10 x 1-inch baking pan.
Using floured fingers, press dough evenly into pan.
Bake for 12 to 15 minutes.
Cool.

title: fruit cocktail cookies
directions: Combine the shortening, sugars, eggs and vanilla.
Shut off mixer
and	add fruit cocktail by hand.
Sift together the flour, all
spices,
baking
powder and soda.
Add to ingredients.
Drop by	spoonfuls
on
greased cookie sheet and bake. Dough can
be used
right
away or refrigerate.
Do not place cookie dough to close together on cookie sheet because cookies will spread while baking.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes.
